(114,85,'This series of study is aimed at fortifying every member of TACEF in the foundational principles of Christ, which is the basis to become strong pillars in the great house and impactful agents of revival in our communities. We live in a time when the realities of God is fading so fast, as erroneous doctrines and inaccurate truths are being peddled with consequent shipwreck of the faith of many. The coming of the Lord is getting near and the best we need at a time like this is to be established in the timeless truth of the gospel of Christ. The implication of being rooted in the sure foundation of Christ will determine how far each of us will stand firm till the end.','2019-10-20 18:44:30');

(115,85,'Each study will explore the theological insight behind fundamental Christian truth, while also exploring emerging contemporary errors to be aware of. While some of these teachings may seem familiar, we must have the learning heart of 2 Peter 1 vs 12 “Wherefore I will not be negligent to put you always in remembrance of these things, though ye know them, and be established in the present truth”','2019-10-20 18:45:30');

(116,85,'This first study will help us to better understand who God is as the ultimate foundation of our lives. A man’s journey in God is as good as the knowledge he has of Him. When the foundation of the knowledge of God is missing in a life, such a life will collapse like packs of cards. The knowledge of God is beyond attending fellowships or keeping a prayer pattern. It is a journey of personal discovery and reality that nothing in this world can take away.','2019-10-20 18:46:30');

(117,85,'If you are in any kind of relationship with someone, you will get along better with that person the more you know who they are and understand their personality. It is no different in our relationship with God, so we must strive to get to know our Lord at the heart of who He is. The underlying topics are:','2019-10-20 18:47:30');

(118,86,'We cannot see God, yet we know that He is, through the physical evidence He has left with us in the natural world. “The invisible things of him from the creation of the world are clearly seen”, as Paul says in Romans 1:20. God wants a personal relationship with us as His creatures who He made in His own image and after His own likeness. The commitment and passion with which we immerse ourselves in an ongoing relationship with our Creator, will determine whether we stand or fall through the ungodliness of this present world and through the storms of life. The more we become intimate with Him, the sure the foundation of our lives.','2019-10-20 18:48:30');

(119,86,'The word ‘intimacy’ carries the meaning of closeness and endearment, beyond mere casual friendship. It speaks of depth. It speaks of something that is heart-to-heart and not just ordinary','2019-10-20 18:49:30');

(120,86,'It is not enough for us today to go to church, attend fellowships, sing praises, sow seeds into programmes and do other religious activities. All those things are good, but if we do not know God intimately, then, we have no firm and sure foundation. The risk of backsliding or compromise is high when we do not have a strong personal relationship with God. The underlying topics are:','2019-10-20 18:50:30');

(121,87,'This third week, the series of building firm foundation, deals with the dynamics involved in developing an efficient prayer-life and a vibrant scripture-life. Without personal Bible study and prayer, there is simply no relationship with God.','2019-10-20 18:51:30');

(122,87,'Most of us know we can access God through His Word and through prayer, but we must rightly understand how these two critical forces help our relationships with God. When we fail to understand how to maximise these tools as enablers of relationship with God, we will see instances of boring prayer life, unanswered prayers, incorrect application of Scripture, falling into false doctrines, and other such problems. We will look at proper ways to build our relationship with God in these two critical areas. The underlying topics are:','2019-10-20 18:52:30');

(123,88,'This study will focus on what it truly means to be “in Christ”. Many people claim to be born again but have never actually realised what that means. We are not talking about religion here, but about who Jesus is and what He has done for us through His death, burial, resurrection, ascension, and the outpouring of His Holy Spirit.','2019-10-20 18:53:30');

(124,88,'The Bible says “as many as received him, to them he gave power to become the children of God” (John 1:12). We will explore what this means for us and why that truth should direct our thinking and how we operate in this present world. The more we accept our identity, the more we fortify our foundation in God. A man who loses his sense of identity has lost the sense of his future. When we fail to understand who we are, the enemy can tell us who we are not and we believe and live in error. The underlying topics are:','2019-10-20 18:54:30');

(125,90,'The concept of salvation or “being born again” has been so commonised in our time to the extent of being misunderstood. In reality, the spiritual implication is getting lost on us. A street fighter has an inscription of “I am born again” on his T-shirt while a prostitute who sells her body wears a tattoo that reads, “I am redeemed”. It has been so cheapened and downgraded by the world that now we must define terms and be personally convinced that we have truly had the genuine experience.','2019-10-20 18:55:30');

(126,90,'It is important to emphasis the unchanging truth that without genuine salvation, no one can be a member of God’s kingdom. The underlying topics are:','2019-10-20 18:56:30');

(127,91,'We will be looking at restitution and why it is an important aspect of repentance. One cannot claim to be sorry for the wrong done to another without trying to fix the damage done.','2019-10-20 18:57:30');

(128,91,'Restitution is an act of making amends for wrongs done against our fellowmen; restoring stolen or misappropriated things, properties or persons to their rightful owners; paying back just debts, giving back where one has defrauded and making right what is wrong to have a conscience void of offence toward God and men. This is done whether the person injured knew or not, for God knows (Hebrews 4:13).','2019-10-20 18:58:30');

(129,91,'Restitution comes from a place of godly sorrow and a genuine desire to do what is right. The study will look closer at what restitution is and why it should matter to us. The underlying topics are:','2019-10-20 18:59:30');

(130,92,'Part of building a sure foundation in Christ entails that we know our God-given spiritual rights and privileges, which Jesus obtained for us at the cross and by His resurrection from the dead. When He ascended, He did not leave behind a powerless church. He sent the Holy Ghost to indwell and empower those who believe in Him. If we are unaware of this reality, Satan can defeat us in life and make a mockery of our salvation. This study will look at why we must realise and utilise our God-given rights.','2019-10-20 19:00:30');

(131,92,'First and foremost, it is very important that we are fully convinced that the same power and authority which manifest in Jesus is now available to each of us as born again Christians.  Jesus says: “Truly, truly, I say to you, whoever believes in me will also do the works that I do; and greater works than these will he do, because I am going to the Father.” (John 14:12). Authority is the right to command and be in control and as a new creation in Christ; we have been put in a position of power and authority– a position delegated to us by God through Jesus Christ. Along with that authority come certain responsibilities.
The topics are:','2019-10-20 19:01:30');

(132,93,'A very common question, which many Christians ask, is: What is God’s Will for my life? It is important that we understand the foundational truth on this matter especially because we have gotten to a new era of the gospel where motivational speakers have motivated us to doing things spontaneously and forgetting the fact that the path of a child of God are ordered by the Lord.','2019-10-20 19:02:30');

(133,93,'One of the foundational fact is that it is a disaster and tragedy for a Christian to wander aimlessly for long periods like the Israelites in the wilderness, when the Promised Land was only a relatively short distance within reach. Not knowing God’s will can cause us to waste lots of years of our lives unfruitfully. So, how can we know what our purpose is? How can we find out what it is that God wants us to do with our allotted time on Earth? How can we receive precise answers concerning specific areas of my life, and what decisions to make? This study will dive into these questions. Building a firm and sure foundation in Christ will require us to know what He wants us to do with our lives. The topics of focus are:','2019-10-20 19:03:30');

(134,95,'In building a firm and sure spiritual foundation, we need to hear from God for many reasons. He communicates to us primarily through the Bible. However, there are many specific life situations where God need to reveal His specific plans. God is very interested in every detail of our lives, hence He can guide us into major life decisions like who to marry as a life partner, which course to study, where to live, where to work, where to invest etc.','2019-10-20 19:04:30');

(135,95,'This study will outline some key principles involved in hearing God and walking in His will.The underlying topics are:','2019-10-20 19:04:30');

(136,96,'Discipleship is a critical matter in the heart of God. It has always been God's method of raising men for His use. If you have given your life to Christ, as a new convert, God expects that a systematic teaching of His word will follow in order to transform the new believer into the image of Jesus Christ.','2019-10-22 14:27:30');

(137,96,'The primary purpose of God in discipleship is to get every child of God conformed to the image of the Lord Jesus Christ (Rom 8:28-29). Hence, discipleship becomes God's only approved means of reproducing the life of Christ in all who came to be saved. However, discipleship is not just a <strong>teaching</strong> but a "making". It is a life relationship with our Lord Jesus Christ. It is an access into the very life of Jesus. It involves direct encounters and interactions with our Lord Jesus in prayer, in word, in service and in following in His steps. Thus, it is a day to day process and course of life, resulting in becoming like Jesus Christ.','2019-10-22 14:28:30');

(138,96,'Discipleship process is meaningless if there are no disciples. In this study, we will consider;','2019-10-22 14:29:30');

(139,98,'One critical assignment that Jesus did at the prime of His true manifestation as the only begotten son of God was the choosing of His disciples. Jesus did it so early because he wanted them to have a practical knowledge of His ways and firsthand experiences of His acts. However, Jesus performed this with future in view because the first set of disciples were supposed to be the pioneer disciples, setting the pace for many others.','2019-10-22 14:30:30');

(140,98,'In the first study text, we realize that the promise of Jesus to the disciples was not to turn them to fishers of men but to make them. This quickly depicts that discipleship requires a process of making unlike a mere conversion. Hence, there is a wide margin between converts and disciples. While the former is basic, the latter is advance. So, our focus right now is to examine what it takes to transit from the ordinary to the extraordinary in the context of growth both as individuals and agents for other people.','2019-10-22 14:31:30');

(141,98,'Consequent upon the premises established earlier, we shall critically highlight the pros and cons of discipleship with the aim of noting its necessity, requirements and benefits. We shall, first of all, note the pattern Our Lord Jesus set for us before, during and after the selection of His disciples. Structurally, we shall divide this study into three subheadings:','2019-10-22 14:32:30');

(142,99,'Eternal consecration occurs when you dedicate your life entirely to God, by giving Him lifelong sacrifices and setting aside times during each day in a committed lifestyle of prayer and fasting as you display yourself as a living Epistle to all that see you. When you live this type of life, then you walk in the Spirit continually.  This lifestyle gives you the ability to remain in a steadfast position of obedience, sanctification, holiness and humility as you maintain a walk of righteousness. It means you are constantly in prayer and feasting of the Word, because it keeps you with a hunger and thirst for seeking God','2019-10-22 14:33:30');

(142,99,'This happens when there is a sense of perpetual connection and unchanging allegiance to God forever. A sense of a man who has crossed the bridge and burnt it so that there is no chance of returning. This happens when we are genuinely crucified with Christ and to continue to live for Him everyday of our lives, which means, to be dead to the world, sin, self and the deeds of the flesh and to be alive unto righteousness.\n
This study looks at:','2019-10-22 14:34:30');

(143,100,'We oftentimes struggle through life as Christians, though, we have been empowered with the most important endowment, which is the gift of the Holy Spirit at new birth.  The Bible says, “But as many as received him, to them gave e power to become the sons of God, even to them that believe on his name” (John 1:12). But the biggest question is why do we still struggle to live the Christlike life when we have the seal of the Spirit. It is because we tend to enjoy the delicacies of the sinful nature called the flesh though the blood of our Lord Jesus had delivered us. The Scriptures encourage us to, “Stand fast therefore in the liberty by which Christ has made us free, and do not be entangled again with a yoke of bondage” (Gal. 5:1). The only way to stand firm in the dominion over the influence of the flesh, and stay free from every yoke of bondage of sin is by walking in the Spirit. A lot of us are still dancing around sinful habits despite the fact that we have had the Salvation experience for quite a while. Our story has not changed from Paul’s lamentation of the sinful nature.','2019-10-22 14:35:30');

(144,100,'The answer to the dilemma highlighted above is in Walking in the Spirit, and this is what we will be looking at in this study under the following teachings:','2019-10-22 14:36:30');

(145,102,'“Now in the morning as he returned into the city, he hungered. And when he saw a fig tree in the way, he came to it, and found nothing thereon, but leaves only, and said unto it, Let no fruit grow on thee henceforward for ever. And presently the fig tree withered away” (Mathew 21:18 -19).          I believe we are familiar with this story. Something very striking about it is the desire of God. He desires fruit from our lives, and can decide to check us out any time, any day to request for fruit. The fig tree in question did not know Jesus would “randomly check it out”. Jesus was expecting figs or fruits from the fig tree, but found only leaves. There is something interesting and historical about fig leaves. You will recall that fig leaves were used by Adam and Eve to cover their nakedness after the fall in the Garden of Eden (Genesis 3:7). They used the leaves to cover their true state and reality. So, in a way, we can see that the fig leaves tend to act as a covering we use to provide false impression of what we are not. We do a lot of activities year-in year-out, coloured and coated with the name of God, but lacking in the reality of God. We appear religious, but the righteousness of God is not evident in our lives.  What the Lord desires is fruit, and not leaves, not mere activities that are having the form of godliness but denying the power thereof (2 Timothy 3:5). That was why Jesus declared in Matthew 7:20, saying, “Wherefore by their fruits ye shall know them”.','2019-10-22 14:37:30');

(146,102,'It is our fruits that show if truly we are have a sure foundation in Christ or not.  Since we have the seed of God in us by the help of the Holy Spirit, God expects us to bring forth the fruits of the Spirit as outlined in Galatians 5:22 – 23 (NLT), “ But the Holy Spirit produces these kind of fruits in our lives: love, joy, peace, patience, kindness, goodness, faithfulness, gentleness, and self-control. There is no law against these things! Like begets like. We cannot claim we belong to God and be producing fruits of the wicked. The Bible says, “For every tree is known by his own fruit. For of thorns men do not gather figs, nor of a bramble bush gather they grapes” (Luke 6:44). If truly we have accepted Jesus as our Lord and Saviour, then, we have the Spirit of God in us for as many that received Him (that received Jesus), He gave them power to become the sons of God (John 1:12). If truly we have the Spirit of God, then we “MUST” exhibit the fruits of the Spirit. It is not a choice; it is a “MUST”.\n
This week, we shall consider  the following topics:','2019-10-22 14:38:30');

(147,103,'In an earlier study, we have come to an understanding on the personality of the Holy Spirit and with this understanding comes the question “what are the benefits of having, knowing or allowing the Holy Spirit in my life as a child of God?” This study is set to explore the great benefit that God’s children have in the Holy Spirit – The Gifts of the Spirit.','2019-10-22 14:38:30');

(148,103,'The Gifts of the Spirit are unique skills and abilities given by the Holy Spirit to faithful followers of Christ to serve God for the common benefit of His people, the church and sustain us for eternity. They are simply, God empowering faithful Christians to do what He has called us to do. 2 Peter 1:3 says, "His divine power has given us everything we need for life and godliness through our knowledge of Him who called us by His own glory and goodness." The gifts of the Holy Spirit are part of "everything we need" to accomplish His plans for our lives.','2019-10-22 14:39:30');

(149,103,'The Holy Spirit can manifest anyone of the gifts through any believer anytime He wants  to do so. Each of these gifts are supernatural, miraculous manifestations which comes directly from the Holy Spirit Himself and any Christian can get themselves in proper place to receive these gifts, as the apostle Paul himself tells us to stir up the gift of God, 2Tim 1:6. These gifts are a tremendous help and aid not only to a child of God in his/her own personal walk with the Lord, but many of them can also be used to help other people out, as special needs and circumstances arise in their lives – 1 Cor 12:7 says that these gifts are given “as a means of helping the church NLT.”\n
To have a deeper understanding of this benefit we have in the Holy Spirit, we shall consider:
','2019-10-22 14:40:30');

(150,105,'The church was founded on revelation of the personality of Christ (Matthew 16:16), however, the sustainability and continuity of the church depends largely on “the great commission” of our Lord and master Jesus Christ to us believers to “go ye into all the world, and preach the gospel to every creature” and then “….thou shall be my witnesses in Jerusalem, Judea and unto the uttermost part of the earth” (Mark 16:15; Acts 1:8).','2019-10-22 14:41:30');

(151,105,'The rate at which churches spring up everywhere with large crowd in attendance is such that one could have easily concluded that the church (body of Christ) is experiencing tremendous growth, however, it is only church attendance that is increasing numerically (gathering of multitude) while the body of Christ is experiencing a great decline','2019-10-22 14:42:30');

(152,105,'The reason for this great decline is because the great commission has been neglected by individuals; the “tell others about Jesus” mindset of individual believers is no longer there, the lifestyle of personal evangelism is fast disappearing, giving way to other substitutes that are not adding up to the body of Christ in terms of quality of believers.        
In this study, we shall be considering the following teachings:','2019-10-22 14:43:30');

(153,106,'The desire of God for His children is to live each day of their lives in the supernatural, which is something that is above and beyond ordinary natural life. When He made man in His own image in Genesis 1:26-27, He did that with the intention for us to dominate and subdue the earth. It takes the supernatural to have dominion over the earth. Man lost this dimension of glory when sin came, but it was restored when Jesus died and resurrected. Our Lord Jesus Christ went about doing good works, healing the oppressed, raising the dead, opening the blind eyes, and practically living the life of the supernatural while on earth. We cannot do less. Little wonder the Bible says, “Verily, verily, I say unto you, He that believeth on me, the works that I do shall he do also; and greater works than these shall he do; because I go unto my Father” (John 14:12). Our Lord expects us to do greater works than He did when He was here on earth. These supernatural works are not limited to spiritual dimensions; they also include physical works. This is our default mode as born again Christians. The Bible says, “Jesus answered them, Is it not written in your law, I said, Ye are gods? If he called them gods, unto whom the word of God came, and the scripture cannot be broken” (John 10:34 -35). This scripture reveals God’s expectation for our lives – to live a daily walk of miracles in our academics, career, business, family, marriage, health, finance, ministry and every other area of our lives.','2019-10-22 14:44:30');

(154,106,'The bible, from Genesis to Revelation consists of chronicles of the display of God's miraculous acts to demonstrate His absolute sovereignty and showcase His mightiness. They are written to strengthen our resolve and absolute confidence in the supernatural power of God to do wonders. From creation to specific miracles of healing, provision, wondrous move of God to His promise of mighty miracle among us that believe, God is confirming one truth, He is a miracle working God that wants every of His children and all those who believe in Him to experience the wonders He can do on a daily basis.','2019-10-22 14:45:30');

(155,106,'As believers, the supernatural should be our natural! We ought to be doing “exploits” for God. And we can! Therefore, we shall consider the following subtopics in this study:','2019-10-22 14:46:30');

(156,107,'To pant after God means to long with breathless or intense eagerness; deep yearning for God. Intense desires for God's presence as the baby desire the sincere milk. As newborn babes, desire the sincere milk of the word that ye may grow thereby.','2019-10-22 14:47:30');

(157,107,'King David’s thirsting after God was characteristic of the heartfelt desire of all God’s people in proportion to the realization of their need of divine grace. The very life of a hart depends upon the refreshing waters of the brook. Likewise, our lives as Christians depend upon the springs of divine grace and mercy which flow from God to us when we put ourselves in a position to receive the blessings with which He stands ready to supply us so abundantly. The hart panteth after the water brooks because water quenches thirst and sustains life; so, those who have learned to know God “pant” after Him because they know they cannot live without the life-sustaining provisions of His love and grace.','2019-10-22 14:49:30');

(158,107,'To “thirst” after God means much more than merely to desire Him. One might desire something which is not a vital necessity to life. A Christian does indeed desire God; yea, he longs to know Him better, and to depend upon Him fully but the thought of thirsting after God as the hart thirsteth for water brooks, goes beyond desire. It denotes the recognition of necessity. If thirst is not assuaged, death is the result. Thus, for a Christian to thirst after God means that he is willing to set aside all other considerations so that his thirst might be quenched.','2019-10-22 14:50:30');

(159,107,'The mandate of TACEF came up after several days of longing for revival in the African Church by the pioneers though studying in school, their undying love for God and passion for souls brought about the mandate of raising an army with a vision of revival where so many were birthed in today.\n
In the course of this study, we shall examine critically:','2019-10-22 14:50:30');

(160,108,'Our society has defined a leader as a person who gives commands and therefore the one who is to be served by others. While this may be true in some worldly scenarios, the Biblical model for the ideal leader is a person who is here to serve. A Christian leader is to be more concerned about how he can be of useful service to others than how he can be served by others. Christian leadership requires a heart that is willing to make sacrifices for the greater good of the ones being led. We must remind ourselves that leadership is not only for pastors or fellowship executives. We are all called to be leaders to one degree or the other, because we all have the capacity to influence others with God’s Word. This is a powerful way of building a firm foundation in Christ when we have a heart that seeks to serve and be beneficial to others. The underlying topics for this study are:','2019-10-22 14:51:30');

(161,109,'Every person is accountable before GOD, FOR WE SHALL ALL GIVE Account before God, even account of resources handed over to us, there will be no excuses. There is a common saying which is actually an error, “I am the master of my fate; I am the captain of my soul”. This is a mistake because we are all accountable to God, Ezek.18:4; “all souls are Mine”.','2019-10-22 14:52:30');

(162,109,'Accountability is simply being responsible for one’s actions, Rom.14:12, we will all be responsible for all our actions including how we spend our time and finances (time and finance are given to us by God and we have to give account of them Lk.12:48).','2019-10-22 14:53:30');

(163,109,'There have been misunderstanding of financial resources and misappropriation of financial resources, the world is being destroyed because finances are not being used according to the plan and purpose of God. God desires us to manage our finances His way not ours, so, it is important to learn financial management God’s way.','2019-10-22 14:54:30');

(164,109,'God has been around forever before time existed, He inhabits eternity, He created time Isaiah57:15. He is unrestricted by time IIPeter3:8. Though, God is not controlled by time the way humans are, He still put great emphasis on time (He is always punctual, He acts at the right time). God created time as a tool, as a Christian, time management means learning to use time as God wants us to use it, Eph.5:15-16. Time management is a divine mandate for us; God will judge our use of time Eccl.3:17.','2019-10-22 14:55:30');
