(109, 'Week 29: 16 – 22 March 2020','Accountability to God: Time Management and Finances','Romans 14:9-13','Romans 14:9-13\n
9  For to this end Christ both died, and rose, and revived, that he might be Lord both of the dead and living. 10  But why dost thou judge thy brother? or why dost thou set at nought thy brother? for we shall all stand before the judgment seat of Christ. 11  For it is written, As I live, saith the Lord, every knee shall bow to me, and every tongue shall confess to God. 12  So then every one of us shall give account of himself to God. 13  Let us not therefore judge one another any more: but judge this rather, that no man put a stumbling block or an occasion to fall in his brother's way.',1, 2020, '2020-3-16', '2019-10-18 16:48:00');

