INSERT INTO `lessons` (`lesson-id`, `point-id`, `row`, `date`) VALUES
(1, 1, 'The primary reason Paul left Timothy at Ephesus was because of certain teachers in the church who had begun to mix the truth of Christ with “other” doctrines (1 Tim. 1:3). Paul knew that accurately teaching the truth was foundational in creating strong disciples, while falsehoods would only bring a church to spiritual ruin. Today, many churches still have the same problem the Ephesians had, as the Word of God is being mixed with other doctrines that are not of God.', '2018-02-17 17:57:38'),
(2, 1, 'Just as Timothy was called (among other things) to defend the truth, we today are under a similar obligation to rise for the truth of the Word of God. False doctrines not only pervert the believers, but also bring division in the Body of Christ, as Paul strongly cautioned us (1 Cor. 1:10). Such division, in turn, weakens the overall witness of the Church to an unbelieving and skeptical world, and many who are curious do not even know which “church” to join. Let us, therefore, strive to be of reasonable service to God, in accordance with what He Himself has revealed in His Word.', '2018-02-17 17:57:38'),
(3, 2, 'Paul referred to Timothy as his own son in the faith. Their relationship translated into salvation coming to many peoples in different parts of the world. In the Acts of the Apostles and in the Epistles, we have a record of how these two champions of Christ worked side by side, along with other ministers of the Gospel, to propel the Great Commission to the ends of the Roman Empire. Paul could trust Timothy with a simple task like bringing him his cloak and books (2 Tim. 4:13), or with far more critical responsibilities as abiding at Ephesus to help protect the believers from deception. They had that kind of a relationship. Paul could trust Timothy with a very personal task and a general assignment. It is sad today that there is a scarcity of reputable and dependable sons, who can be trusted to where and when it matters most. Men and women of great grace apply their intelligent reasoning and full senses with total faithfulness to discharge kingdom tasks with excellence and even far beyond what is expected of them. We can always be sure not to find gaps with these kinds of people because they fully commit their mind to the firm principle that God deserves only the best—irrespective of their challenges, excuses, or limitations.', '2018-02-17 17:57:38'),
(4, 3, 'The first key lesson from this study is how tampering with God’s truth brings problems for both the church and the ones doing the false teaching. The false teachers bring upon themselves “swift destruction” (2 Pet. 2:1). For the church, misleading doctrines bring division and confusion, and usually leads to the hearers becoming false teachers themselves; “seducers” will grow worse and worse, “deceiving and being deceived” (2 Tim. 3:13).', '2018-02-17 18:03:31'),
(5, 3, 'The Lord Jesus has clearly stated that not everyone who calls Him Lord will enter into His kingdom, but only those who do the will of the Father (Matt. 7:21). Part of His will is that we “teach no other doctrine,” as Paul instructed Timothy at Ephesus to ensure this. False teaching, therefore, can ultimately keep people from entering God’s eternal kingdom (Rev. 22:19). These should be sobering realities that should keep us diligent in ensuring that not only are we receiving correct teaching from God’s Word, but that we ourselves never veer off the straight and narrow path of Truth when teaching others.  Therefore, beware of the so-called “new revelation” or “another Gospel.”', '2018-02-17 18:03:31'),
(6, 4, 'We must always remember that we are on a journey through this world, and our final destination is the Promised Land of God’s eternal kingdom. Many of the Israelites that God saved out of Egypt got distracted along the way and lost the inheritance (Jude 1:5). Just as it was in Paul and Timothy’s time, we also are living in an age of deception with a multitude of false beliefs being mixed within the church. We must be careful to keep our eyes on the prize (the Lord Jesus and heaven). Fables, endless genealogies, and speculations are really a strategy of the enemy to bring distraction and throw us off important things. The Lord’s sheep hear His voice only, and will not adhere to the voice of false doctrines (John 10:4–5). Let us stay focused on God’s plain Word, while fulfilling our individual calling and ministry, and not get carried away with any wave of the numerous falsehoods that have permeated into the modern church (Eph. 4:14).', '2018-02-17 18:03:31'),
(7, 5, 'We have seen that false teachers are actually under the influence of Satan himself, having been taken captive by his snare. We, therefore, cannot handle the matter carnally (by human wisdom), but must rely on spiritual tools, as listed in “the whole armour of God.”', '2018-02-17 18:03:31'),
(8, 5, 'A false teacher refuses to agree with the plain revelation of God’s Word. He desires to be a teacher of his own version of truth and draw disciples unto himself. Pride is a common trait among such people, so the matter is to be handled delicately, “in meekness instructing those that oppose themselves . . .” (2 Tim. 2:25). Perhaps, God will give them the grace to repent and acknowledge the truth.', '2018-02-17 18:03:31'),
(9, 5, 'Within our own sphere of influence, we must show the false teacher that his own agenda cannot take preeminence over God’s agenda. We must also point out that God Himself has said that adding and subtracting from His Word have eternal consequences. If a false teacher has no fear of God’s wrath and judgement, then at this point, we must back off and leave the matter to God—we have done our part. It is by the fear of the Lord that men depart from evil (Prov. 16:6).', '2018-02-17 18:03:31'),
(10, 6, 'The biggest function of God’s Law in this age is to reveal to sinners the perfect nature of God’s holiness. It is like looking into a mirror that shows us our face is dirty, which we may not have noticed. This realisation shows an individual why the Lord Jesus is not just a matter of choice or preference, but also an absolute necessity for justification, redemption, and salvation. Since the Lord Jesus Christ came in the flesh almost 2,000 years ago, He has become the Way, the Truth, and the Life—and no human can successfully come to God anymore except by Him (John 14:6).', '2018-02-17 18:09:12'),
(11, 7, 'Our second key lesson from this teaching is the absolute need for sound doctrine in the church. “Sound” or healthy teaching is not only spiritual nourishment as natural food is to the body, but also spiritual medicine to cure any ailments that have been brought about by previously ingesting falsehoods and lies. Paul understood this truth and, therefore, emphasised it throughout the pastoral epistles to Timothy and Titus (e.g., 2 Tim. 4:3, Titus 1:9, 2:1). Doctrinal truths found in God’s Word, from the Creation to the Second Coming of Christ, and the things in-between, cannot be tampered with but must be taught faithfully in the churches from one generation to the next.', '2018-02-17 18:09:12'),
(12, 8, 'What we have learnt from Paul’s example is that no matter how off-track a person is (even an oppressor of God’s church), the superabundant grace and mercy of the Most High is more than enough to bring deliverance. We must never give up on anyone as far as issues of salvation is concerned. The worst sinner is not out of God’s reach—there is always hope. The power of God is able to change the human heart and mind from delusion and depravity to faith and obedience. God has always been a God of mercy and grace, and we saw this first displayed in the Garden of Eden. After Adam and Eve fell into transgression, they tried to “cover their nakedness” literally by sewing fig leaves for themselves. But God in His mercy killed an animal (probably a lamb) to give them proper covering physically and also spiritually, as He later revealed (Lev. 17:11) that the blood makes atonement for the soul. This was a foreshadowing of the coming Lamb of God (the Lord Jesus), who would take away the sin of the world (John 1:29). His grace and mercy continues to this day to bring lost souls to a saving knowledge of the Lord Jesus Christ, the Redeemer and Deliverer of mankind.', '2018-02-17 18:16:16'),
(13, 9, 'After the conversion of Saul, the first major activity the Bible records about him is that <b>“straightway he preached Christ in the synagogues</b>, that he is the Son of God” (Acts 9:20). The “chief” of sinners almost instantaneously became the chief of servants of the One whose grace had brought salvation. Though Paul regarded himself as the least of all apostles, he surely laboured more than they did (1 Cor. 15:9–10). Even Peter had to acknowledge the abundance of revelation and wisdom given unto Paul (2 Pet. 3:15–16). He was forgiven for much, and this great forgiveness translated into great love and service for the Lord and Saviour. This is the normal response of a heart that has been transformed by the grace of God. The sheer gratitude (for God’s willingness to forgive and recover a person who was on a path to eternal destruction) is enough to drive us into depths of love, adoration, appreciation, and heartfelt service.', '2018-02-17 18:16:16'),
(14, 9, 'How do you value your salvation and to what degree does this encounter push you to go farther like Paul? Always know that the originality of your encounter with God is seen in what you do for your Saviour.', '2018-02-17 18:16:16'),
(15, 10, 'We have seen how God used Agabus to inform His people about future events so they could prepare themselves and move accordingly. Paul encouraged Timothy to war a good warfare by recalling the prophecies over his personal life and ministry. Prophecy is one of the spiritual gifts (1 Cor. 12), and it is still for the modern church today. God is still the same (Mal. 3:6, Heb. 13:8). He still speaks specific words through His servants.', '2018-02-17 18:23:08'),
(16, 10, 'The record in Acts 27 of Paul’s journey by sea to Rome is an incredible manifestation of the gift of prophecy in the daily life of believers. From verse 20 down, the Bible shows how the soldiers and shipmasters had lost all hope and believed they would perish at sea. But God revealed something to Paul and he prophesied the same to the passengers. The prophecy was that not a single person would die, though the ship would be destroyed. This gave Paul himself courage and comfort, which rubbed off on the others, as they also regained their lost appetite and good cheer from the prophetic word (Acts 27:33–38). The prophecy was fulfilled to perfection, as not a single person died but the ship was destroyed (Acts 27:44). What if there was no revealed prophetic word? Would they on the ship have had any hope or courage at all after the gloomy situation arose? What if some took drastic action out of despair and desperation, which would have been a wrong move that only compounded the problem?', '2018-02-17 18:23:08'),
(17, 10, 'Prophetic knowledge is extremely useful and of great benefit when God does reveal them through his servants. Satan our enemy is very crafty and always attempts to lay traps and snares on our paths. But prophecy helps us to avoid pitfalls by maintaining the correct attitude towards situations and making accurate decisions.', '2018-02-17 18:23:08'),
(18, 11, 'Spiritual shipwreck occurs when a person abandons either faith or good conscience. When a spiritually sound Christian turns back into his vomit through partial or total backsliding into sin, worldliness, and fleshly living, we can say it is a shipwreck of faith. When a beloved brother now finds it very easy to lie, cheat, fornicate, and commit other sins with no caution or any form of restraint, we see a life that is under the risk of a painful shipwreck.', '2018-02-17 18:23:08'),
(19, 11, 'In our call unto reasonable service, holding faith and a good conscience are essential to preventing shipwreck of our faith. A good conscience is a call unto honesty, purity, humility, patience, and other godly character. Moral integrity must be our standard at all times.', '2018-02-17 18:23:08'),
(20, 12, 'Our first major lesson from this study is how prayer should be a priority in the Christian’s walk with God. As simple as it may seem, prayer is actually a supernatural engagement. Prayer is not an “on and off” act, but a lifestyle. We can only speak freely with God if we get to know Him and build friendship with Him. This is why Moses could stand in the gap and pray for days because it was not about time spent but relationship that was being nurtured (Exod. 32:9–14). The Bible says that God spoke to Moses “face to face” as a man speaks with his friend (Exod. 33:11). No wonder Moses commanded so much authority and became one of God’s greatest servants. This kind of relationship is foundational for our prayers to be heard and answered. You cannot succeed in life without a prayer life that comes through a relationship with God and not just vigil, prayer meeting etc. ', '2018-02-17 18:29:56'),
(21, 13, 'God in the New Testament encourages us to always pray. Men ought always to pray and not be tired (Luke 18:1). We are to pray without ceasing (1 Thess. 5:17). But then God tells us to not only pray always, but also pray with all prayer and supplication in the Spirit (Eph. 6:18). So even though Paul specifically mentioned only four kinds of prayer in verse 1 of our study text, the higher reality is that the ways and dimensions which we can pray to God are not restricted. The point is that we can talk to God in any dimension we wish because He is actually a person with a personality, not a robot. That is why Paul said he could pray with the spirit and pray with the understanding also (1 Cor. 14:14-15); he could even sing his prayers to God if he liked. Even when we are weak and do not know exactly how to express ourselves to God, His own Spirit makes intercession for us with “groaning” which cannot be uttered (Rom. 8:26). It is good to understand the four dimensions of “supplications, prayers, intercessions, and thanksgiving,” but we should also know that our God is a genuine person and there are manifold ways in which we can commune with Him, either for ourselves or on behalf of others.', '2018-02-17 18:29:56'),
(22, 14, 'According to verses 1–8 of our study text, there is a strong connection between intercessory prayer and salvation. We know that it is God’s goodness that leads to repentance (Rom. 2:4), but He can be moved to exercise His goodness and mercy on a person based on the deep compassionate prayers of another person. We saw an example of this above when He was about to destroy Israel but changed His mind after the deep intercession of Moses (His friend). We are called by God a “royal priesthood” (1 Pet. 2:9) made up of kings and priests (Rev. 1:6). One of the functions of a priest is to intercede and stand in the gap between God and man. In Ezekiel 22:30-31, God was looking for someone to intercede on behalf of the people of the land, but found no one. The people ultimately received the righteous judgement of God upon them and were destroyed. If people had stood in the gap as Moses did, they would have been spared. We are called to stand in the gap for our nation and particularly for our church as a fellowship that is called unto revival. We must have compassion on the lost and utilize our privileged access to God for the sake of others.', '2018-02-17 18:29:56'),
(23, 15, 'God is a God of order. In divine order, each sex has its unique place and role in creation. A man is to be a man and a woman is to be a woman, and particularly within marriage, the two complement each other. In marriage, the unique roles of husband and wife can be summarised as headship and submission. Headship is the divine calling of a husband to take primary responsibility for Christlike servant leadership, protection, and provision in the home while submission is the divine calling of a wife to honour, affirm her husband\'s leadership, and help carry it through according to her gifts.\r\n\r\n', '2018-02-17 18:39:30'),
(24, 15, 'Man is not the woman\'s master, but rather her provider and leader. The truth is there can be no true union or Biblical marriage without the man and the woman functioning biblically in each of their distinctive roles. If the man abandons his role of providing for his family and being the spiritual leader, then the family falls into serious trouble. The same applies to the woman who tries to step into the role of the man. In either case, the family as God created and structured is severely weakened or destroyed. ', '2018-02-17 18:39:30'),
(25, 16, 'Christians have been called unto a life of moderation in the use of jewellery and even external adornment or dressing. No biblical law states strict absence, but we are told clearly to live moderately. God also deals with us at different levels and some may have it as a personal, individual consecration as Lord instructed them. Individual consecration in adornment, eating, giving, and sacrificial living must not become the standard for all, since they were specific to the recipient.', '2018-02-17 18:39:30'),
(26, 17, 'We have seen from God’s Word that spiritual growth takes time, effort, and discipline. One must go through a process to attain the qualities needed to serve as workers, executives, and leaders of the church in general, in fellowship specifically, or as a hands-on servant. All followers of the Lord Jesus Christ must strive for these qualities.', '2018-02-17 18:57:06'),
(27, 17, 'Note that many churches today have misunderstood the roles of a deacon, and some have ignorantly exalted the office, to receive honour from men. The true meaning of the word and the office is a menial servant; even as the chosen seven were appointed to “serve tables” (Acts 6:1–6). The word “serve” here is the word diakoneo, which is the same word Paul uses in his instruction to Timothy, which means attendant, waiter, or menial servant.', '2018-02-17 18:57:06'),
(28, 17, 'It is a disaster today in the church when we create different roles and titles for purposes that are outside the desire to edify the church but to raise money.', '2018-02-17 18:57:06'),
(29, 17, 'But just as Stephen and Philip were unusually close to God in faith and power, God rewards all who take the humble route. Paul said they purchase to themselves a “good degree” and great boldness in the faith which is in the Lord Jesus Christ Jesus.', '2018-02-17 18:57:06'),
(30, 18, 'Since this mystery of Christ has been revealed, we have a God-given responsibility to uphold the truth of the Gospel as pillars of the truth. This means that the truth about who God is cannot be found anywhere else on earth. Many speculations and belief systems abound, but only the body of the Lord Jesus Christ holds the truth of the mystery. The Lord Jesus said that no man knows who the Son is except the Father, and no man knows the Father except the Son and whosoever the Son chooses to reveal Him to (Luke 10:22). The reality of God has been revealed and we must promote and communicate that same reality to others.', '2018-02-17 19:41:16'),
(31, 19, 'We are the ones to represent God to the rest of the world. We cannot do this effectively without a sense of order as His church. This proper conduct first begins with the inward man, then shows forth externally in our behaviour, both when we are alone and when we gather. In times of meeting and gathering, we should always remember who and where we are and, therefore, recognise the need for mutual respect. Order, effective planning, preparation, decorum, governance, and mutual respect must be used to honour God and His house. This orderly conduct also speaks to leaders who fail to attend meetings and programmes or come late without having any sense of regard to either prenotify their leaders and colleagues or willingly offer an apology before anyone asks them. Individuals who act this way do not understand how to behave on this ground of truth and thus do not deserve to lead God’s people.', '2018-02-17 19:41:16'),
(32, 20, 'We have seen a prophecy of an end-time departure from the faith. There is good reason to believe that we have been in these prophesied end-times for many years now. And the deception will only increase as we move towards the time of the Antichrist and eventual return of the Lord Jesus. There is an attack on the truth in this day and age. You need to check the poisons being served on the so-called Christian televisions and social media. We must be on guard not to fall prey to the “alternatives” to the truth, which Satan and his demons are spreading in the earth today. It is a spiritual battle that must be fought with spiritual weapons to guarantee our victory: truth, righteousness, preaching the Gospel, faith, salvation, the Word of God, and prayer (Eph. 6).', '2018-02-17 19:46:58'),
(33, 20, 'Not only must we protect ourselves, but we must warn others also about the threat. This is because the seducing spirits are very subtle and not always explicit. Their words are made to sound intellectual, rational, and full of wisdom and positivity. They can quote many scriptures with exciting parallelism, but lack the truth. Paul emphasised that they use good words and fair speeches to deceive the hearts of the simple (Rom. 16:18).', '2018-02-17 19:46:58'),
(34, 21, 'The word translated as ‘exercise’ is the Greek gymnazo, which means to “practise naked for the games.” This word is used in reference to how the ancient Greek athletes would strip off their outer clothing so as not to be hindered from their purpose of winning the event. Paul intentionally used this word to show Timothy that he must strip off everything that would hinder him from attaining godliness. He was to practise/train naked—i.e. refuse and strip off any unnecessary distractions, weights and besetting sins. Just like the athlete, the Christian must avoid distraction to attain his goal. Many things in this world will cause unnecessary complications for us if we are not focused. That is why we should “lay aside every weight, and the sin which doth so easily beset us, and let us run with patience the race that is set before us” (Heb. 12:1). ', '2018-02-17 20:22:39'),
(35, 22, 'In addition to the spiritual benefit of exercising ourselves unto godliness, Paul in verse 8 of our study text stated that bodily exercise profits little. It means that it is good for us to be physically fit. How disappointing is an anointed life that cannot go far due to a lazy weak body? The need to maintain regular routine of training our muscles, body and keeping fit is critical as revival army. How many of us can stand for one hour without sitting down or how many can run ten minutes without follow-up strain? ', '2018-02-17 20:22:39'),
(36, 22, 'The “little profit” here is useful to us. We can gain so many things from physical workout such as not being overweight and having long-term wellness. It has been proven that regular exercise can reduce the risk of major illnesses, such as heart disease, stroke, type 2 diabetes, and cancer by up to 50% and lower risk of early death by up to 30%.', '2018-02-17 20:22:39'),
(37, 22, 'In addition, a contemporary research has shown that physical activity can also boost self-esteem, mood, sleep quality, and energy, as well as reduce the risk of stress, depression, dementia, and Alzheimer’s disease.', '2018-02-17 20:22:39'),
(38, 22, 'As a reasonable child of God, commit yourself to a weekly bodily activity of at least 150 minutes of physical activity over a week through a variety of activities like walking, running, cycling, or taking part in sports and formal gym programme.', '2018-02-17 20:22:39'),
(39, 23, 'We have seen that a successful ministry is dependent on first having a successful walk with the Lord Jesus Christ. He is our power source that gives us energy to accomplish whatever tasks are necessary in Christian service. Anybody who is “serving” God without having a vibrant relationship with Him is either insincere and doing it for other motives. You cannot be a true child of God without a solid foundation of being in a strong relationship with Him, which is based on love, trust, and friendship. Moses would not have been able to lead Israel if he did not have personal communion with God. It would have been impossible for Paul to manage several churches throughout the world of that time, exposed to all risks and demonic forces without a perpetual connection to the Risen Saviour. The truth is that we function in the currency of His presence as a minister, and when we lack this, we do not have a ministry. For without Him we can do nothing (John 15:5). Our personal walk with the Lord Jesus Christ must be our first priority, and then our ministry flows out of the fountain of that ongoing relationship with the Lord.', '2018-02-17 20:40:46'),
(40, 24, '“Neglect not the gift which is in thee” (1 Tim. 4:14) is a necessary admonition for many Christians today. The Holy Spirit has deposited at least one special gift in every believer, but our gift will lay dormant inside us if we do not stir it up, just as Paul reminded Timothy (2 Tim. 1:6). We must develop that special ability and interest, and put it to the maximum use for the expansion of the kingdom of God.', '2018-02-17 20:40:46'),
(41, 24, 'In addition to this, our lives must be an example for others to see and follow. Six specific dimensions were mentioned by Paul (speech, conduct, love, spirit, faith, purity) and we will do well to not only radiate these things in the presence of other believers, but continue to grow in them as well.', '2018-02-17 20:40:46'),
(42, 25, 'Let us cite an example for this present-day generation. Brother Timothy is someone who wanted everyone to like him. He relies on public endorsement as a leader to feel good and fails in being firm, steady, and frank to drive right behaviour. Bro Timothy will see a bad Facebook post from the choir leader but he will not talk because he does not want to offend the sister. He would see how a leader reacts to his wife in his presence but will keep quiet. He will openly see how someone is abusing fellowship purse but he will be mute. He will see how executives come late to fellowship yet he will be dumb when his voice is most needed. He does not want to ruffle feathers. He will see an error planted as a seed and naively watch it grow into a spiritual cancer in the fellowship to the destruction of many.', '2018-02-17 20:40:46'),
(43, 25, 'True leadership requires that we must get past ourselves and not allow our personal sensitivity to becloud the demand of God upon our lives. Who we are is different from our desires as a leader; we must seek to cover the gap with high sense of urgency.', '2018-02-17 20:40:46'),
(44, 26, 'God has had a problem with sin from the beginning of times in the Garden of Eden. His holy nature will not allow lawlessness to continue perpetually without being dealt with. His own children are not exempted. We are actually more accountable, as Apostle Peter stressed that judgement must begin in the house of God (1 Pet. 4:17). In Colossians 3:5-6, we are warned to “mortify” sin from our lives in this present earth, because it attracts the wrath of God. But even more frightening is the knowledge that “the unrighteous shall not inherit the kingdom of God” (1 Cor. 6:9).', '2018-02-19 12:15:36'),
(45, 26, 'These things should motivate us not only to live clean lives ourselves, but also be caring enough to intervene when we see other Christians go astray. Of course, as we have seen, we must take precautionary measures before we correct another person. It is a delicate matter but necessary. An end-time prophecy in Daniel 12:3 says that those who turn many to righteousness will shine like the stars forever! If we love our brothers and sisters, we will not leave them to continue in error.', '2018-02-19 12:15:36'),
(46, 26, 'In Leviticus 19:17, God gave a strong commandment through Moses for his people: the commandment was to “rebuke thy neighbour” and not permit sin upon him. This verse is directly related and connected to the next verse: “thou shalt love thy neighbour as thyself.” There is a direct link between loving our neighbour and correcting him from sin. This must be our spirit and disposition to correcting errors in our brethren with no form of hypocrisy.', '2018-02-19 12:15:36'),
(48, 27, 'The most fundamental point in this study is that the person who works deserves his wages. This includes secular jobs and businesses, but it also includes full-time Christian ministry. It is interesting that Paul did not just refer to the Old Testament, he also aligned with our Lord Jesus Himself from Luke 10:7 where he said “the labourer is worthy of his hire” (word for word in the Greek). The Lord was giving instruction to the seventy disciples that were sent out to preach the Gospel. He even told them not to bother about taking their purse (representing money), bag, or shoes (Luke 10:4), since they would be taken care of wherever they went. ', '2018-02-19 12:21:41'),
(49, 27, 'This should be a great encouragement to all genuinely called servants of God that the Lord who has called is also sufficiently able to meet and exceed their needs. It is a distraction for a full-time minister to leave his calling of a dedicated prayer, Word study, visitation, and evangelism to be begging for salary payment.', '2018-02-19 12:21:41'),
(50, 27, 'Those who have put their trust in the Lord Jesus can also be rest assured that not only will they be rewarded now in this present time, but a “crown of righteousness” is also laid up for them in the coming eternal kingdom of God.', '2018-02-19 12:21:41'),
(51, 28, 'The church is the visible extension of the Lord Jesus Christ on earth. We are His body and His representatives. If He is holy, then we also are to be holy (1 Pet. 1:15–16). Thus, we are all to be consistent in who we select to represent Him on earth. We must be fully persuaded that we have chosen people who will not tarnish the name of the Lord.', '2018-02-19 12:28:31'),
(52, 28, 'We must raise leaders who are fully aware of the responsibilities that they carry and how their little moment of wrong living can bring timeless damage to the body of Christ. A sense of implications and consequences is necessary caution to be self-aware as leaders. We have seen how Nathan told David that his sinful acts had given the enemies of the Lord a reason to blaspheme the God of Israel (2 Sam. 12:9, 14). The implication of this is that when the “head” commits a sin, it becomes a basis for it to spread like a viral infection into all the parts of the body—herein lies the leadership caution.', '2018-02-19 12:28:31'),
(53, 28, 'We must also be careful in our choice process and be sure again and again that we are fully led of the Lord. We must pray very well, do proper background checks, and investigate to know the candidates’ convictions, inner crisis, and potential weaknesses before we endorse them for spiritual leadership roles.', '2018-02-19 12:28:31'),
(54, 28, 'In leadership, men and women should possess impeccable integrity and proven reputation within or outside of the fellowship and church. How can we select a leader who is known at his workplace as a snobbish, irresponsible, intemperate, and lazy person, who is also indebted to virtually everyone in his office? How can the church of Christ be led by a sister who is known in her neighbourhood more for her bitterness and uncooperative behaviours? Consistency in godliness is a priceless asset in a leader, as an up-and-down personality is sure to fall into sin sooner or later.', '2018-02-19 12:28:31'),
(55, 29, 'We have seen from our text that God demands we submit to our secular and Christian employers. The principle of submission has its origin from God Himself, and trickles down to His creatures. Beginning with God is a hierarchical order and designated authority from class to class, which is to be respected and obeyed.', '2018-02-19 15:59:27'),
(56, 29, 'In the human realm, God appointed some to be above others in rank or authority. This applies in various dimensions—from secular government, school administration, healthcare institutions, and even families. Our mandate is to submit to the demand of excellent performance, rules of work that do not contradict our faith, and consistent performance that will not bring us into a compromised situation at any time. As we do this, not only is the name and Gospel of the Lord Jesus Christ Jesus glorified, but our bosses may even become positively affected by our disposition and become interested in knowing more about our beliefs. In fact, we may even get a raise and promotion like Joseph eventually did after being mistreated by his master’s wife and still maintained a good attitude while being punished in prison for what he did not do (Gen. 39:19–21, 41:39-40). If we are hated because we do not lie, cheat, or defraud customers, we should remain in the will of God and serve the Lord Jesus Christ faithfully.', '2018-02-19 15:59:27'),
(57, 29, 'One of the areas of submission that is often an issue is when we fail to submit to the regulations of our workplace. For example, if we are paid to work from 8 a.m. to 5 p.m., it is not Christlike to use our paid time to run our private projects. This is particularly common in the public sector where some individuals decide which day to go to work and not. Beloved, this contradicts the laws of faithfulness; you either resign if you feel you have other projects than to be cheating another person.', '2018-02-19 15:59:27'),
(58, 30, 'God Himself being a Master expects much from His children, who are privileged to be masters and employers as well. He expects justice and fairness to be the order of the day. It would be greatly dishonouring to the Lord if a Christian employer or business owner treat his workers like insignificant slaves or delay payment of their wages for months for no reasons.', '2018-02-19 15:59:27'),
(59, 30, 'Christian enterprises must also maintain good governance practice at all times and never be in a place where we ridicule the name of the Lord for operational malpractices, especially when it comes to government regulations, taxes, and dealings with other entities. We must be conscious that there is a Lord of lords in heaven whose name we represent, and we must not use what He has entrusted to us for His glory to see any form of corruption.', '2018-02-19 15:59:27'),
(60, 30, 'One of the men who comes to mind here is Henry Heinz, a 19th century Christian businessman who founded the Heinz Company in 1869. Heinz based his business on Christian principles and proclaimed that his success was a direct result of his faith in God. Heinz was committed to bringing out the best in people and his company was credited for its fair treatment of workers and for pioneering safe and clean food preparation. Today, the Heinz Company is worth around $12 billion. Its most famous product is tomato ketchup, with 650 million bottles of Ketchup being sold every year.', '2018-02-19 15:59:27'),
(61, 30, 'We find many other examples of such Christian business proprietors who followed the Bible in their method of worker relations and business operation. In fact, many of them started out as employees themselves who remained faithful until God gave them ideas that opened the way to success. Oftentimes, God opened doors for employees to become employers, as they go the extra mile when they are given assignment in another Christian business project. Are you a faithful representative of the Lord Jesus in your place of work?', '2018-02-19 15:59:27'),
(63, 31, 'The false teachers supposed that gain is godliness, that godliness and Christian faith are a means to get money and material wealth. Since money was their true god, they did not see any problem with using “godliness” as a method or strategy at arriving at their goal. To them, the end (money) is a good reason or justification for the means (“godliness”).', '2018-02-19 16:06:23'),
(64, 31, 'But the truth is that the end does not justify the means in this case. It is true that money belongs to God (Hag. 2:8), and that it is He who gives us power to get wealth (Deut. 8:18). We are called to enjoy the blessings of God on the face of the earth, but the purpose of the Lord Jesus’ death and resurrection was not primarily to bring us earthly riches, but to make us become like God in holiness and righteousness, which must be our priority.', '2018-02-19 16:06:23'),
(65, 31, 'The importance of eternity to us means that whether prosperity comes or not, our loyalty to the Lord does not change. Of course, we receive every blessing from the Lord while we are here on earth and accept them with hearts of thanksgiving, to be used for the purpose of expanding God’s love and turning the hearts of men unto God and not for our selfish ostentatious living. Wealth must be the last in our cadre of priority with God. Remember that God allowed the devil to take away all of Job’s material prosperity to prove him; but we know that today’s Christians are likely to curse God to his face (Job 1:11) if that ever happens. But those who sincerely love God will serve Him no matter what because wealth is never the primary focus but a by-product.', '2018-02-19 16:06:23'),
(66, 32, 'The exhortation is: “From such withdraw thyself.” Many churches today, whose ministers over-emphasise the topic of prosperity without holiness, but deemphasise the importance of godliness, repentance, and holiness. Be aware of what you feed your spirit and do not be deceived by the effizi that surround these ministries. Be careful not to fall into the snare of the devil. Be alert and protect yourselves from those who influence you with doctrines that disagree with God’s truth, no matter their popularity, scriptural gifts, and testimonies.', '2018-02-19 16:06:23'),
(67, 32, 'Peter could have been tempted to use godliness as a means of gain, by accepting money from Simon with false promise of power (Acts 8:18–21). Many ministers today delude people into believing that if they pay them a certain amount; they will receive one blessing or the other, such as long life, fruit of the womb, foreign visa, successful business, and other personal benefits. They use their status of “man of God” to get gain and see nothing wrong with it. May we abide in the truth and protect ourselves from erroneous doctrines and the teachers that promote them.', '2018-02-19 16:06:23'),
(68, 33, 'The natural, carnal worldview puts money as the first priority, and the present life as its focus. The way we celebrate people in our church and society today is setting new basis for what people should aspire for. We do not celebrate the old headmaster who served faithfully for 35 years without stealing. Rather, we celebrate, award, and confer chieftaincy titles on people who just stole money from the government. The church must never be a part of an inverted pyramid. The society’s wrong basis for valuation is bringing so much dissatisfaction, competition, and even wars between individuals, small groups, and entire nations. Many deaths have occurred because of the dog-eat-dog mentality, yet man is still dissatisfied.', '2018-02-19 16:13:06'),
(69, 33, 'We are not meant to be like that. Those of us whose priority is to please God are not controlled or driven by money. We enjoy and use what He gives us for the kingdom and His glory. We are content whether we are rich financially or whether we are not. Our perspective, our focus is the coming world that God has promised to those that love Him. We know that without the Lord Jesus’ suffering and death we would not be partakers of His glory; so greed and covetousness have been replaced with hearts of thanksgiving for God’s mercy on our souls. This sense of priority is how we will remain content in this world and continue to offer reasonable service unto God under any circumstances, until the day we hear Him say, “Well done, thou good and faithful servant” (Matt. 25:21, 23).', '2018-02-19 16:13:06'),
(70, 34, '“Having food and raiment, let us be therewith content” (1 Tim. 6:8) is one of the most profound statements in the human history. It goes directly against everything this world teaches us to do and be. It goes against our pride, our natural lusts, and our thirst to achieve material greatness. It is incredible because we know that God is a God of abundance, yet He simplifies our requirements into the most basic.', '2018-02-19 16:13:06'),
(71, 34, 'God owns the heaven, even the heavens, but He has given the earth to the children of men (Psalm 115:16). Yet He tells His own children to be satisfied with just the basics. God knows our wants and needs. He is the only wise God our Father who loves us and knows what is best for us, even when we think we are smarter. He has already declared the end from the beginning and sees many pitfalls ahead that we do not see. He has our best interest at heart, hence His call for a simplified life.', '2018-02-19 16:13:06'),
(72, 35, 'Chain reactions occur when one chemical reaction results in another. In a similar fashion, when a domino falls, it knocks the next one down, which knocks the next, and so on. The dimensions of the risk of loving money play out in the same way. The desire for riches results in personal delusion, which ends with the individual’s destruction. In 2 Kings 5:20–27, Elisha’s servant, Gehazi was a covetous man. Naaman (the Syrian king’s captain) had just been healed of leprosy and offered Elisha money as a sign of gratitude, which Elisha refused. But the love of money in Gehazi would not let Naaman go free. He ran and caught up with him, told a lie, and received money and clothes. But he must have forgotten that his master Elisha was an actual prophet of God. Elisha had knowledge of what had happened and the curse of Naaman’s leprosy fell not only on Gehazi, but also on his descendants after him. His strong desire for wealth tricked him into believing that he could get away with unrighteousness, and this delusion ultimately brought his destruction. One thing led to another and Gehazi who would have continued to be a healthy young man, ended up being a leper, with the curse following his children after him. For us today, the desire to be rich does not only bring temporal consequences, but if left uncorrected will lead to the loss of one’s place in God’s eternal kingdom.', '2018-02-19 16:25:03'),
(73, 36, 'We concluded that money itself is not the root, but the love of money (as Gehazi exemplified), which becomes the root of all sorts of evil thoughts, words, and deeds. The rich man in Luke 16:19-31 was wealthy, clothed in purple and fine linen, and fared sumptuously [Greek lampr?s = luxuriously] every day. But his greediness would not even let him take care of the poor Lazarus who was sick and lay at his gate continually. He could have easily taken him to the physicians and started some kind of trade for him. But he left him outside his gate to feed on crumbs and leftovers. It costs the rich man nothing to meet the needs of Lazarus who sits by his gate. Clearly, the rich man’s money was not the root of this evil; it was his greed, selfishness, and love of wealth that was the problem. He just would not want to see a little from himself flow to others. This is the spirit of our part of the world where we would rather be the only rich man among many poor colleagues, rather than a better perspective of being a rich man among other rich look-alikes.', '2018-02-19 16:25:03'),
(74, 36, 'People may have money, and yet not love it; but, if they love it inordinately, it will push them to all evil. The line between the pursuit of money for godly ends and the love of money can be thin, so let us take care not to be deceived by the false promises of wealth. At the same time, let us never look down on those believers we know who have been blessed by the Lord with material wealth. Such an attitude is likewise evil.', '2018-02-19 16:25:03'),
(75, 37, 'We saw that the race, which God has called us to, is not a short sprint but rather a long distance marathon. It requires the energy of God’s Spirit, who is the One who empowers us to flee the dangers of this world and remain focused on serving God. We are also aware of our enemy called Satan who is determined to knock us off our path, to lose focus and backslide into the carnalities of the flesh. God’s Word tells us to resist the devil, and he will flee from us (James 4:7). While the Bible warns us to flee fornication (1 Cor. 6:18), flee idolatry (1 Cor. 10:14), flee youthful lusts (2 Tim. 2:22), and flee covetousness (1 Tim. 6:11), we are never told to flee from the devil, but rather to resist him. We are to stand up against the devil. To rest, we must hold on ground and maintain our position by creating an atmosphere of grace and spiritual victory that pushes the enemy away.', '2018-02-19 16:33:05'),
(76, 37, 'We must also know assuredly that the enemy will not let us flee worldliness and pursue godliness without putting up a fight. He knows we are human and will always come with all forms of temptations, which are intended to make us shift our ground and push back into the world. This is why there is a necessary instruction to walk in the Spirit in order to deny the lust of the flesh (Gal. 5:16). We are also certain that we already have victory over the devil. Romans 16:20 says that “the God of peace shall bruise Satan” under our feet.', '2018-02-19 16:33:05'),
(77, 38, 'For those of us who are into secular works or any entrepreneurial ventures, we see daily pressures of the enemy to weaken our position and to lose our grip in the walk of eternity. The pressures at the workplace and from the world on a day-to-day basis often shift our place in God with multiple temptations of official lies, corporate truth, conscious deception, and so forth. We must never lose our sense of the Lord Jesus Christ in the midst of secular pressures. The pressure for promotion at work must never become a temptation to join the world to sin.', '2018-02-19 16:33:05'),
(78, 38, 'Judas Iscariot was one of the twelve, and went out on preaching and healing crusades with the other apostles (Matt. 10:5–8). But he was a lover of money (John 12:4–6) and this greed caused him to betray the Lord for 30 pieces of silver (Matt. 26:14–16). A man who had such a great privilege of being numbered among the Lord Jesus’ apostles ultimately traded his eternal inheritance in God’s kingdom for a temporary desire for wealth. He did not lay hold on eternal life, but was deluded by the foolish and hurtful lusts that worldliness and love of money can bring. Peter said that those of us who have escaped the pollutions of worldliness will be in a worse state than ever if we allow ourselves to be entangled therein all over again (2 Pet. 2:20).', '2018-02-19 16:33:05'),
(79, 39, 'We are instructed to keep the commandment of God without spot and unrebukable, until the appearing of our Lord Jesus Christ. The understanding that we have shared above on who our Lord is should enable us to do this faithfully no matter the calibre or title of any persons who may oppress and oppose us. When I know that I belong to the Only One who has all power, I am encouraged to face all adversaries. ', '2018-02-19 16:42:34'),
(80, 39, 'The word “keep” in verse 14 is the Greek t?r?o which means to guard something from loss or damage. It means to watch over carefully to ensure safety and security. This is how we are to represent the Lord Jesus Christ  in this world, by carefully observing to do what His Word says. The word Paul used for “commandment” is a Greek word that means an “authoritative injunction or prescription.” It is not a suggestion or advice, but a military-type order from a higher ranking official to a subordinate. This means that God’s commandments are authoritative and He expects us to obey them. “Without spot” means that we keep his word unblemished, that is, without fault on our own part. It means we are obedient in season and out of season (2 Tim. 4:2), that is, when it is convenient we obey and even when it is inconvenient we must continue to obey the Lord. If the people around us love us, we obey God; if they hate us, we still obey God. We obey Him even if it means ending a pleasurable but ungodly relationship. We obey Him even if we are threatened with bodily harm or even death. We just simply represent the Lord Jesus Christ at all times and in all situations.', '2018-02-19 16:42:34'),
(81, 39, 'Knowing the glory and majesty of God through continual, ascending revelation will keep us steadfast, unmoveable, always abounding in the work of the Lord (1 Cor. 15:58), regardless of where we find ourselves in this world. We will please Him by keeping His commandment without spot, unrebukable, until that long-awaited day when we see Him face to face.', '2018-02-19 16:42:34'),
(82, 40, 'Wealth is relative and anyone who can meet his needs and have extra is wealthy enough to give to others. As Christians, we must remind ourselves that we are stewards of God’s blessings (1 Pet. 4:10). We should never be deluded into thinking that our finances and material possessions are solely ours, but realise that God is the Giver of all things, and that He expects us to make proper use of what we have been entrusted with. We are to be rich in good works, willing to distribute accordingly, “as God has prospered us” (1 Cor. 16:2).', '2018-02-19 16:48:39'),
(83, 40, 'God’s Word speaks of believers “distributing to the necessity of saints” (Rom. 12:13). The successful propagation of the Gospel requires our funding and input of money. As we distribute, we must focus on meeting “needs” and not “wants.” Needs are things that are required to survive. This would include the needs for food, clothing, and a place to lay one’s head. Wants are things or indulgences that are unnecessary but that we desire or wish. Example, “thirst” is a need that can be met with “boiled tap water” while Eva bottled water sold at N100 is a want serving the same purpose. In the same vein, the need to support someone’s university can be met with very good public university while it is an extra demand to consider a private university.', '2018-02-19 16:48:39'),
(84, 41, 'Even though Timothy’s parent and grandparent were strong believers who taught him the Scriptures, however that did not automatically earn Timothy his salvation. He still needed his own personal, “unfeigned” faith. Any childhood baptism or family connection in the church is insufficient for a person to be saved. We only become a “Christian” by having a personal relationship with the Lord Jesus and not through the religion of our parents.', '2018-02-19 16:58:01'),
(85, 41, 'For those of us who are parents, God expects us to train our children in His Word; we must also pray for them so that God can give the increase. Teaching them the God’s Word and correcting them lovingly (Prov. 23:13–14) is the planting and the watering.', '2018-02-19 16:58:01'),
(86, 42, 'Paul told Timothy to “stir up the gift of God which is in thee,” because “God hath not given us the spirit of fear” (2 Tim. 1:6–7). These two verses and statements are directly connected. God has not given us a fearful spirit, so we can freely and fearlessly express whatever gift He has placed in us. Many Christians fear man and, therefore, are afraid to operate their gifts of the Spirit. We know that the fear of man brings a snare (Prov. 29:25). Instead of operating in timidity, we should rather exercise our spiritual gifts in power, in love, and with a sound mind, that is, a mind that is controlled by God’s Word.', '2018-02-19 16:58:01'),
(87, 42, 'A world that is full of darkness needs God’s people to stand up and shine brightly. We are the light of the world; a city set on a hill cannot be hidden (Matt. 5:14). The Lord Jesus says that it does not make any sense to ignite a candle and hide it under a bushel (Matt. 5:15–16). It has to be placed on a candlestick, in full view of all, so that they may see and glorify our Father who is in heaven. In the same vein, we must not hide the gifts of the Spirit, but ignite and minister them courageously to whomever God has put in our lives and whomever else He sends us to.', '2018-02-19 16:58:01'),
(88, 43, 'Not only should we not be ashamed of the testimony of our Lord, we should see the great privilege, favour, and opportunity that we have been given through the Lord Jesus Christ. We must stand for the Lord Jesus Christ at all times and never be ashamed of our association with Him. There is no amount of affliction on earth that is anywhere close to the torment of hell (Luke 16:24). Our Lord Jesus has also commanded us not to fear them which kill the body, but rather for us to fear him who has the power to cast into hell (Luke 12:4–5). It is also assuring to know that “the sufferings of this present time are not worthy to be compared with the glory which shall be revealed in us” (Rom. 8:18).', '2018-02-19 17:01:45'),
(89, 43, 'So whether we are at our workplace, school, homes, or anywhere else, let us always remember what the Lord Jesus delivered us from. Let us remember that our sins are forgiven because of the afflictions and persecution He Himself suffered, and that we have eternal life for the same reason. We should, therefore, not let our circumstances and those around us intimidate us, but rather see how blessed we are in the Lord Jesus Christ and how much God our Father loves us.', '2018-02-19 17:01:45'),
(90, 44, 'Paul would not have been able to speak the way he spoke or do the things he did, if he did not know the Lord Jesus Christ on an intimate level of revelation. Today, God reveals Himself to His people on an individual basis and in different ways. The Lord Jesus has said “this is life eternal, that they might know thee the only true God, and Jesus Christ, whom thou has sent” (John 17:3). This knowledge comes from God Himself, and our faith is based on what He has already revealed about Himself that we now know without a doubt is true.', '2018-02-19 17:07:20'),
(91, 44, 'Every Christian who will stand is rooted on the platform of personal knowledge and not following the crowd. Christian faith requires seeing the invincible to go the extra mile to do the impossible. If our journey of faith is based on what someone told us at a time, then the likelihood of going farther and further is at risk. It is this type of assurance that provoked the writing of John the beloved in 1 John 1:1, “which we have heard, which we have seen with our eyes, which we have looked upon, and our hands have handled, of the Word of life.”', '2018-02-19 17:07:20'),
(92, 44, 'Paul said, I know whom I have believed. Can we say the same?', '2018-02-19 17:07:20'),
(93, 45, 'The second half of verse 12 of our text shows Paul’s confidence in the Lord Jesus Christ’s ability to preserve his salvation up until he passes into eternity. The Lord has promised to keep us in Him, as we live our lives in this present world, and bring us safely into His eternal kingdom. But we also have a responsibility towards Him. It does not come on a platter of gold; there is a mutual deal here as two partners have beneficial agreement. As we have deposited our lives to His trust, He also has deposited “that good thing” to our trust. That good thing is summarised as “the Good News,” that is, the Gospel. This involves us holding fast the form of sound words of the Gospel, as well as expressing the Gospel message through our daily lives. We can do neither of these two things without the enabling of the Holy Spirit who dwells in us.', '2018-02-19 17:07:20'),
(94, 45, 'It is He who teaches us the truth of God’s word, and it is He who lives through us to exhibit the fruit of the Spirit in our lives, as we cooperate with Him. This is why the Lord Jesus gave us “the Comforter” to guide us into all truth (John 16:13-14).', '2018-02-19 17:07:20'),
(95, 46, 'It is a known fact that men will fail us. It is a common truth that the same man whom you have spent all your life on will come back and stab you. It is pathetic when people talk about how the same person they sent to the university fails to allow their own children to put up with them for one-month industry attachment since they live faraway. Men will always be men! Human beings will always let us down from time to time. Sometimes, our trusted friends and even family members fall short of our expectations. Even the Lord Jesus’ own disciples fled when he was about to be arrested, one even left his clothes behind (Mark 14:50-52). The instruction to us is that we must not become bitter, resentful, or harbour hatred towards the offenders, since they are flesh-and-blood and prone to weaknesses of the flesh. Never allow the failure of another man to make you a failure in your walk with God. Forgive, forget, and move on and most importantly never expect any return from any man. Zero your mind for the worst, so that you do not carry any unnecessary pain that becomes a burden on your path. Rather, we should pray for them sincerely and put all our confidence in God instead. If we also guard ourselves emotionally, the disappointment will not hurt us so bad when it happens.', '2018-02-19 17:15:50'),
(96, 46, 'Let us quickly reflect again on Joseph’s episode in prison. We can remember in Genesis 40 how Pharaoh’ chief of bakers and chief of butlers both had dreams in a night and were sad the next day until Joseph interpreted their dreams. The butler’s dream came to pass after three days, as Joseph had told him but it was not until after two whole years (Gen. 41:1) when Pharaoh himself had a dream that the butler remembered Joseph (Gen. 41:9–14).', '2018-02-19 17:15:50'),
(97, 46, 'He was forgotten just like Paul, for two full years! But at the end of Joseph’s story, he saw everything that happened to him as all part of God’s greater plan, even forgiving his brothers who betrayed him (Gen. 45:5). He did not see himself as a victim, but as a victor in God’s purpose. The ultimate level of reasonable service is when we learn to forgive, forget, and avoid carrying the pain of what people failed to do for us or what they painfully did to us. Beloved, when we get disappointed or betrayed by others, let us remember who we are in the Lord Jesus Christ—that all things work together for good to them that love him, to them that are the called according to his purpose (Rom. 8:28).', '2018-02-19 17:15:50'),
(98, 47, 'Who knows what exactly Paul needed in the prison? Maybe a more adequate supply of soap to bathe, a little more food, a change of clothes, a copy of the Hebrew Scriptures or just to have someone to talk to in his moment of loneliness. Whatever the case, Onesiphorus supplied the need and “oft” refreshed him. In doing this, Onesiphorus may or may not have known that he was not just ministering to Paul, but indirectly to the Lord as well. The Lord Jesus has said that those people who ministered to even the least of his brethren were actually ministering to Him (Matt. 25:35–40).', '2018-02-19 17:15:50'),
(99, 47, 'This means that when we come to the aid of God’s people in need, He looks at it as if we were doing it to God Himself! That alone should motivate us not to be selfish, but to happily make use of our resources to help. In our case, it may just be simple visitation, regular prayer meeting in someone’s homes, frequent personalised SMS/WhatsApp messages (not bulk ones), and financial or material support. We also remember that when Paul was persecuting Christians before his conversion, the Lord Jesus asked him, “Saul, Saul, why are you persecuting me?” (Acts 9:4). In essence, this means that if we persecute, neglect, or abandon our fellow believers in their moment of need, we are persecuting the Lord indirectly. But if we minister to them, we are ministering to the Lord as well. May we take hold of this truth, and may the Lord give us the grace to be good stewards of all He has entrusted to us—our time, resources, and heart of love.', '2018-02-19 17:15:50'),
(100, 48, 'The first and most important thing for us to know is that we are only saved by the grace of God, through the faith He gives us in the Lord Jesus Christ Jesus. We do not deserve eternal life in God’s kingdom; but His own goodness, mercy, kindness, and love for us is what made Him to save us. We were all sinners that had fallen short of His glory (Rom. 3:23), deserving judgement and death (Rom. 6:23). The death spoken of here is not just the physical death of the body, but also the second death in the lake of fire (Rev. 21:8). It is necessary to grasp the eternal nature of our redemption to fully appreciate the saving grace of God. This same grace is what God uses to empower us unto good works, holiness, and righteousness. It is the fuel for the Christian life and service. <b>If this grace can sufficiently save us from sin, then it can sufficiently keep us from living in sin!</b>', '2018-02-19 17:23:24'),
(101, 48, 'Without this, we would just be attempting to serve God in our own strength and carnal capacity. This is why many “Christians” only practice outward religion, but have never encountered the saving grace of God that changes the human heart. The grace of God is the true enabler for a meaningful Christian walk with God.', '2018-02-19 17:23:24'),
(102, 49, 'Sometimes in our Christian service and life in general, we face pressure and trials, which can be overwhelming. We seem to be caged and bombarded on all sides. It appears as if we are the only one pushed into where the battle is hottest. The answer here is to, first of all, recognise our limitations to help ourselves and then turn wholeheartedly to the grace and ability of God. When we have “the sentence of death” upon us, speaking figuratively to represent any insurmountable challenge, then we must not trust in ourselves but in God who is able to raise the dead. That is why we should “come boldly unto the throne of grace, that we may obtain mercy, and find grace to help in time of need“ (Heb. 4:16). No man can help a man in time of need without the ministry of the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ. It takes grace not to be disgraced in life! Man’s strength is limited and insufficient, but the strength that is released through God’s grace is more than sufficient to move any mountain, and this grace is found in the Lord Jesus Christ.', '2018-02-19 17:23:24'),
(103, 50, 'A person who has been given something of eternal value is of necessity expected to faithfully handle such with high sense of responsibility. Unfortunately, many people who are supposed to be the trustees of God’s Word have proven to be incompetent and even destructive to the people they should be edifying. Men who have been called to deposit in people’s lives have actually been withdrawing from their lives. How sad does it sound when we hear leaders who exploit their followers sexually and still advise the affected individuals to continue to pretend along as if nothing happened? How irresponsible is it for a leader who is made to invest in others turns his flock into ATM and profiting from them for selfish gains? It is painful when we hear that some parents who opened their doors to some brethren out of their love for the Lord Jesus Christ have been milked to the bone by these brethren. It is painful that many of these innocent victims have closed their heart to the Lord Jesus Christ because of this exploitation.', '2018-02-19 17:28:31'),
(104, 50, 'The church is also seeking these faithful men in the areas of total accountability – men who can be trusted with God’s resources with utmost sense of regard and decency. Men and women of honour who know the boundaries between God’s things and their own things. Brothers and sisters who will not use their access to fellowship property for their own personal usage.', '2018-02-19 17:28:31'),
(105, 50, 'In the same vein, we need truly called faithful shepherd and not many who found themselves in the ministry because there are no jobs or they have failed in other areas of life. When a man comes to the ministry because he could not secure admission from mainstream institutions, then you can be sure that his congregation are on perpetual “admission,” like the sick in the hospital. Such a man is on a rat race, he wants to prove a point and he will spend more time in church politicking than in prayers in order to survive a ministry he was never called into. May God raise for His church faithful men who have come to the altar not to alter the truth of God!', '2018-02-19 17:28:31'),
(106, 51, 'The life of the believer is one of sacrificing now to reign later. The simple lesson is that we have to endure any difficulty now with the guarantee of reaping our rewards in due time. The Lord Jesus has said, “If any man will come after me, let him deny himself, and take up his cross daily, and follow me” (Luke 9:23). Three things are required here:', '2018-02-19 17:35:53'),
(107, 51, 'a)	<b>Self-denial.</b> The Christian life is a life of self-denial. The flesh desires many ungodly things, which must be put to death through the Spirit. God’s Word tells us that we cannot fulfil the lust of the flesh if we walk in the Spirit of God (Gal. 5:16–17). It also tells us that the flesh and the Spirit are contrary or opposing forces; therefore, we cannot do the things that the normal carnal man would do. An unbeliever may not see any big deal with sex outside marriage, telling lies, drunkenness, stealing, and being a lover of money. The follower of the Lord Jesus Christ, on the other hand, knows that these things are wrong and God is not pleased with them, so he must deny all ungodly inclinations of the flesh.', '2018-02-19 17:35:53'),
(108, 51, 'b)	<b>Cross carrying.</b> The Roman cross was an instrument of brutal punishment. It also brought public humiliation and rejection. What the Lord Jesus is saying here is twofold. The first part is a continuation of self-denial, “And they that are Christ’s have crucified the flesh with the affections and lusts” (Gal. 5:24). The second part has to do with the public humiliation and rejection, which the Christian may face “daily.” The Lord Jesus has said, “If the world hate you, ye know that it hated me before it hated you” (John 15:18). God’s Word further says we should be “looking unto Jesus the author and finisher of our faith; who for the joy that was set before him endured the cross, despising the shame, and is set down at the right hand of the throne of God” (Heb. 12:2). If we do not endure our cross now, we will never get to wear the crown later.', '2018-02-19 17:35:53'),
(109, 51, 'c)	<b>Following Him.</b> Following the Lord Jesus means walking in His steps through obedience. We may have to leave some people behind to follow Him, just as James and John had to leave their father Zebedee and the servants (Mark 1:20). Following the Lord Jesus is not the easiest endeavour on earth. We must do things His way even when it is painful. The Lord Jesus Himself said to God the Father, “not my will, but thine, be done” (Luke 22:42). He was willing to submit Himself to the higher will of God the Father, and so must we. Though following Him may get tough sometimes, we should never get discouraged. He has never promised us a smooth journey but a glorious destination. We must always be reminded that we have a guaranteed promise: “Therefore, my beloved brethren, be ye steadfast, unmovable, always abounding in the work of the Lord, forasmuch as ye know that your labour is not in vain in the Lord” (1 Cor. 15:58).<br/>\r\nThe conclusion is that we must endure the hardships and challenges that come with being identified as followers of the Lord Jesus Christ, if we hope to receive the reward of reigning with Him forever in glory. May the Lord give us the discipline, humility, strength, courage, and patience that we need to endure hardship. We will be glad that we went through the process when we finally hear Him say, “Well done, thou good and faithful servant!”', '2018-02-19 17:35:53'),
(110, 52, 'Our first key lesson is based on the necessity for the continual global spread of the Gospel in our present generation even in the midst of personal challenges and general threat. Even though Paul was bound in a Roman prison, he declared that the Word of God is not bound. The Gospel of the Lord Jesus Christ continued to increase unto the unreached territories even with Paul’s inability to move around—this is the beauty of the truth—no man can hold God to ransom.', '2018-02-19 17:45:43'),
(111, 52, 'Today we also cannot allow our circumstances to hinder the continuation of the Gospel message. Paul made a prayer request that the Word of the Lord may have free course (2 Thess. 3:1). That phrase “free course” is the Greek word trecho which literally means to “run or walk hastily.” His desire was to see the Gospel move quickly and permeate everywhere, such that his own personal situation must not be the basis of how far the Gospel will go or not. This is a big lesson for many of us who think the effectiveness of our service is tied to our good times. We are best in prayers when things are working and we do not even remember to visit new converts when things are not coming the way we want. The fact that certain expectations in our lives are delayed does not mean the mandate of God that we carry must suffer the same fate and be delayed. The fact that our miracles have not come does not mean we stop talking to others about God of all miracles. Many missionaries who served God in Africa continued to preach even while on the sick bed as a result of malaria—<b>the truth and urgency of the message is more important than the situation of the messenger!</b>', '2018-02-19 17:45:43'),
(112, 53, 'A major theme of 2 Timothy is the need for believers to endure the hardships of Christian life and ministry, in great expectation of the rewards promised by God. We have explored this previously but it is coming again as a critical theme for reasonable Christian walk of faith. In this particular instance, Paul even made it so generic that if our Lord Jesus went through the same as human—descendant of king David—we all must endure the pain and shame of the cross. Our degree of identification with His suffering is also an indicator of the degree of our glorification in His rising, hence a need to endure hardship as joint-heirs with Him (Rom. 8:17). If we be dead with Him, then we also get to live with Him. If we suffer with Him, then we also get to reign with Him.', '2018-02-19 17:45:43'),
(113, 53, 'The key summary is that we must always remember that many have suffered before us and have passed on into glory to be with the Lord. If the Lord Himself had to endure trials, and His apostles and followers through the centuries had to go through pain and challenges, then we should never shy away from the hardships of the Gospel either.', '2018-02-19 17:45:43'),
(114, 54, 'Many different teachings float around in Timothy’s time, and Paul gave him a strong antidote that would keep him from falling prey. He had to be diligent to show himself as an approved workman unto God by rightly dividing the Word of Truth. We saw how the phrase “rightly dividing” means to make a straight cut and not be a here-and-there minister who scatter with some Scriptures but cannot gather them back unto a holding focus. We make a straight cut through God’s Word by, first of all, accepting the plain meaning of the text, before moving into any deeper spiritual or symbolic meaning. The error of many is that they desire to have special knowledge of the Bible and, therefore, begin to invent spiritual doctrines that are non-existent in the passage. The Scripture often confirms itself through other parts of Scripture. We can know God’s mind and intent by comparing what He has said throughout the Bible and thus come to a consistent conclusion. We must remember that God does not contradict Himself but very consistent in using different text to validate the same truth.', '2018-02-19 20:17:09'),
(115, 54, 'Jesus our Lord is our best example on how to rightly divide the Word. He Himself had to quote Scripture to correct the compromised traditions of the religious people of His day. The Sadducees were a Jewish sect that taught false doctrines. They tried to trap the Lord Jesus by using what Moses said to prove that there is no resurrection (Matt. 22:23–33). But, of course, the Lord knew Scripture perfectly, and showed them things they were ignorant about. He even had to counter Satan’s misuse of the Word (Matt. 4:5–7). We should be like the Lord Jesus, who knew Scripture well enough to rightly divide it and “convince the gainsayers” (Titus 1:9).', '2018-02-19 20:17:09'),
(116, 54, 'The ultimate way out of error is to diligently study to show ourselves approved unto God. By doing this, we protect ourselves and other Christians from falling victim to the continual traps of the deceiver.', '2018-02-19 20:17:09'),
(117, 55, 'It is easy to be caught up in the web of debates concerning doctrine and theology. Paul already showed us that this only subverts the hearers (2 Tim. 2:14), furthers ungodliness (2 Tim. 2:16), spreads like gangrene (2 Tim. 2:17), and overthrows some people’s faith (2 Tim. 2:18).', '2018-02-19 20:17:09'),
(118, 55, 'Our focus rather should be on who we are in the Lord Jesus Christ and what our assignment on earth is. Reasonable service cannot be interrupted with confusions of false doctrines and false teachers. Some Jewish teachers including the Pharisees, who believed in the Lord Jesus, were teaching that the Gentiles could not be saved unless they were circumcised and kept the Law of Moses (Acts 15:1, 5). The apostles had to convene and come to the correct conclusion that the Law was for Israel and the Scriptures already pointed to a time when God would choose people for Himself from among the Gentiles. This led to what was probably the first epistle written to the Gentile church, which addressed four prevailing problems which a formerly pagan people would naturally struggle with—food offered in sacrifice to idols, fornication, eating strangled animals, and eating meat with the blood in it (Acts 15:20).', '2018-02-19 20:17:09'),
(119, 55, 'The apostles did not “strive about words to no profit,” but knew the mind of God through Scripture and came to the right conclusion. They wrote an epistle commanding them to depart from iniquity. They did not allow man-made confusion to interrupt their mission, but remained focused on what God had called them to do. We also must avoid doctrines of men and give full attention to what God has called each one of us to fulfil.', '2018-02-19 20:17:09'),
(120, 56, 'We have seen that in a great house are two kinds of vessels: one kind unto honour and the other kind unto dishonour. Ultimately, only the honourable vessels are useful for the kind of service required by God. Romans 9:21-24 shows us that the vessels of honour are unto glory, while the dishonourable vessels are fitted for God’s wrath and destruction.', '2018-02-19 20:27:37'),
(121, 56, 'In the study, we clarified clearly that each of us has a huge responsibility to play in becoming honourable or dishonourable vessels of the Lord. The Bible reads, “If a man therefore purge himself...” (2 Tim. 2:21), therefore, we are fully accountable for what we choose to do or not do in life. We are not saved by works of righteousness (Titus 3:5), but we are still God’s workmanship which He created in the Lord Jesus Christ for the purpose of doing good works (Titus 3:8, 14). Then, we must keep living a purged life to count in the scheme of God.', '2018-02-19 20:27:37'),
(122, 56, 'A life may have a prophetic destiny in God to become honourable vessel of gold or silver, but such a man has a role to play by walking worthy of the Lord unto all pleasing or else he will miss the promise. The path of purging is our daily effort to make ourselves fit and able to birth God’s purpose as vessels of honour. The fact that God desires vessels for use does not mean He will go for anything, in the manner as your thirst will not necessarily force you to drink a poison that is available. Beyond being available, we must be available in the best clean state for the Master’s use.', '2018-02-19 20:27:37'),
(123, 57, 'The word “vessels” is from the Greek word skeuos. It refers to containers or utensils. In ancient times, there was a wide array of skeuos in a house, and each had a designated purpose. The word skeuos could be used to depict everyday utensils, agricultural equipment, baggage, instruments of various sorts, vases used in worship, kitchen items, and elegant articles of gold and silver for display.', '2018-02-19 20:27:37'),
(124, 57, 'Vessels made from “wood and earth” were usually functional items used for everyday household use. The wooden items were also used as containers for water, flour, oil, or wine. Vessels fashioned from “gold and silver” were evidently intended for exhibition and were, therefore, displayed in visible places in the homes of the rich. Gold and silver objects were meant to be seen and appreciated rather than to serve a practical function. Different vessels, different uses, different levels of honour, and different situations of exposure.', '2018-02-19 20:27:37'),
(125, 57, 'This underscores the fact that all kinds of vessels and people are needed in God’s house. Imagine how dysfunctional a house would be if all the vessels in it were made of gold, silver, precious stones, or costly porcelain. It would be difficult to live in such a house. For a house to operate normally, it needs regular pots and pans! It needs special cups and ordinary cups. It needs tissue papers for the dining table and another type for the toilet—each serving different purpose. The utensils in the kitchen may not receive the same admiration as the more elegant objects displayed in the living room showcase, but kitchen utensils are essential for the proper functioning of a house.', '2018-02-19 20:27:37'),
(126, 57, 'By using such imagery, Paul indicated that all kinds of vessels—people with different functions and roles—are in God’s house. Although they are different from one another, each one is important and serves a purpose. In essence, the great house is filled to overflowing with human vessels whose various gifts and talents are essential to the effective functioning of the house. Some people have visible positions; other people have less visible positions. But each person is vital to the operation of God’s house. Each person also has the capability to determine if he will count for honour or dishonour.', '2018-02-19 20:27:37'),
(127, 58, 'We saw that relational and teaching skills are necessities in God’s servants who go to correct those in error or confusion. The goal is to be effective in giving the person an opportunity to hear the truth in a plain and simple presentation, thereby increasing the likelihood of understanding and accepting it, with a full appreciation that God Himself is the One who grants repentance. We must not strive, we must be gentle, we must be able to teach, we must be patient, and we must be meek. We must not have the attitude of “I must prove myself.”', '2018-02-19 20:35:44'),
(128, 58, 'The driving force that motivates us is twofold: (a) We love God and are His obedient servants and (b) we love our neighbour and do not want to see the person in a state of confusion. We must remember the early exhortation to avoid foolish and unlearned questions which generate strife, and accept the reality that there are people whom we should be very careful with when correcting or guiding into the truth. We have cases of unwise Christians who have been brutally killed before their time by their repeated persistence to convert a fanatical believer of another religion who has clearly shown anger and attitude of war. Always remember that our part is to operate in the right attitude and exercise the effective characteristics, and look to God for the outcome of a favourable fruit.', '2018-02-19 20:35:44'),
(129, 59, 'Paul and Apollos could plant and water through preaching and teaching, but it was beyond their ability to make anyone repent and accept the truth. Only God can do that; His goodness leads people to repentance (Rom. 2:4). After Paul took the whole day to explain and scripturally instruct the Jews about the Lord Jesus and God’s kingdom, the outcome was that “some believed the things which were spoken, and some believed not” (Acts 28:23-24).', '2018-02-19 20:35:44'),
(130, 59, 'We must do our part in teaching, but also intercede on behalf of our hearers that the Lord should grant the increase. This applies both to an unbeliever who is just hearing a clear presentation of the Gospel, or a person who is in doctrinal confusion and does not know what to believe. God willing, they will recover themselves out of the snare of the devil, and abide in truth unto eternal life.', '2018-02-19 20:35:44'),
(132, 60, 'If we really want to be sincere with ourselves, most of us know what false Christianity looks like. We know when a preacher is saying things that are completely wrong, as our conscience pricks us most of the times; but the aura of the so-called miraculous and our natural excitement towards theatrics blind our eyes from the fundamentals, as if we just love to be deceived. How do we explain it when a so-called man of God asks his congregation to drink petrol or to eat grass, or wear a cloth that is turned around in the opposite when they are not madly influenced? Even the Lord Jesus has said that our Father in heaven will never give us serpent, when He knows we need bread—same as our earthly father. So why will a pastor put our lives at risk and we still follow such a man foolishly (Luke 11:11)?', '2018-02-19 20:46:57'),
(133, 60, 'We only need to watch our television to see many of these Christian preachers whose practices are not different from traditional practice of witchcraft. They, of course, mention the name of the Lord Jesus, but we know they can actually praise God with their lips, but in reality, their hearts are far away from God (Matt. 15:7–9). The word “hypocrite” which Paul called them in verse 7 is a Greek word hupokrit?s, which literally means “an actor under an assumed character.” It means that this kind of preacher is only pretending to be somebody he is actually not. He has hidden agendas and ulterior motives. Like every actor, he is just acting to entertain us for the moment and his acting is not real because as soon as he leaves the stage, he takes on new characters. Have we not seen popular actors who just acted the role of a very rich man on television and the next time we see them on the street, they are jumping from one okada (commercial bikes) to another. This is the reality of actors on the pulpit; they pretend to be who they are not. They have a form of godliness when they are on stage but they deny the power thereof when they are out of stage.', '2018-02-19 20:46:57'),
(134, 60, 'But “the Lord knoweth them that are his” (2 Tim 2:19). We who are Christ’s must depart from this great iniquity of being an “actor.” We must not turn the church to a place of drama where we come to act as a holy sister in the choir on Sunday and in our real world we are not different from a harlot, or a brother who blasts in tongue and use the same mouth to sing worldly songs once he has left the church or fellowship. We must follow righteousness, faith, love, and peace, along with those who call on the Lord out of a pure heart (2 Tim. 2:22). The emphasis here is a pure heart! Let our hearts be pure and true—let us never deceive ourselves. It is an act of reasonable service to apply our reason or sense when we observe an error. Never allow a man of God to play on your intelligence or sense of reasoning. May God give us the discernment to avoid being seduced into error, in Lord Jesus’ name. Amen.', '2018-02-19 20:46:57'),
(135, 61, 'Even though Jannes and Jambres were imitators who withstood Moses and Aaron being genuine servants of God, the Lord and His people still got the ultimate victory in the end. Those who do not depart from falsehood and turn wholeheartedly to the Lord Jesus Christ will be the eventual losers in the end. The Lord Jesus has expressly promised that the “gates of hell” will not prevail against His church (Matt. 16:18). This means that no matter what the enemy does, we will still come out on top. Though there are many religions and false versions of Christianity, the Gospel is still being preached on every continent in the world and the undiluted truth of the Lord Jesus Christ continues to be translated into local languages with amazing impact everywhere. As we enter deeper into the perilous times of the last days, there will be more errors and opposition against absolute truth. The Lord Jesus already predicted that many false prophets will rise and deceive many (Matt. 24:11). We must pray to our Father in heaven to give us the strength and courage to stand up for Biblical truth without compromise. We will be vindicated (i.e., shown to have been right all along), when the Lord comes back (Matt. 24:31).', '2018-02-19 20:46:57'),
(136, 62, 'Paul once before told Timothy to “be thou an example of the believers, in word, in conduct, in charity, in spirit, in faith, in purity” (1 Tim. 4:12). Now in verse 10 of our text, he used at least four corresponding words to remind Timothy that he [Paul] also had been an example to Timothy in those areas. He said, “Thou has fully known my doctrine [word], manner of life [conduct], purpose, faith [faith], longsuffering, charity [charity], and patience.”', '2018-02-19 21:03:52'),
(137, 62, 'Paul could rightfully exhort Timothy to be an example to others because he himself had always been an example to the young minister. Christians today must always strive to live transparent and godly lives which speak volumes about the God they serve. We have all heard of many ministers and pastors who were good at preaching, but had many character flaws and moral shortcomings. Actions speak louder than words. Paul explained that Christians are living epistles, “known and read of all men” (2 Cor. 3:2–3). Some unbelievers may never even have opened a Bible to read, but may observe our lives and become curious for the truth, which, in turn, can lead to their salvation. It is a disaster to the kingdom when our neighbours cannot attest to our faith or be attracted to want to know more about our God because of our hostility and deliberate isolation.', '2018-02-19 21:03:52'),
(138, 62, 'The emerging younger generation are seriously in need of role model disciplers and mentors, whose lives can boost and fast-track their journey of growth in God. Moses was a godly example, and Joshua could attest to the genuineness of his ministry, his character, and his personal relationship with God, similar to Paul and Timothy. David saw the Spirit of God in Samuel and looked up to him as a godly guide and encourager. We can safely say that the strength of Elisha’s ministry was as a direct influence from Elijah. He received a double portion of his mentor’s spirit. Being godly examples should be a natural part of our reasonable service to God, as we not only encourage fellow Christians young and old, but also provide strengthening and edification for the next generation.', '2018-02-19 21:03:52'),
(139, 63, 'In verse 14, Paul urged us to “continue” in the things which we have learnt and have been assured of, since we know whom we have learnt from. Timothy learnt from the Scriptures and from his mother Eunice, his grandmother Lois, and the godly examples of Paul. Who are we learning from? This question is coming to us a second time with a lot of emphasis. There are many teachers out there teaching errors on our television stations, social media, and the newspapers! We can only have the kind of assurance that Paul spoke of by knowing the credibility of our spiritual sources. Do not be excited about a message or a manifestation without discerning the source for authenticity. Be careful in the spirit to know what is behind every crowd-pulling and attention-grabbing moves. Oftentimes, a fake Chinese product appears more attractive than even the original. May we not be deceived in Jesus name. Amen', '2018-02-19 21:03:52'),
(140, 63, 'To “continue” is a Greek word that means to remain steadfast. It means that we are consistent in Biblical truth, which leads to our spiritual growth and development. To bear fruit like we have said before, we [the branches] must abide in Christ [the vine]. A branch that does not “continue” and remain steadfast and abide in the vine loses its source of nourishment and withers away, eventually becoming good for nothing but to be burned (John 15:6).', '2018-02-19 21:03:52'),
(141, 63, 'We can only climb upward into spiritual maturity by abiding in the Lord’s truth. We must “continue” in the things which we have learnt and assured of, knowing that who we are learning from is the Author of life and existence, the Creator of heaven and earth.', '2018-02-19 21:03:52'),
(142, 64, '<i>“All Scripture is given by the inspiration of God.”</i>', '2018-02-20 11:06:13'),
(143, 64, 'Everything else about our faith depends on this. The Creator of the earth and the heavens could have chosen to reveal Himself to the human race in any other way, but He has chosen to use written words. He told Moses to write the words of His covenant with Israel (Exod. 34:27). He told Isaiah to write the word (Isa. 8:1–4). He told Jeremiah to write many prophecies (Jer. 36:2). He also told John to write the entire vision He was about to show him (Rev. 1:11). The Lord Jesus and the apostles continually used the phrase “It is written” before quoting the necessary Scripture. They were very clear about the source!', '2018-02-20 11:06:13'),
(144, 64, 'Our confidence in God’s written Word comes from our confidence in God Himself, for “He that hath received his testimony hath set to his seal that God is true” (John 3:33). The Bible is also a witness to its own self. It was written by forty different authors on three continents (Africa, Asia, and Europe) over a span of about 1,500 years. The authors of these books came from different social classes and walks of life: kings, shepherds, priests, farmers, judges, fishermen, and tentmakers.', '2018-02-20 11:06:13'),
(145, 64, 'Historic and archaeological evidence continually point to the Bible’s accuracy and reliability. Secular archaeologists have through the centuries unearthed names of cities, kings, and ancient cultures, which the Bible speaks of that many historians did not believe until the physical evidence said otherwise. Biblical prophecies from people such as Isaiah and Daniel concerning secular kings and kingdoms have come to pass precisely as foretold. For example, Isaiah prophesied that Cyrus would one day be ruler of an empire (Isa. 45:1) and that God would use him to rebuild the temple in Jerusalem (Isa. 44:28). God’s Word says that all of Isaiah’s prophecies were recorded during the reigns of Uzziah, Jotham, Ahaz, and Hezekiah (Isa. 1:1). It was more than 140 years after his prophecy that Cyrus took the throne and fulfilled the Word of God spoken by Isaiah (Ezra 1:1-4). We have secular record which validates that this event actually happened, as seen in the “Cyrus Cylinder,” a cuneiform-inscribed cylinder, written by the Persian king, discovered in the ruins of Babylon in March 1879, and is kept today in the British Museum in London. It contains the edict of Cyrus where he encouraged foreign captives in Babylon to return to their homelands and serve their own gods.', '2018-02-20 11:06:13'),
(146, 64, 'We can also talk about Daniel’s fulfilled prophecies concerning the Babylonian, Medo-Persian, Greek, and Roman empires (Daniel 2:31-42 and other portions of the book, which accurately predicted the fall of the Medo-Persian empire to Alexander the Great’s Greek empire and the eventual rise of the Roman empire through four generals from Alexander’s reign [Daniel 8]).The Bible is 100% true for all ages and times!', '2018-02-20 11:06:13'),
(147, 65, 'The summary of what Paul was telling us in our text today is that we are to serve God faithfully and consistently. The Lord Jesus has promised that He is coming back to judge and reward mankind according to how we have lived and served in this present time. The fulfilment of our ministry is, therefore, quite a serious matter. He says we must be instant in season and out of season. We must do our job whether the external circumstances are good and easy or bad and challenging. There are no excuses for not serving the Lord, no matter the situation.', '2018-02-20 11:16:14'),
(148, 65, 'We must be faithful in season and out of season, enduring afflictions and preaching the Word, until we reach the completion of the assignment which the Lord has given each one of us to fulfil on earth.', '2018-02-20 11:16:14'),
(149, 65, 'Our service to God must not be subjected to the convenience of our own timetable; it must always be at God\'s own terms: all time, all season, when it makes sense and when it does not make sense.', '2018-02-20 11:16:14'),
(150, 65, 'If the whole essence of our commitment to God is only based on our situation, then it is a most unreasonable service.', '2018-02-20 11:16:14'),
(151, 66, 'It seems we are already in the times which Paul spoke of, when Christians will no longer endure sound doctrine. Many have already gone after teachers of strange forms of excesses that diverge from the Bible or a mix of Biblical doctrines with deceptive falsehoods. We need to be extremely careful not to fall into the temptation of going astray from what God has plainly commanded us.', '2018-02-20 11:16:14'),
(152, 66, 'God appeared to Solomon twice and promised to establish his descendants on the throne for all generations, with the only requirement being his obedience in abiding in God’s statutes, commandments, and ordinances (1 Kings 3:14–15, 9:1–9). Solomon walked with God consistently for a notable season in life, but when he got older, his foreign wives turned his ear away from the truth of what God had said to him, and caused him to be turned unto the fables of their pagan gods (1 Kings 11:4–13). God was not pleased and the kingdom became divided with Israel in the North and Judah in the South, with Solomon’s descendants ruling the Southern kingdom. Though Solomon erred greatly, we know that at the end of his life God restored their fellowship and showed him mercy, because of the promise made to David his father (2 Sam. 7:12–15). But the rest of us have no such guarantee. We do not know the day of his appearing and there may not be a second chance.', '2018-02-20 11:16:14'),
(153, 66, 'Our only hope is to remain in sound doctrine, as God has said in His Word. We cannot afford to be misled by seducing spirits, or we may never recover, as Peter warned (2 Pet. 2:21). The warning is repeated with a stronger tone (Heb. 6:4–8). May we be content with God’s revelation of spiritual truth and believe that His divine power has indeed given us all things that pertain unto life and godliness (2 Pet. 1:3), and see that everything we need in life can be found in God’s Word—the Bible, with no need for any extra.', '2018-02-20 11:16:14'),
(154, 67, 'The Lord Jesus has said, “Whosoever will save his life shall lose it, but whosoever shall lose his life for my sake and the gospel’s, the same shall save it” (Mark 8:35). Losing our lives means releasing it unto the Lord for His use as He sees fit, instead of selfishly pursuing the vanities of this world. Paul could look back on his life and say, “I have fought a good fight, I have finished my course, and I have kept the faith.” There is not a more beneficial and rewarding way to spend our time on earth than in devoted service to our Lord Jesus Christ, who died and rose so that we may be partakers of His eternal kingdom. Beloved, there is no better story a man can have than how his life has been spent for the Lord.', '2018-02-20 16:12:14'),
(155, 67, 'We must always ask ourselves: How am I spending my time, my finances, my energy, and my resources? Am I doing all to the glory of God (1 Cor. 10:31)? What is my ultimate passion and heart’s desire? What will my life count for in the weights of God?', '2018-02-20 16:12:14'),
(156, 67, 'At the end of our time on earth, may we not regret our existence. May we be like Paul, who could joyfully pour out his soul as a drink offering unto God, knowing he had done his job and fulfilled his divine assignment on earth.', '2018-02-20 16:12:14'),
(157, 68, 'Christians will all appear before the judgement seat of Christ, for the purpose of receiving different rewards according to what we did with our salvation (2 Cor. 5:10). Some will build valuable works with their salvation, represented as gold, silver, and precious stones; but others will build weak structures and poor service, represented as wood, hay, and stubble (1 Cor. 3:10-15). Though there could possibly be more, the Bible mentions at least five crowns, that deserving Christians will receive from the Lord when that day comes. The crown of rejoicing is reserved for soul winners. The crown of righteousness is for Christians who are diligent in righteousness. The crown of glory is reserved for church leaders who have ruled well. The imperishable crown is for those who have exercised self-denial to please God. And the crown of life is for martyrs.', '2018-02-20 16:12:14'),
(158, 68, 'You may ask how an individual can wear three or four crowns on the same head. Well, we do know that even in the ancient Rome, kings used to wear three crowns of iron, silver, and gold. The Bible also records that the Lord Jesus had many crowns upon His head as King of kings (Rev. 19:12). Therefore, our aim should be to strive to obtain as many crowns as the Lord gives us the gifts and opportunity to serve His purpose. Paul qualified for all the five crowns listed. As we pour out our lives in reasonable service to the Lord, we should keep in mind that He takes account of our devotion and ministry, and He will one day return to give every man according as His work shall be (Matt. 16:27, Rev. 22:12).', '2018-02-20 16:12:14'),
(159, 69, 'Even in Paul’s affliction, when it seemed as if the whole world had deserted him, the Lord Jesus was right by his side at all times, keeping him company, putting joy in his heart, cheering him up, and encouraging him to keep moving forward. The Lord Jesus has promised to never leave nor forsake us, and to be with us to the very end (Matt. 28:20). Before Paul’s house arrest at Rome, the Lord Himself had personally appeared at least once to him after his salvation experience (Acts 18:9–10) and, on another occasion, sent an angel to him (Acts 27:23–25). On both occasions, he had an assurance of protection from the Lord, along with his guaranteed presence. We must always remember whom we serve and whom has called us into the Christian life and ministry. The certainty of our safety cannot be doubted. We are not going out on our own charges and the One who sent us is fully there by our side.', '2018-02-20 16:33:34'),
(160, 69, 'There came a time in Elijah’s life when he was in a situation that looked like all Israel had forsaken him as a lone ranger fighting against the Baal kingdom (1 Kings 19:9–18), but in reality, God was with him and had also reserved seven thousand people in Israel who had not fallen away into apostasy (1 Kings 19:18). God was also with Paul in his loneliest season, but like Elijah and Israel, the Lord also reserved a small amount of people for Paul, such as Timothy, Luke, and Onesiphorus as back-up supporters or intercessors to give human touch of God\'s always-there presence.', '2018-02-20 16:33:34'),
(161, 69, 'He will never let us down; he will never fail us; he will never forsake us. He knows that the road is a little rough and that there are many challenges. As we continue to fulfil our course on earth, let us keep the reality of his everlasting presence in our minds, which will enable us to overcome all trials.', '2018-02-20 16:33:34'),
(162, 70, 'Though Paul was old, imprisoned, and forsaken by many trusted friends, he did not allow such things to stop his ministry of the Gospel. He used Mark to take care of some ministerial duties, which his limitations would not permit him to do himself. He was still a useful vessel to the Lord and he knew that by him “the preaching might be fully known, and that all the Gentiles might hear” (2 Tim. 4:17). He even kept studying and learning from books to continue developing spiritually and mentally for more effectiveness in his ministry. He still believed he had a ministry and could still do more as long as he was alive and breathing. This is the right attitude to have for Christians of all ages under all circumstances.', '2018-02-20 16:33:34'),
(163, 70, 'In our world today, we are faced with all kinds of negativities and oppositions to the truth and righteousness. Our co-workers might despise us or our employers deny us of rightful promotions. We may also find ourselves not being adequate financially as we would like to be, desiring to take God’s Word and kingdom further than where we presently are. In spite of all these and other personal challenges, we must determine in our hearts and minds to continue serving the Lord faithfully and with enthusiasm just like Paul. The fact that admission has not come, marriage is delayed, or a good job has not materialised must never be an excuse to reduce our commitment to the kingdom. The fact that we are still believing God for the fruit of the womb does not mean we cannot be fruitful in other areas and carry lives in the womb of grace. No Christian has any excuse to take eyes off the joy of eternity because of the short-time pain of the temporal life that we live. No one can compare a hundred years on earth with billions of years in eternity, which is like a drop of a grain of sand in an ocean!', '2018-02-20 16:33:34'),
(164, 70, 'Throughout history, God’s people have had to deal with varying forms of trials, which could have made them give up or feel they have already done enough. But the true heroes are those who have kept on doing God’s will till their final breath. May we continue in reasonable service to God for the full length of our lives. May we be diligent and happy to serve for as long as we are alive in this physical body, in the Lord Jesus’ name. Amen.', '2018-02-20 16:33:34');
INSERT INTO `prayer` (`prayer-id`, `study-id`, `row`, `date`) VALUES
(1, 40, 'Lord, open my eyes to see every area where I am already taking steps into strange\r\nliving, relationship, lifestyle, affection and commitments that are contrary to your will and purpose.', '2018-11-02 12:04:26'),
(2, 40, 'Lord, burden my heart for your presence. I refuse to remain with a strange land\r\nwhere prayer, holiness and discipleship are becoming strange to my life. Lord, place\r\nin my heart a perpetual longing for you…a hunger that only your presence can fill.\r\nPsalm 42:1-2.', '2018-11-02 12:04:26'),
(3, 40, 'May our souls thirst after God continually, and not be distracted by the busyness of\r\nthe present world.', '2018-11-02 12:04:26'),
(4, 40, 'May He grant us to know Him better (Hosea 6:6, John 17:3), because the more we\r\nknow Him the more we will love Him, which is the first commandment and what He\r\nultimately desires from us.', '2018-11-02 12:04:26'),
(5, 40, 'May the Lord work in our hearts a desire to do His good pleasure (Phil. 2:13, Psalm\r\n40:8). So that wecan pant after God like the thirsty deer after the water brook, or like\r\nDavid in Psalm 63:1.', '2018-11-02 12:04:26'),
(6, 40, 'May the Lord give us courage to fight the spiritual battles (Eph. 6:10-18)and any\r\nunclean spirits that attempt to take us captive through sin.May He grant us the\r\nstrength to recover from any backslidden state, and the focus to never look back.', '2018-11-02 12:04:26'),
(7, 41, 'Father, I refuse to lose my identity in Christ. I remain focused in projecting your name no matter the ridicule that comes with it.', '2018-11-02 12:27:46'),
(8, 41, 'May God grant us grace to purpose in our hearts like Daniel not to defile ourselves\r\nwith the daily demands of the present Babylon.', '2018-11-02 12:27:46'),
(9, 41, 'We receive grace to renew our consecration. We receive divine help to stand true to our decisions for God even when it is becoming old fashion. We reject the pressures of the world and fortify our feet in the mercy of the Lord for a consistent stand in Jesus name.', '2018-11-02 12:27:46'),
(10, 41, 'Lord, put in my heart a vacuum and a longing that only your presence can fill. Create in me an eternal desire for you that does not change by time, age, location or circumstance in Jesusname.', '2018-11-02 12:27:46'),
(11, 42, 'We pray that the Lord will quicken our hearts to grasp and understand His timetable\r\nover our lives in Jesusname (Luke 24:25).', '2018-11-02 12:39:58'),
(12, 42, 'We receive grace to nurture, treasure and birth all the prophetic words that have\r\nbeen spoken over our lives and future. They will not be wasted, they will not be\r\npostponed or cancelled in Jesusname.', '2018-11-02 12:39:58'),
(13, 42, 'We receive grace for diligence in rightly dividing the word of truth like Daniel and the promptness to act with the right attitude of prayerfulness, fasting and humility of hearts in Jesus name.', '2018-11-02 12:39:58'),
(14, 42, 'May the Lord grant us foresight like the wise virgins, so we can see the importance of\r\npreparation, and we will not miss the coming of the Bride in Jesus name.', '2018-11-02 12:39:58'),
(15, 42, 'May God open our eyes to see the need for revival before it is too late.', '2018-11-02 12:39:58'),
(16, 44, 'May the Sovereignty of God reign over my life and may He rule and reign in all the\r\naffairs of men over my life and destiny in Jesusname.', '2018-11-02 12:57:05'),
(17, 44, 'We decree that the Lord will raise men and women, men of power and honour, who\r\nwill stand in our favour and work for our good to bring forth the plans and purpose\r\nof God in Jesusname.', '2018-11-02 12:57:05'),
(18, 44, 'We receive discernment and humility of hearts to walk with all types of men\r\nwithout corruption of our faith.', '2018-11-02 12:57:05'),
(19, 44, 'May God reveal Himself to everyone around us who have not yet known Him as the\r\nSovereign of heaven and earth. May He touch and stir their hearts unto salvation\r\nlike Cyrus in Jesusname. (Dan. 4:25-26, Acts 17:24).', '2018-11-02 12:57:05'),
(20, 45, 'Lord, set our affection on things above and not on things on the earth. We break off\r\nfrom every excusethat shiftsour minds away from the soul of men (Col. 3:2),', '2018-11-02 13:08:22'),
(21, 45, 'We ask for the passion for the house of God, the dying soul of men and the Church\r\n(1Tim. 3:15). “The zeal of your house has eaten me up”, John 2:17. May we have zeal\r\nfor God\'s house, which will drive us to leave our comfort zone and participate in\r\nmatters of the kingdom.', '2018-11-02 13:08:22'),
(22, 45, 'We receive grace to be a\r\ntrusted vessel that can go for the Lord no matter the\r\nroughness of the road.', '2018-11-02 13:08:22'),
(23, 45, 'We break off from every weight, distractions, pressures, tensions and challenges\r\nthat are shifting our attention away from the callof the Lord over our lives.', '2018-11-02 13:08:22'),
(24, 46, 'We pray that God grants us the grace to first seek His kingdom and His righteousness above all else.', '2018-11-02 13:32:19'),
(25, 46, 'We trust the Lord to always meet our physical needs as wewillingly offer our lives to the service of the Kingdom. We shall never be put to shame as He provides all our needs according to His riches in glory.', '2018-11-02 13:32:19'),
(26, 46, 'We receive grace not to waste every physical provisionthat God has made available\r\nto us for the purpose of the kingdom expansion. We shall not divert every increase\r\nand lifting for self. We shall not become selfish, self-centred and arrogant and forget where to lay our treasures in Jesusname.', '2018-11-02 13:32:19'),
(27, 48, 'We receivethe help of the Lord to restore and bring back the instruments of true\r\nworship, especially heartfelt prayer, and application of Biblical principles to our practical daily lives.', '2018-11-02 13:44:48'),
(28, 48, 'May we do His will from our hearts (Eph. 6:6), so that all our outward deeds are\r\nsincere, genuine, and effective.', '2018-11-02 13:44:48'),
(29, 48, 'We pray for a total recovery that brings us back to a level higher than wehave been.', '2018-11-02 13:44:48'),
(30, 48, 'We ask for divine awakening from any spiritual slumber and backsliding that wemay\r\nhave fallen into, so that we become aware of our state and start thirsting after God\r\nagain.', '2018-11-02 13:44:48'),
(31, 49, 'God, grant us the zeal, and the courage, to forsake anything that is keeping us in\r\nBabylon and keeping us from entering into our full calling.', '2018-11-02 13:59:59'),
(32, 49, 'Lord, grant us diligence to pay attention to the details of our lives, as you pay\r\nattention to details. May we not be slack or compromise in any area, and may your\r\nHoly Spirit convict us when we do, and restore us to intimate fellowship with you.', '2018-11-02 13:59:59'),
(33, 49, 'We pray that no sin will have dominion over us ( Rom. 6:14), or cause our names to be excluded from the Lamb\'s book of life.', '2018-11-02 13:59:59'),
(34, 50, 'Lord, grant us the grace to focus and to be single-minded in the pursuit of divine\r\nmandate. We reject every form of distraction and ask that the Lord cut us off from\r\nevery assignment that we are doing that is not of the Lord.', '2018-11-02 14:25:56'),
(35, 50, 'We receive a fresh zeal for the mandate of revival and for building lives of men. We receive a new impartation to be a master builder, who is committed to building the temples of God in the lives of men.', '2018-11-02 14:25:56'),
(36, 50, 'Nothing shall we hold back. Freely we have received and freely shall we give all that we have for the cause of the kingdom.', '2018-11-02 14:25:56'),
(37, 50, 'Father, set us on fire for your glory. Let us become willing to go above and beyond; willing to go the extra mile for the Kingdom.', '2018-11-02 14:25:56'),
(38, 52, 'I receive the fresh fire of the Lord to build a true altar in my prayer life. Set my altar on\r\nfire and let it remain fresh, in connection with the Lord Jesus Christ. Lord, clear every\r\ndust and ashes on my altar and renew me in a fresh relationship with you.', '2018-11-02 14:39:24'),
(39, 52, 'Lord, establish my life on the foundation of Christ. Fortify my feet in the path of the cross and build me up on the nature and character of Christ.', '2018-11-02 14:39:24'),
(40, 52, 'I reject every temptation and tendency to break off from the unity of the spirit. I refuse every inner thought and action that created vision, consciously or\r\nunconsciously in Jesus name.', '2018-11-02 14:39:24'),
(41, 52, 'I repent of every act of disunity that I may have caused or am causing. I repent of every act of gossip or backbiting that I may have done which has cut off the hearts of the affected ones from the Lord Jesus Christ.', '2018-11-02 14:39:24'),
(42, 53, 'Lord, fortify my foundation to stand the test of time. Give me inner strength to\r\nwithstand challenges, pressures and oppositions of life.', '2018-11-02 14:54:24'),
(43, 53, 'Lord, I receive grace to live by the singular demand of your foundation, which is to depart from all iniquities. I receive grace to flee all appearances of evil and divine help to stand strong in holiness.', '2018-11-02 14:54:24'),
(44, 53, 'I declare that my life will not be a source of collapse to the foundation of the Lord that is ever sure.', '2018-11-02 14:54:24'),
(45, 53, 'Father, I receive grace to be guided and mentored and will not lose touch with the\r\nsource of this vision. I refuse every spirit of disobedience that disconnects a man from instruction and discipleship.', '2018-11-02 14:54:24'),
(46, 53, 'As a leader, I receive grace to be available, understanding, mature and relevant to support the emerging generation. I receive depth and clarity of mind to always\r\nsupport, guide, coach, mentor and disciple the next generation according to your\r\npattern for this vision.', '2018-11-02 14:54:24'),
(47, 54, 'Lord, I come against every attempt of the devil to shift me away from the established truth of your word.', '2018-11-02 15:07:22'),
(48, 54, 'I receive grace and inner strength to say NO to every satanic influence, doctrinal\r\nerror and distraction of time in Jesus name.', '2018-11-02 15:07:22'),
(49, 54, 'I understand that I am God\'s representative in my local church and I am promising\r\nJesus that no error or evil will be permitted to thrive in Jesusname.', '2018-11-02 15:07:22'),
(50, 54, 'I receive boldness to stand firm and oppose every error of the devil everywhere I find myself.', '2018-11-02 15:07:22'),
(51, 54, 'Lord, we receive a fresh baptism of the gift of discernment to unravel every mystery\r\nof iniquities (2 Thess .2 vs 7) that abound in our times in the name of new revelation\r\nin Jesus name.', '2018-11-02 15:07:22'),
(52, 54, 'Lord, protect us from deceptive distractions, assignments and roles that intend to\r\ninfiltrate and eventually hinder the work of building your kingdom on earth, which\r\nyou want to use us to accomplish.', '2018-11-02 15:07:22'),
(53, 56, 'We lay hold on our position in Christ. We refuse to shift to opposition. We receive\r\ngrace to abide in our calling and stand firm till the end.', '2018-12-03 19:08:58'),
(54, 56, 'Heavenly Father, may the enemy never succeed in attempts to weaken our hands\r\nand discourage us. And may your LOVE for us bring us out of any depressing\r\ncircumstances wemay have found ourselves in Jesusname.', '2018-12-03 19:08:58'),
(55, 56, 'I come against every form of fear that has held me captive in sin or in the hold of\r\nmen. I break off from every threat that has compromised my walk with the Lord and\r\nreduced my service in the kingdom.', '2018-12-03 19:08:58'),
(56, 56, 'I will not faint in the days of adversity. I receive divine encouragement to face\r\nchallenges and frustrations without compromise in Jesus name.', '2018-12-03 19:08:58'),
(57, 56, 'I re-adjust my focus on the Almighty God alone. I look up unto the hills, where comes\r\nmy help. I declare that vain is the help of man and the Lord alone shall be my trust in\r\nJesus name.', '2018-12-03 19:08:58'),
(58, 57, 'We blot out all the handwritings of all ordinances that are written against us by the\r\nblood of Jesus.\r\n', '2018-12-03 19:20:45'),
(59, 57, 'We refuse every guilt and accusation of the devil that is weakening our hearts from\r\nserving the purpose of the Lord.', '2018-12-03 19:20:45'),
(60, 57, 'We receive divine wisdom to manage every past issue that we need to address and\r\nresolve in Jesus name.', '2018-12-03 19:20:45'),
(61, 57, 'We receive divine confidence to face every mistake of the past and turn them into\r\nstepping stones of greatness in Jesus name.', '2018-12-03 19:20:45'),
(62, 57, 'We receive the comfort of the Lord on every scar of the past that has remained a\r\ncontinuous pain point on our journey in life.', '2018-12-03 19:20:45'),
(63, 59, 'Lord, help me to make you the One and Only of my life. I reject and refuse all\r\ndistractions that are taking my eyes off the call and demand of God in Jesus name.', '2018-12-03 19:35:55'),
(64, 59, 'I cut off from every assignment that the Lord has not called me unto. I break away\r\nfrom every assignment of man and human agenda that is contrary to the plan of God\r\nfor my life.', '2018-12-03 19:35:55'),
(65, 59, 'I open up my spirit to the prompting of the Holy Spirit. I refuse to be misled by men or\r\nselfish desire. My conscience is opened unto divine instructions and guidance in\r\nJesus name.', '2018-12-03 19:35:55'),
(66, 59, 'Lord, keep our ears sensitive to your voice, so that we can “hear what the Spirit says\r\nunto the churches”.', '2018-12-03 19:35:55'),
(67, 59, 'We receive discernment, so we can identify the difference between a\r\nfalse prophet\r\nand a genuine one which you have sent.', '2018-12-03 19:35:55'),
(68, 59, 'Father, grant us the spirit of discipline and long-term focus, so that we can be less\r\nconcerned about our material needs and more concerned about the long-term goals\r\nyou have set for our lives.', '2018-12-03 19:35:55'),
(69, 60, 'Lord, I receive a fresh grace for determination. A fresh commitment to lay down my\r\nlife in trust of your ability to fix everything on my behalf', '2018-12-03 19:49:55'),
(70, 60, 'Lord, come through for me as I face the fears and uncertainties of life. Let every\r\nmissing scroll of my destiny be found. Grant me favour beyond my expectations and\r\nturn my afflictions into joy in Jesus name.', '2018-12-03 19:49:55'),
(71, 60, 'Lord, I receive help to stand firm in the midst of challenges and oppositions.', '2018-12-03 19:49:55'),
(72, 60, 'Lord, I receive divine help that comes from those who stand for you in all spheres of\r\nmy life and ministry in Jesus name.', '2018-12-03 19:49:55'),
(73, 60, 'Father, grant us the spirit of courage and strength, so that we refuse to compromise\r\nour assignment and purpose which you have given us to do on this earth in Jesus\r\nname.', '2018-12-03 19:49:55'),
(74, 61, 'Lord, we pray that you grant us the grace to consecrate our lives to you for the sole\r\npurpose which you put us on this earth for. Let our lives be dedicated and set apart\r\nunto you, and unto the work of the Gospel of Christ Jesus.', '2018-12-03 20:01:23'),
(75, 61, 'Grant us grace to derive fulfilment in being human temples and vessels for the Most\r\nHigh God, and may Your Spirit use us to do great things on the earth.', '2018-12-03 20:01:23'),
(76, 61, 'Heavenly Father, we pray also that you pour out Your Spirit as the latter rain, and\r\ncause a heavy move of revival that will be characterised by salvation of souls,\r\nrededication and heavenly consciousness in Jesus name.', '2018-12-03 20:01:23'),
(77, 61, '•We pray that you prepare and position us for the Second Coming of Your Son Jesus\r\nChrist—we shall be rapturable and heaven-ready.', '2018-12-03 20:01:23'),
(78, 63, 'Lord, let the light of the revelation of your Word enlighten our darkness and let it\r\nprovide a new drive to dig deep into the depth of your word.', '2018-12-03 20:12:07'),
(79, 63, 'Lord, grant us a new passion and hunger for the living word like water to a thirsty\r\nsoul, let your word become real to us like never before.', '2018-12-03 20:12:07'),
(80, 63, 'We pray the word of God will take a\r\ndeeper root in our lives and provide the strength\r\nfor the word of revival in Jesus name.', '2018-12-03 20:12:07'),
(81, 63, 'Father, fill us up with your Word and your Spirit, so that we are empowered to\r\nactivate revival wherever you send us. Let us be labourers in your harvest, and let\r\nthe people be drawn to you through the living word in our lives in Jesus name.', '2018-12-03 20:12:07'),
(82, 64, 'Lord, we receive grace to reach out and recruit more souls and workers for you.', '2018-12-03 21:09:07'),
(83, 64, 'We receive fresh understanding to work in the unity of the spirit, maturity and order\r\nto be able to complement other Christians for the sake of the kingdom revival.', '2018-12-03 21:09:07'),
(84, 64, 'We receive divine empowerment for discipleship and mentoring. We receive grace\r\nfor impartation in raising high-quality workers to deepen the work of revival in\r\nJesus name.', '2018-12-03 21:09:07'),
(85, 64, 'Father, we also pray that your people will be united in the Spirit (\r\nEph. 4:3-4). May we\r\nsee the need for agreement and cooperation, as we achieve much more for the Lord\r\nin one accord.', '2018-12-03 21:09:07'),
(86, 64, 'We come against every spirit of disunity, rumours, hearsays, personality tensions and\r\nwrong attitude that is weakening our ability to work together for kingdom advance.', '2018-12-03 21:09:07'),
(87, 65, 'Lord, we receive grace to trust you as our source, shield and supplier at all times and\r\nin all circumstances. We refuse all help that you have not given us and we refuse to\r\ncheapen your call by seeking human help.', '2018-12-03 21:25:51'),
(88, 65, 'We receive grace to wait on the Lord at all times for instructions and guidance. At no\r\ntime, shall we launch out for God\'s work without heaven\'s backing.', '2018-12-03 21:25:51'),
(89, 65, 'We receive grace for effective fasting and prayer life. We pray for brokenness,\r\nhumility and genuine submission that translates fasting into kingdom impact.', '2018-12-03 21:25:51'),
(90, 65, 'We receive your sure and abiding presence in our lives\' journey. We receive\r\nprotection and covering for every stage and phase of our passage in destiny. We shall\r\nnot become victims and no calamity shall come near us in Jesus name.', '2018-12-03 21:25:51'),
(91, 67, 'Lord, help us to separate from the defilement of the world and to remain\r\nconsecrated unto you as living sacrifice.', '2018-12-03 21:39:40'),
(92, 67, 'Lord, we pray that the Holy Spirit who dwells within us will convict our hearts\r\nanytime we begin to drift into worldliness.', '2018-12-03 21:39:40'),
(93, 67, 'We pray that you give us wisdom to engage this world without being drawn into its\r\nungodly ways, much like Daniel operated in Babylon without compromising his\r\nfaith. We receive grace not to be stained by the corruption of our time.', '2018-12-03 21:39:40'),
(94, 67, 'We receive divine help to be eternally minded and yet earthly serving your purpose\r\nwithout compromise and corruption.', '2018-12-03 21:39:40'),
(95, 67, 'Father, place the burden on our hearts for lost souls who have not encountered the\r\nsalvation of Jesus Christ; and may our intercessions be followed with preaching\r\nand teaching of the Gospel, so that more people can be saved.', '2018-12-03 21:39:40'),
(96, 67, 'Let the burden of the house of the Lord eat us up with deep sense of intercession to\r\nstand in the gap for our church until true revival breaks forth.', '2018-12-03 21:39:40'),
(97, 68, 'We pray for a release of fresh burden for souls of men and a\r\nnew passion that seeks\r\nfor genuine conviction of sin.', '2018-12-03 21:51:50'),
(98, 68, 'Father God, we pray that your Holy Spirit will convict us of any sins we may have\r\nbeen rationalising away as not so bad. We pray that you bring every secret sin and\r\nerror to our attention in a way that we cannot deny but repent genuinely.\r\n', '2018-12-03 21:51:50'),
(99, 68, 'We ask for fresh fire in our lives and ministries (\r\npreaching, teaching, singing,\r\ncounselling etc.) that it may be filled with grace for conviction of sin and power to\r\ndraw men into full encounter of the reality of God in Jesus name.', '2018-12-03 21:51:50'),
(100, 68, 'Father, we ask for grace and spirit of humility, so that we can make restitution for\r\ndamages we have done in the past as the Holy Spirit will convict and lead us in\r\nJesus name.', '2018-12-03 21:51:50'),
(101, 69, 'Lord, burden my heart again to feel the heartbeat of heaven per time.', '2018-12-03 22:04:21'),
(102, 69, 'Lord, let my heart remain connected to the burden of heaven and let not the\r\ndemand of life disconnect me from the signals and frequency of divine instruction.', '2018-12-03 22:04:21'),
(103, 69, 'Lord, let me not be content with my life success only, but let my passion and longing\r\nfor kingdom expansion in the hearts of men be my reason for living in Jesus name.', '2018-12-03 22:04:21'),
(104, 69, 'May the zeal of the Lord\'s house consume me to long for the welfare of many lives\r\nwho are in ruins of a life that has no wall.', '2018-12-03 22:04:21'),
(105, 69, 'Grant us the spirit of excellence in our secular work, passion for continuous self improvement\r\nand God-glorifying outcome as we cause your light to shine through\r\nthe work of our hands in Jesus name.', '2018-12-03 22:04:21'),
(106, 69, 'We also pray for the wisdom and ability to carry out our career obligations while\r\nbringing revival to wherever our heart\'s burden and your Spirit leads us.', '2018-12-03 22:04:21'),
(107, 71, 'Lord, we rededicate our lives to you to be a trusted vessel whose life you can trust\r\nand in whose hand you can drink from.\r\n', '2018-12-04 07:14:59'),
(108, 71, 'Father Lord, my life will not bring poison to the King of kings. I\r\nwill not desecrate\r\nthe altar of the Lord with a poisonous lifestyle in Jesus name.', '2018-12-04 07:14:59'),
(109, 71, 'We receive courage and strength to be fearless risk-takers in the service of your\r\nkingdom.', '2018-12-04 07:14:59'),
(110, 71, 'We receive grace for discipline for consistent self-improvement, self-upgrade and\r\ncontinuous learning as a platform for self enhancement and kingdom impact in\r\nJesus name.', '2018-12-04 07:14:59'),
(111, 71, 'We refuse to be a\r\nliability in the kingdom. We build capacity to be an asset whose\r\nlives and sphere of influence can expand the frontiers of the kingdom in\r\nJesus name.', '2018-12-04 07:14:59'),
(112, 72, 'Lord, grant me grace, patience and discipline to stay long in the place of preparation\r\nwhere burdens from heaven are perfectly birthed into vision and action in\r\nJesus name.\r\n', '2018-12-04 07:25:16'),
(113, 72, 'I reject every diversion of burden and spiritual abortion of divine purpose.', '2018-12-04 07:25:16'),
(114, 72, 'I refuse every act of service that is not rooted in the divine leading and God\'s will.', '2018-12-04 07:25:16'),
(115, 72, 'I pray that you stir up my spirit so that I see the spiritual need around me, and so I see\r\nthat revival is needed in my home, community, nation, and the world at large.', '2018-12-04 07:25:16'),
(116, 72, 'I receive grace to be an inspirational leader whose lifestyle, passion and motivation\r\ndraw men into the purpose of God and into the vision of revival.', '2018-12-04 07:25:16'),
(117, 73, 'Lord, I receive a fresh baptism of the vision of revival—to be clear and to be sure of\r\nthe demands of God with a brilliant picture of the glorious future that God has for\r\nthis great house.', '2018-12-04 13:05:56'),
(118, 73, 'I refuse to be spiritually blind and short-sighted. I receive spiritual long range sight to\r\nsee into the accurate future and be motivated to pursue this all my life.', '2018-12-04 13:05:56'),
(119, 73, 'Lord, we pray that you equip us with the gift of foresight. Open our eyes so that we\r\nsee areas of great need, and help us with drawing up a clear-cut plan to meet that\r\nneed.', '2018-12-04 13:05:56'),
(120, 73, 'Lord, help us to inspire others with the gift of our tongue in communicating the vision\r\nfor great results in our home, family, workplace and relationships.', '2018-12-04 13:05:56'),
(121, 73, 'Lord, let your favour make all the difference in our lives. Grant us favour with men in\r\nways that actualise and accelerate your perfect will for our lives.', '2018-12-04 13:05:56'),
(122, 75, 'Father, let me be a\r\ntrusted vessel. I\r\nrefuse to be a\r\nsource of leakage of spiritual\r\ninstruction. I receive God-led silence as a fence of my spiritual journey.', '2018-12-04 13:20:04'),
(123, 75, 'Father, I\r\nreceive grace to be better organised and be more disciplined with sharper\r\neyes for details, smarter mind for careful thinking and deeper heart for better\r\nresults in Jesus name.', '2018-12-04 13:20:04'),
(124, 75, 'I receive wisdom that guides moments of instructions.', '2018-12-04 13:20:04'),
(125, 75, 'Lord, may my steps and stops be ordered by you.', '2018-12-04 13:20:04'),
(126, 75, 'I refuse to be a fool who reveals all his thoughts without discretion, but God baptise\r\nme afresh with temperance and self-control as a daily manifestation of the fruit of\r\nthe spirit.', '2018-12-04 13:20:04'),
(127, 76, 'Lord, I receive grace to be accountable and responsible in the portion of the task that\r\nyou have trusted my life with. I receive help to abide in my calling and work out my\r\ntask allocation in divine location.\r\n', '2018-12-04 13:38:39'),
(128, 76, 'Father, we receive grace, humility of heart and maturity to work with others with a\r\nhigh sense of mutual affection and love of Christ.', '2018-12-04 13:38:39'),
(129, 76, 'We come up against every pain and offence of the past that are consciously and\r\nunconsciously limiting our availability for kingdom demand.', '2018-12-04 13:38:39'),
(130, 76, 'We receive grace for excellent leadership and excellent practice in our homes,\r\nworkplaces, subgroups and life generally.', '2018-12-04 13:38:39'),
(131, 76, 'We receive grace to be trusted followers who take every delegation seriously with\r\nan utmost sense of excellence. We shall not disappoint leaders to whom you have\r\nattached our lives to.', '2018-12-04 13:38:39'),
(132, 76, 'We pray that we will be faithful, loyal, trustworthy, and cooperative in any area of\r\nservice you place us in.', '2018-12-04 13:38:39'),
(133, 77, 'Father, I\r\nreceive divine encouragement in the midst of the ridicule, fear and threat of\r\nthe enemies in Jesusname.', '2018-12-04 13:48:17'),
(134, 77, 'I reject the pain of every negative word that has been spoken against me in my path.', '2018-12-04 13:48:17'),
(135, 77, 'Father, wereceive grace to abide in your presence for a\r\nrenewed mind at all times.', '2018-12-04 13:48:17'),
(136, 77, 'I receive grace for a balanced and most fulfilled spiritual and rewarding secular\r\nlife. None shall bring shame and disgrace to the name of the Lord.', '2018-12-04 13:51:07'),
(137, 81, 'Lord help us to remain faithful as watchmen. We receive divine prompting and sharp\r\nspiritual antenna to download from heaven\'s frequency per time and to be able to\r\nstand in the gap in sincere and faithful ministry of intercession in Jesus name.', '2018-12-04 19:39:08'),
(138, 81, 'Our Father, we thank you for each victory we receive. We receive grace not to go to\r\nsleep after each victory. We ask that you grant us the attitude to be on guard at all\r\ntimes against the wiles of the devil.', '2018-12-04 19:39:08'),
(139, 81, 'We reject every deception of status and lifting that takes away the innocence of\r\ngenuine service to the Lord. No lifting will lift us away from God in Jesus name.', '2018-12-04 19:39:08'),
(140, 81, 'We also pray that you give us a\r\nfresher vision for the future, so as to raise high-quality\r\nsons and daughters of grace and glory, who will continue the next lap of this relay\r\nrace of eternity.', '2018-12-04 19:39:08'),
(141, 81, 'May our success in God transcend time. May the fire we ignite continue even when\r\nwe are not there in Jesus name.', '2018-12-04 19:39:08'),
(142, 82, 'Lord, breathe into my life and ministry and make me a true oracle of your word who\r\nspeaks at the frequency of heaven.', '2018-12-04 19:48:40'),
(143, 82, 'Lord, let my ministry produce impact and result for the kingdom.', '2018-12-04 19:48:40'),
(144, 82, 'Lord, I receive divine caution and alertness to respect every opportunity given to\r\nme to be a vessel. I receive grace for preparation, discipline and excellence in\r\nJesus name.', '2018-12-04 19:48:40'),
(145, 82, 'Lord, anoint us afresh and fill us up with your Spirit, and let the word of truth\r\nwhich we preach convict and convert the hearers.', '2018-12-04 19:48:40'),
(146, 82, 'May your indwelling Spirit flow through us and impart understanding to our\r\naudience in Jesus name.', '2018-12-04 19:48:40'),
(147, 83, 'Lord, break the yoke of sin— corruption, selfishness, tribalism, nepotism and all\r\nforms of unrighteousness in our nation in Jesus name.', '2018-12-04 19:58:26'),
(148, 83, 'Lord, burden my heart afresh for a godly move of righteousness in our community\r\nand nation.', '2018-12-04 19:58:26'),
(149, 83, 'Lord, use me to build altar of revival in nations.', '2018-12-04 19:58:26'),
(150, 83, 'Lord make me a vessel of reformation in every facet of life— spiritually, physical,\r\nfinancial, health, governance.', '2018-12-04 19:58:26'),
(151, 83, 'Lord, lead our nation into a revival of values, God-consciousness, honesty, morality,\r\nexcellence and good governance in Jesus name.', '2018-12-04 19:58:26'),
(152, 83, 'Our Father in heaven, help us to be humble people before you. Help us to see and\r\nadmit our crimes and our wrongs. Give us the courage that we need as individuals\r\nand as a people to repent and turn from our evil deeds. Help us to love our neighbour\r\nas ourselves, and actually care about the welfare of one another. Help us to be more\r\nunited in seeking your face. Heal our land.', '2018-12-04 19:58:26'),
(153, 83, 'Let the Holy Spirit bring conviction to the hearts of our leaders. We pray that they see\r\nthe truth of your word that righteousness exalts a nation.', '2018-12-04 19:58:26');
(154, 85, 'Lord, plant an eternal longing in my life that only your presence can fill. Lord, baptise me with fresh passion to seek for more of God.', '2019-10-04 14:14:26');
(155, 85, 'Father, I receive grace to serve God with no other gods. I reject all distractions shifting my heart from God or placing themselves side-by-side the place of God in my life.', '2019-10-04 14:15:26');
(156, 85, 'Grant me, I pray, the strength to continually remain grounded in Who You are, and what You have said in Your Word', '2019-10-04 14:16:26');
(157, 85, 'Lord, may the fullness of the Godhead live within me, teach me, guide me, instruct me and direct my journey in this life. In Jesus’ name I pray. Amen.', '2019-10-04 14:17:26');
(158, 86, 'Lord, I humbly pray the prayer which David prayed in Psalm 139:23-24, “Search me, O God, and know my heart: try me, and know my thoughts: And see if there be any wicked way in me, and lead me in the way everlasting.” Lord, search my life.  Create in me a clean heart, and renew a right spirit within me (Psalm 51:10).', '2019-10-04 14:18:26');
(159, 86, 'Heavenly Father, give me grace and commitment to invest the efforts needed to spend time in your Word and in Prayer. Help me make any necessary sacrifices, such as cutting down time spent in recreational activities, time spent watching TV and movies, time spent at social functions, etc., so that I can invest more into our relationship, building a sure and steadfast foundation with you thereby.', '2019-10-04 14:19:26');
(160, 87, 'Lord, put the new fire of prayer and passion for the word of God in my heart.', '2019-10-04 14:20:26');
(161, 87, 'Father, create a genuine longing for the word of God in my heart.', '2019-10-04 14:21:26');
(162, 87, 'I receive fresh grace for another level of commitment to my quiet time – consistent prayers and ministry of the word.', '2019-10-04 14:22:26');
(163, 87, 'Father in heaven, help me to be sincere in my prayer life with you. Grant me grace to pour my heart to you at all times, worshiping you in spirit and in truth.', '2019-10-04 14:23:26');
(164, 87, 'Lord, help me understand your Word. Make it clearer and clearer to me. Give me insights and revelations into areas which I have previously remained blinded to. I desire a firm and sure foundation in these critical aspects.', '2019-10-04 14:24:26');
(165, 88, 'Heavenly Father, open the eyes of my understanding so I can really see and realise who I am in your Son Jesus Christ. Help me believe what you say about me and to walk in them every day of my life.', '2019-10-04 14:25:26');
(166, 88, 'Lord, I confess my identity in you. I identify with the work you did for me on the cross of Calvary and I rise up in the authority that I have in Christ.', '2019-10-04 14:26:26');
(167, 90, 'Father, let me see myself the way you see me. Let the light of your truth shine in my heart unto genuine encounter in Jesus name.', '2019-10-04 14:26:26');
(168, 90, 'I receive grace to work out my salvation with fear and trembling. I will not waste the investment of God in my life or take for granted the precious work of Calvary', '2019-10-04 14:27:26');
(169, 90, 'I refuse to walk in lies. I receive grace to have a transformational change of heart and grace to turn unto the Lord completely in Jesus name.', '2019-10-04 14:28:26');
(170, 91, 'Lord, help my heart to face the errors of the past that continues to threaten my walk with God', '2019-10-04 14:29:26');
(171, 91, 'I receive the humility of heart and the guidance of the Holy spirit to restitute as the Lord leads and guides me in Jesus name.', '2019-10-04 14:30:26');
(172, 91, 'I receive divine courage to not only acknowledge the wrong I have done to others, but also to go back and make practical corrections wherever possible.', '2019-10-04 14:32:26');
(173, 91, 'Lord, I also ask that you grant me the financial means to recompense those who I am indebted to. Help me pay back what I owe', '2019-10-04 14:33:26');
(174, 92, 'Lord open the eyes of my mind for me to understand my position in you', '2019-10-04 14:34:26');
(175, 92, 'Lord I believe, help my unbelief. I overcome every fear of the unknown as I rise into my position in you in Jesus’ name.', '2019-10-04 14:35:26');
(176, 92, 'I take authority over sin, self and Satan in Jesus’ name.', '2019-10-04 14:36:26');
(177, 92, 'Lord, I pray for boldness to stand in the authority of Jesus’ Name. Remove fear and doubt from my inner man. Let me not be the double-minded man who is unstable in all his ways. Give me the confidence and courage to operate from that place of authority. Use me to accomplish your will in the earth, as I present myself as a living sacrifice and a willing vessel in Jesus’ Name.', '2019-10-04 14:38:26');
(178, 93, 'Heavenly Father, thank you for your will for me as outlined in your written Word. Empower me to walk in obedience to what I find in your Word', '2019-10-04 14:39:26');
(179, 93, 'Lord open my heart to you perfect will for my life', '2019-10-04 14:41:26');
(180, 93, 'Lord, I pray that you reveal to me in what ways you want me to use the gifts and abilities you’ve blessed me with. Give me courage to not hide my gift like the man with one talent', '2019-10-04 14:42:26');
(181, 93, 'Help me realise my God-ordained purpose in this world', '2019-10-04 14:43:26');
(182, 93, 'Lord let my mind and heart be renewed by the blood of Jesus, let the light of God flood my heart ', '2019-10-04 14:44:26');
(183, 93, 'Lord, teach and guide my paths by your spirit, lead me in way to go and direct my  feet in the path to follow, cause my ears to hear your voice saying this is the way go therein', '2019-10-04 14:45:26');
(184, 95, 'I receive the grace to build the discipline of hearing God', '2019-10-04 14:45:26');
(185, 95, 'I cut off from every distractions and turn off from all other voices and noises shifting my mind away from God', '2019-10-04 14:46:26');
(186, 95, 'Lord, Give me an ear to hear. Adjust my spiritual listening skills in a way that recognises your voice in my inner man', '2019-10-04 14:47:26');
(187, 95, 'Lord, Let my spirit become sensitive to know when it is you, and able to discern when it is not you.', '2019-10-04 14:48:26');
(188, 95, 'Create in me a clean heart, O God, and renew a right spirit within me. Let my inward man be expectant of a holy visitation via dream or vision. Speak to me through as you will', '2019-10-04 14:49:26');
(189, 95, 'I will not fall into errors of wrong leading in Jesus name', '2019-10-04 14:50:26');
(190, 96, 'Lord Jesus, help me to have an encounter of salvation in you.', '2019-10-04 14:51:26');
(191, 96, 'Lord Jesus, l receive all grace to be a true disciple', '2019-10-04 14:52:26');
(192, 96, 'Lord Jesus, help me to be submissive under your tutelage', '2019-10-04 14:53:26');
(193, 96, 'Lord Jesus, I receive grace to yield my neck to His yoke.', '2019-10-04 14:54:26');
(194, 96, 'Lord Jesus, I receive boldness to deny what the world has to offer me', '2019-10-04 14:55:26');
(195, 98, 'Lord, let me not live the place of making until You are eventually formed in me.', '2019-10-04 14:51:26');
(196, 98, 'Dear God, I receive the grace to patiently wait in the place of divine incubation until my egg is hatched. I refuse to roll out of Your warmth and become a spoiled egg.', '2019-10-04 14:56:26');
(197, 98, 'Lord, I refuse to die a barren but make disciples of others for you after I have been made one myself. I will be a blossoming tree, bringing out its fruits in its seasons.', '2019-10-04 14:57:26');
(198, 99, 'Father help me to live my life for you alone. I renounce everything in me that is contending with your Lordship over my life.', '2019-10-04 14:58:26');
(199, 99, 'Lord, help me to live a life of consecration always and to dedicate my entire life to you', '2019-10-04 14:55:26');
(200, 99, 'Lord give me a heart to be completely sold out to the ministry of raising an army with a vision of revival.', '2019-10-04 14:59:26');
(201, 99, 'I pledge allegiance to the Lamb to be faithful, loyal and honest to Him every day and night, so help me God.', '2019-10-04 15:00:26');
(202, 99, 'I pledge allegiance to the Lamb to be faithful, loyal and honest to Him every day and night, so help me God.', '2019-10-04 15:01:26');
(203, 100, 'Father, please grant me a new hunger to walk in the Spirit.', '2019-10-04 15:02:26');
(204, 100, 'Holy Spirit, please give me the grace to yield totally to you', '2019-10-04 15:03:26');
(205, 100, 'Lord, deliver me from every encumbrance of the flesh. Please, set me free Lord.', '2019-10-04 15:04:26');
(206, 100, 'Father, saturate my spirit man with the influence ofs Your Spirit till I no longer live for myself but for You alone.', '2019-10-04 15:05:26');
INSERT INTO `reflection` (`reflection-id`, `study-id`, `row`, `date`) VALUES
(1, 40, 'Are there areas of my life where I am already taking a journey away from God on a path to a\r\nstrange land? Is my affection and interest already straying away from God? Am I physically\r\npresent with the brethren but my soul and spirit have travelled far into a strange land of\r\nimmorality?', '2018-11-02 12:00:50'),
(2, 40, 'Am I already joined to someone in a strange relationship or a business partnership that does\r\nnot agree with the principles of God?Am I already entering a strange emotional relationship\r\nwith someone that is not my spouse or already fantasising about a strange woman or man in\r\nmy thoughts? Have I joined a strange group on WhatsApp where what we share or discuss\r\nisin complete disobedience to the instructions of God? Have I joined a group or association\r\nwhere everything we discuss is completely strange to Christian faith? Am I living a life that is\r\ncompletely strange to the tenets of a disciple and being part of a revival army?Have I taken a\r\njourney like Jonah away from the presence of the Lord? Am I living on the Lord\'s side or\r\nalready in a strange land?', '2018-11-02 12:00:50'),
(3, 40, 'Sometimes where you are used to is not where you belong and that is why you must not\r\nallow your experience to determine your appetite.', '2018-11-02 12:00:50'),
(4, 41, 'Am I longing for God or for gold? Am I longing for eternity or for the short-term enjoyment of\r\nthis temporary world? As a person who is supposed to be a revival agent,where has my\r\nallegiance been lately? Where is my heart, and my mind? What do I desire and long for, and\r\nwho or what does my mind think about the most? Have I put the cares of this life ahead of\r\nGod\'s kingdom? What consecration do I have in my walk with the Lord and how do I cherish\r\nthem and stand by them even in the midst of the worst pressures. Have I become like some of\r\nthem who indulge in mixing worldly songs with the spiritual melody in a quest to gain\r\nacceptance and to sound modern? Do I listen to worldly songs in secret and pretend to be\r\nsomething else to the brethren. What do I browse on the internet when no one is there?\r\nWhat songs are stored on my phone? What lyrics do I share with friends? What books and\r\nmovies do I indulge in when no one else is around? What can I change in my attitude, and\r\nhow can it be shifted from any compromise or complacency unto the Kingdom?', '2018-11-02 12:25:25'),
(5, 42, 'The word of the Lord, spoken by the mouth of Jeremiah, came to pass as predicted. What are\r\nthose words that the Lord has spoken to me that are looking forgotten or impossible? Am I\r\ntaking God\'s prophecies seriously or have I just dismissed them as unimportant? Where are\r\nmy jotting books that capture many years of divine instructions, promptings, dreams and\r\nrevelations? Do I study them to be guided by what God has said in the past?', '2018-11-02 12:36:46'),
(6, 42, 'Am I worried that those great prophecies of a glorious future, fruitful marriage, global lifting,\r\nheavyweight of glory and many others may not come to pass because of the negativities and\r\nmultiple delays around me? <b>God is not a man that he should lie.</b>', '2018-11-02 12:36:46'),
(7, 42, 'Be assured that all of His words over your life will come to pass. Be assured that God is never\r\nlate. God is always on time. God\'s timing is always perfect and opportunity presents itself\r\nwhen He believes we are ready, we only need to trust the process. When the timing is right\r\nand we are unready by reason of wrong attitude, a postponement or cancellation of divine\r\npromise may happen. It is, therefore, important to understand His timetable and be like the\r\nchildren of Issachar who understood times and knew what to do per time (1 Chr 12: 32)', '2018-11-02 12:36:46'),
(8, 42, 'Of higher importance is how I take the prophecy of the second coming of Christ. When last\r\ndid I remember that the trumpet may sound unannounced? When last did I evaluate my life\r\nto be sure I am ready to meet the groom as a chaste virgin without spot or wrinkle. How am I\r\npreparing for the inevitable end of the age?', '2018-11-02 12:36:46'),
(9, 44, 'Have I limited God by doubting His ability to touch the hearts of anyone as He wills? How do I\r\ntreat my unbeliever neighbours, co-workers, in-laws, family, alumni groups etc? How do I\r\ntreat my local church minister? Who have I been looking down on, not realising that they\r\nmay be a key component in bringing God\'s will to pass in my life? When was the last time I\r\nconsciously prayed for my leaders at work, church and in the country? Do I always enjoy\r\nblaming, causing and abusing those in power even when I have not genuinely invested in\r\nprayer concerning them?', '2018-11-02 12:55:17'),
(10, 45, 'Can God trust my life to go for Him? Am I so attached to my past that I cannot yield my future\r\nunto the Lord? Am I so emotionally connected to my certificates, achievements and lifting\r\nthat they have become a god in my life? Am I truly available for this call of revival or I am just\r\npretending and hanging around with no genuine commitment to the cause of DISCIPLESHIP?\r\nAm I a Christian who is willing to forsake worldliness, sacrifice old friends and networks for\r\nthe ridicule of following Jesus? Will I be among His people who will answer the call to true\r\nrevival? Is my local home church suffering because Ihave failed to let go of my comfort to\r\ninvest time in true discipleship? Is my family altar fire going down because of the excuses of\r\nwork pressures and never-ending targets? Have I put on His wedding garment, or is my\r\nspiritual clothing inappropriate and still stained with sin? Am I just enjoying the ambience of\r\nfeel-good place of worship at the detriment of serving the Lord in a lower level place where I\r\nhave been called unto as a revival army?', '2018-11-02 13:06:28'),
(11, 46, 'Who am I looking up to; to meet the demands of the work of God? Have I become a slave to\r\nman in a quest to raise money for the work of God? Am I serving God and mammon (Matt.\r\n6:24), or do I have my priorities in order by first seeking God\'s kingdom and righteousness\r\n(Matt. 6:33)? Have I in any way compromised my spiritual walk because of ungodly\r\nmonetary pursuits? Do I organise spiritual programmes or visits out of a hidden desire to\r\nraise money to meet my needs and not genuinely for salvation of souls? Is ministry making\r\nme irresponsible in meeting demands of life as a parent? Am I really sure God is calling me\r\ninto a \'full-time\' ministry when there ismore than enough free time to engage my hands\r\ninbeneficial income-generating projects to support my family and the work of God?', '2018-11-02 13:30:27'),
(12, 48, 'What aspects and areas of my life have I left in a Babylonian worldly temple for a long time now? What part of my emotional and financial investment are still in the world, being used to promote the god of Babylon? After returning to the Lord, after a few months/years of backsliding, have I truly been restored back to my former state or am I only struggling in pretence and deceit? How much of my previous spiritual gifts and depth of revelation have\r\nbeen restored back in higher fold after I sorted my walk with the Lord? How can I restore these areas of my life to their proper place where they are supposed to be in Christ?', '2018-11-02 13:42:32'),
(13, 49, 'Am I in the right position doing the right thing? Am I in God\'s assignment or man\'s\r\nassignment? Have I left the comfort of what I love to go to the discomfort of where God wants\r\nme to be? Do I take my local fellowship seriously or do I prefer the aura of the central events?', '2018-11-02 13:58:47'),
(14, 49, 'What am I pursuing in life that is keeping me away from my God-ordained purpose for His\r\nkingdom? Is there any career goal or academic hunt that is hindering my spiritual progress? Is\r\nGod calling me to something far greater? Also, is my life in order according to God\'s will? If\r\ntoday were my last day on earth, would my name be found written in the heavenly register?\r\nHave I lost my identity to secret sins, a lifestyle of online fraud, betting, pornography and\r\nother modern sins that are corrupting our souls?', '2018-11-02 13:58:47'),
(15, 49, 'Do I keep important records in the things of God? Do I pay attention to details on the critical\r\nthings of the souls of men and things of heaven in my care? Do I take God\'s demand with a\r\nhigh sense of accountability or do I just do it anyhow?', '2018-11-02 13:58:47'),
(16, 50, 'Is my eye focused on the assignment that God has given unto me or I have become distracted by things happening around me? Have I become so busy here and there that I have forgotten the most important reason why I am called into this vision of revival? Am I sure I am pursuing the vision of revival or I am serving self or man\'s agenda? Am I genuinely sold out to the cause of the Lord or I am a pretender whose heart is far from God? Am I working in the fellowship so that men will see me and not from my hearts? Am I giving myself freely and willingly to Him?<br/> Am I focused on the things of the kingdom, or letting myself be distracted by worldliness?<br/>\r\nWhat areas of my life need spiritual resuscitation, and what do I need to adjust in my thoughts, words, and deeds? What can I do for God, which I am not doing already? Am I building lives or just playing fellowship?', '2018-11-02 14:23:33'),
(17, 52, 'Do I have a place of continuous connection with the Lord? Do I have an altar where I connect\r\nwith God and God connects with me? Am I standing on the right foundation? Is my Christian\r\nlife in agreement with the nature and character of Jesus? Do I even have a sure foundation in\r\nChrist through genuine salvation and a true life of holiness or am I a pretender?', '2018-11-02 14:36:30'),
(18, 52, 'Am I living in unity with other brethren? Do I have an ill-feeling, hatred or bitterness against\r\nsomeone? Have I decided to cut myself off from the brethren or detach from the leadership\r\ninstruction? When we gather as a fellowship or a subgroup in the name of the Lord, are we\r\ntruly one or are we just faking it? Am I an instrument of disunity? Do I peddle rumours about\r\nothers? Do I indulge in gossips and tale-tellinghere and there in the name of brotherly care?\r\nHave I become an instrument of division in the household of God whose actions and\r\nreactions are weakening the bond of love?', '2018-11-02 14:36:30'),
(19, 52, 'Am I a follower of Christ in thought, word, and deed, or am I struggling to align my outward lifestyle and daily choices with my inward convictions of Biblical truth?', '2018-11-02 14:36:30'),
(20, 53, 'What is my foundation in Christ today? Is it still standing or have I been blown away by the\r\npressures of life? Have the delays and denials that I have witnessed lately shifted my feet\r\naway from the foundation of the Lord that is sure? Have I permitted secret sins in my life? Is\r\nmy spiritual life already collapsing because an iniquity is weakening my foundation? Am I on\r\nthe path of a shaky foundation? Is my consecration responding to the forces of challenges,\r\ntemptations, persecution that are coming my way? Am I standing strongdespite the storm\r\nand adversity?', '2018-11-02 14:51:19'),
(21, 53, 'How is my relationship with those who are older than I in the vision, especially those whom\r\nthe Lord has committed the oracles of the vision? Do I cooperate in humble reverence, or do I\r\nwalk in conscious disobedience? Do I submit to leadership? Do I sincerely follow instructions\r\nor do I deliberately fall out of order because I feel I understand better? Do I have disciplers\r\nand mentors who are guiding me or have I allowed the “flows” and trends of time to\r\ndetermine my taste and shift my approach to the work of God? Have I changed the scope of\r\nthe vision because I think there are more modern ways to do it? How do I respond to the cries\r\nof the old when they genuinely express a concern?', '2018-11-02 14:51:19'),
(22, 53, 'As the old who saw the past, how sensitive am I to relate with the young ones in the vision?\r\nDo I make all efforts to carry them along, ensuring that they are fully matured in the\r\nunderstanding of the vision? Do I expect more than I am giving to them? Am I becoming too\r\ncritical or unrealistic? Am I an encourager or a source of frustration? Am I willing to help,\r\nguide and mentor the younger generation? Am I willing to show them the ropes of true\r\nrevival and the path of true discipleship? Am I a shoulder to stand on for the next generation\r\nto see further and farther?', '2018-11-02 14:51:19'),
(23, 54, 'Is there a way I have mixed my faith with certain strange practices? Am I already a victim of\r\ndoctrinal errors? Are there certain influences that are compromising my dedication to God?\r\nAre there places I go that brethren must not know? Are there messages I listen to that I will be\r\nashamed to be seen with? Have I been shifted away by the growing erroneous doctrines of\r\nthe last days? Is my heart desirous of some modern day excesses that we see today in many\r\nchurches? Have I been misled and am now actually living in some form of confusion on\r\ncertain truths of the Bible?<br/>\r\nCan Jesus trust me to stand for Him? Do I find it difficult to say NO when friends are pushing\r\nme on a wrong path? Do I find it difficult to say NO when errors are being committed in my\r\npresence? Do I find it difficult to say NO when my flesh and self are pushing me to do things I\r\nhave consecrated not to do? Are there practices in my local churches that contradict the Bible\r\nthat I still submit to?', '2018-11-02 15:04:15'),
(24, 56, 'Do I really feel under pressure in my spiritual walk? Do I feel frustrated and discouraged in my\r\njourney in life? Does every smile I pretend to give deepen the hurt of rejection that I am going\r\nthrough on the inside? Do I feel stressed and strained in my Christian walk? Do I feel I am\r\ncarrying a load that is heavier than I? Do I feel lonely and abandoned in the journey of life?\r\nWhat is discouraging me from building my life for God? Am I already giving in under pressure\r\nto compromise? Who should I fear more—God or man? Is the fear of my friend leading me to\r\nsin or the fear of losing my engaged partner shifting my consecration to consider pre-marital\r\nsex? Is the fear of losing my job forcing me to succumb to lies and hidden sins?\r\nAre there people who I have exalted more than God in my life? Are there people whose\r\npromises are heavier in my heart than the promises of God? Are there people who have\r\nstabbed me and left me in the cold of the night after many promises? Do I carry the pain from\r\nclose friends, spiritual parents or intimate family members? Is my heart still bleeding many\r\nyears after these individuals disappointed me?', '2018-12-03 19:06:20'),
(25, 57, 'Am I still living in the shadow of the fear of my past? Do I feel that there are certain truths\r\nabout my past that I have not fully addressed? Are there carry-over issues that can threaten\r\nmy future that I must face by the wisdom of God? Are there secret sins that I have indulged in\r\nthat can come back to attack me in the future? Are there things that I stole that I am still\r\nenjoying the benefits of today as a believer?', '2018-12-03 19:17:02'),
(26, 57, 'Does my past discourage me from going further with God? Is my past life hunting me? Do I\r\nfeel unworthy or unqualified by reasons of the life I have lived before giving my life to Jesus?\r\nDo I feel guilty with a sense of not being sure that Christ has forgiven me? Do I feel challenged\r\nto go out to preach because many people around me know my past misdeeds? Do I feel\r\ndiscouraged to face the mistakes of the past?', '2018-12-03 19:17:02'),
(27, 57, 'Are there issues of the past that I know I must settle today that I am still hiding from?', '2018-12-03 19:17:02'),
(28, 59, 'Have I put the work of God on hold in my local fellowship? Have I shut down my heart from\r\nthe work of God even though I am physically present but spiritually absent? Am I now\r\npursuing my own earthly goals? Do I take my life goals more seriously than the kingdom\r\nassignments? Do I consider my life aspirations more important than kingdom assignments?\r\nWhere do I put my financial resources today—on self or on the kingdom need?', '2018-12-03 19:32:40'),
(29, 59, 'How do I use my time on a day-to-day basis? Are my daily activities in agreement with God\'s\r\nprogramme for my life? Do I waste too much time on unnecessary things, when I could have\r\nused the time to sharpen myself spiritually or engage in something beneficial?', '2018-12-03 19:32:40'),
(30, 59, 'Am I responding positively to the call to revival? Am I ready to do God\'s work or am I pursuing\r\nmy own agenda? Am I doing the work as the Lord instructed or am I doing it to please man?', '2018-12-03 19:32:40'),
(31, 59, 'Have I heard the instructions of the Lord lately? Is the Lord speaking to me through his word\r\non a regular basis? Is my heart now so hardened that I cannot hear the piercing correction of\r\nthe spirit?<br/>\r\nDo I have a prophetic connection to the leadership of the vision for guidance and correction?', '2018-12-03 19:32:40'),
(32, 60, 'In what ways have I allowed challenges to halt the work that I am supposed to be doing for\r\nChrist? Am I consistent in my commitment to the assignment that the Lord has given unto\r\nme? Do I have any sense of determination or amI weakened by little challenges? Can I stand\r\nmy ground in the midst of oppositions? Can I bear the ridicule of delays and disappointment\r\nin my service unto the Lord?', '2018-12-03 19:47:28'),
(33, 60, 'Do I feel God will not come through for me? Is my faith failing in the wilderness of life? I am\r\nlosing momentum because of the pressures around me? Am I backsliding in my heart\r\nbecause I am afraid things may go wrong if I remain with Christ? Am I already challenging God\r\nin my heart because my faithfulness is not translating to my needed miracles? Is my\r\ndetermination waning and abating with time?', '2018-12-03 19:47:28'),
(34, 61, 'Have I mixed myself with uncleanness? Have I truly separated myself from the world—its\r\ntastes, its music, its affections and lifestyle? Have I genuinely left all on the altar for the Lord?\r\nIs my life a living sacrifice or dead ash on the altar?<br/>\r\nAm I a Christian that serves both God and mammon? Am I a Christian who is possessed by\r\nthe love of money? Do I place physical blessing more than a spiritual relationship with Jesus?<br/>\r\nDo I serve Jesus for what I will get or for what I will give? What other things do I need to\r\nabstain from inlife to be a temple of His dwelling? How am I preparing for the Second Coming\r\nof Jesus Christ?', '2018-12-03 19:59:17'),
(35, 63, 'What is the place of the word of God in my life? To what extent does revelation in the word of\r\nGod guide my life and decisions? Is my heart set to seek the Word of God? Am I a doer of the\r\nWord, or only just a hearer?When was the last time I did an extensive study of the word\r\noutside the normal church or fellowship study? How do I value the word of God in my\r\nspiritual journey?', '2018-12-03 20:10:33'),
(36, 63, 'Does the word of God prick me when I read it? Has the word of God become more or less a\r\nstory book when I read it? Does the word of God give me inspiration and encouragement? Do\r\nI read the word of God because I want to preach? Do I read the word of God because I want to\r\nhear God?', '2018-12-03 20:10:33'),
(37, 63, 'Do I teach others what God is teaching me? Am I willing to be God\'s next agent of revival, and\r\nhave I sincerely answered His call by responding with “Here am I, send me”?', '2018-12-03 20:10:33'),
(38, 64, 'Am I living my life as a lone ranger trying to do the work of God my own way? Am I a faithful\r\nand able vessel that God can trust to be a revival agent unto others? Can my life attract other\r\npeople to Jesus or actually turn them away? Which of my colleagues or family members have\r\nbeen drawn to Jesus through the result that they can see in my life? Is my life a magnet of\r\nsalvation or a distraction?<br/>\r\nHas a personal revival begun within me as an individual? Am I willing to be a fisher of men?<br/>\r\nAm I willing to go all out and recruit more souls for Jesus? Am I doing the work of God alone\r\nand not making an effort to invest in more men with better skills than I? Am I always\r\nthreatened when I see people with better skills than myself? Do I withdraw from any\r\nopportunity to work with other brethren because I am always apprehensive of others?', '2018-12-03 21:06:59'),
(39, 64, 'What can the members of my local fellowship and I do to start a local outreach that will bring\r\npeople into a unique move of God in our local church?', '2018-12-03 21:06:59'),
(40, 65, 'Do I genuinely prepare for every task that I have to do for the Lord? Have I been faithful in my\r\nacts of fasting? Do I always break my fast earlier than I had initially planned? Is my fasting\r\nconsistent or do I only fast when I think I have a problem? Do I participate in TACEF Tuesday\r\nfasting? Am I consistent in the monthly covenant fasting? Have I ever dedicated a fast to pray\r\nfor the vision of revival or do I only fast when I need something from God?', '2018-12-03 21:24:01'),
(41, 65, 'Am I aware that sin can hinder the positive response and power of God from being released\r\nin fasting? Is my fasting more about the length of days involved or more about sincerity and\r\nhumble seeking of God\'s Presence?', '2018-12-03 21:24:01'),
(42, 65, 'Do I really practice what I preach when it comes to trusting God? Do I preach God\'s provision\r\nwhen I indulge in seeking the help of men? Do I proclaim divine provision when I spend time\r\nmoving from one member\'s house to another to beg for money for God\'s work?', '2018-12-03 21:24:01'),
(43, 67, 'Am I genuinely separated from the world? Do I love the Lord or is my heart in the things of the\r\nworld? Is my choice, taste and preference completely separated from the world? Am I living a\r\ntrue or fake Christian life that changes by situation and location? Does my digital footprint and\r\nsocial media chat agree with the image that people know of me? Am I in any way unequally\r\nyoked with unbelievers? Am I already walking in the deception of joining myself to someone\r\nthat I am not sure of their salvation as my future husband or wife? Am I being deceived by the\r\npressure of friends that I can change the person? Am I selling myself cheaply because I am not\r\nsure of what will become of my future? Am I under pressure that time is gone and I have to go\r\nwith anyone around even if they are not genuinely born again?', '2018-12-03 21:37:49'),
(44, 67, 'Do I feel the weight of sin of dying souls in a manner that provoke me unto heartfelt\r\nintercession? Do I feel any pain when I hear that a fellow brother or sister has fallen into sin?\r\nDoes any burden of prayer come on me when I hear that someone has fallen into sin or a\r\nsinner has died? Do I feel any remorse for the people of this world because of their sins\r\nwhich I know will bring God\'s judgement sooner or later? Or could I care less about them?<br/>\r\nDo I pray for souls borne out of deep burden of heart or because I am forced into a prayer\r\nmeeting?', '2018-12-03 21:37:49'),
(45, 68, 'Am I living in secret sin that I have not confessed to the Lord? Is my conscience pure before\r\nGod and man or do I still live with guilt of certain things in my heart? Have I made a\r\ncommitment to the Lord to do what is right? Have I taken practical action in correcting the\r\nwrongs I have done in the past? Am I making excuses that my past wrongs are too\r\nembarrassing and I can\'t go through the humiliation? Is true freedom found in burying my\r\nguilt deep down in my heart, or will it be experienced by confession and restitution? Am I\r\nhiding my past life from my spouse as a married brother or sister?<br/>\r\nDoes my ministry lead to genuine conviction of sin? Is my ministry backed with results of the\r\nrepentance of sin? Has my ministry as a preacher, singer or worker weakened over time to a\r\npoint of being an entertainer and not a minister of transformation? Have I experienced what\r\nI preach? Do I feel the weight of the message that I preach or do I just preach as a routine? Am\r\nI a minister of genuine repentance and true salvation or I am just working for God with no\r\nsense of impact?', '2018-12-03 21:49:50'),
(46, 69, 'Am I serving God as a routine or do I carry a sense of burden in my heart which feels the\r\nweight of the expectation of God for the souls of men? Do I think I feel what God is feeling on\r\nan issue per time, especially on the issues of dying souls? Am I a life that is spiritual but has no\r\nwall in critical areas that bring honour and value? Do I think that my spirituality is evident in\r\nother parts of my life? Is my ability to pray 5 hours non-stop translating into other areas of my\r\nlife as an excellent worker/student, excellent father or mother or child, responsible family\r\nman, financially stable person, socially impactful neighbour or worker etc. Does my\r\nspirituality complement my work impact or does my work have nothing to show forth to\r\nbring glory to God?', '2018-12-03 22:02:26'),
(47, 69, 'Do I strike a balance between my spiritual calling and secular demand? Do I always have\r\nexcuses for why my work is preventing my spiritual fulfilment or why my spirituality is\r\nreducing the time I have for my work? Does the quality of my work and attitude towards my\r\nwork encouragement to want to know more about Jesus in my life or push them away? Have I\r\nlearnt how best to strike a perfect balance between my secular job and my spiritual\r\nassignment?', '2018-12-03 22:02:26'),
(48, 71, 'Can the Lord drink from my hand without being poisoned by my life of fornication, corruption\r\nand deceit? Do I know the taste of the King of kings and does what I bring to him not be a\r\npoison? Am I a risk-taker for the kingdom? Can I lay down my reputation, career, savings and\r\nfuture for the cause of eternity? Am I willing to lay down my life for His sake if the need arises?\r\nDo I count my life more dear to me than the cause of Christ?', '2018-12-04 07:13:04'),
(49, 71, 'Do I have what it takes to stand in the best places of the earth to represent Jesus? Can my life\r\ncommand the attention of the kings of the earth? Have I been building sufficient and\r\nrequisite skills, knowledge and exposure to match the best places that God can take me in\r\nlife? Am I consciously learning and adding to my certificates or am I just making excuses that\r\nthings are not working out? How recent wasmy last certificate? When was the last time I\r\nlearnt life skills (driving, etiquette, public speaking, social engagement, dressing, writing,\r\ngrammatical rightness etc.). How am I educating myself now, so that I can be of greater use to\r\nthe Master in time to come?\r\nthe Master in time to come?', '2018-12-04 07:13:04'),
(50, 72, 'Am I leader whose life inspires people to deliver on a task or am I just carrying a title as an\r\nexecutive with no impact? Does my leadership style motivate people to become more or\r\ndoes my life weary and reduce their drive and aspiration? Do I have a clear sense of vision for\r\nthe task given to me or am I just leading people without clarity and direction? Do I fully\r\nunderstand the vision of TACEF to raise an army with a vision of revival and am I working in it\r\nor am I serving man\'s agenda?', '2018-12-04 07:23:54'),
(51, 72, 'Do I prepare well for every assignment given to me to do or I just walk into it with past\r\nexperience? Do I take time to pray, fast and reflect before I undertake spiritual and even life\r\ntasks? Do I thoroughly think through and plan before acting on any demand placed on me? Do I\r\nevaluate, reflect and identify a delivery path before I do things or do I just decide on impulse?\r\nDo I devote huge portions of my time to prayer, fasting, study, and meditation in His word to\r\nseek clarity one very task of revival in my local church, campus and community?', '2018-12-04 07:23:54'),
(52, 73, 'Is the vision of revival clear to me? Can the vision drive me to take bold steps like Nehemiah\r\nor I am not sure of what the vision is? Do I have a clear picture of the future for my life, career,\r\nhome, marriage, ministry or future? Do I live my life anyhow it comes with no sense of God inspired\r\ndestination?', '2018-12-04 13:04:22'),
(53, 73, 'Am I a good communicator? Does my word provoke positive actions or leave people more\r\nconcerned and demoralised? Do I speak in the language of possibilities or am I laden with the\r\ntonality of caution? Do I inspire or demoralise people? Do I know how to articulate thoughts?\r\nHave I learnt the discipline of communicating as a spouse, parent, worker, colleague, leader,\r\nfollower etc.', '2018-12-04 13:04:22'),
(54, 73, 'Do I feel my life is enjoying God\'s favour or does there seem to be a block somewhere? Does\r\nmy life command the favour of people around me? Do I live a life that can genuinely provoke\r\nfavour with man or does my life push people away from me?', '2018-12-04 13:04:22'),
(55, 75, 'Am I someone God can trust with instructions? Do I speak before God instructs? Do I like to\r\nimpress with revelation or prophetic insights that God has given me? Do I use my gift of\r\ndiscernment to intimidate or come across as more spiritual than others? Do I know how to\r\nbe silent before the Lord? Do I understand the principles of God-led moments? When I say,\r\n“thus saith the Lord”, am I sure that indeed it is the Lord that has asked me to speak?\r\nHow do I plan for the tasks given to me? Am I a person who pays attention to detail or do I\r\nalways see gaps only after I have started a project and say, “I wish I did this or that” or “If only\r\nI had known”? Do I always forget important things when it matters most because I fail to\r\nspend time thinking about how best to do a task? Do I apply my mind consciously on how\r\nbest to improve every assignment given to me? When was the last time I did an evaluation of\r\nmyself, career, financial spending, ministry, health, past programme in my\r\nunit/fellowship/zone/subgroup etc. with an intent to evaluate areas of improvement, things\r\nto stop or do better? Have I taken time to take an honest look at the broken walls in my\r\npersonal life and service to the Lord?', '2018-12-04 13:17:32'),
(56, 76, 'Am I someone who finds it very easy and exciting to work with others or do I like to work\r\nalone? Do I find it difficult to work in a team? Do I always feel easily offended when I work in a\r\nteam? Do I always strive to keep the unity of the spirit when I have shared responsibility? Do I\r\nalways go the extra mile to feel responsible and accountable to the specific role given to me?\r\nDo I like to be a Jack-of-all-trades, assuming every role without nothing to show? Do I always\r\ntrust people with roles or do I just give up easily on them?<br/>\r\nCan I be trusted to do what is given to me? Do I always strive to improve myself so as not to\r\ndisappoint the trust shown in me through delegation? Have I betrayed the trust of delegation\r\nthrough my reckless inefficiency and acts of laziness? Do I feel remorseful each time I\r\ndisappoint expectation and do I make an effort to correct and improve? Am I always afraid of\r\nfailure when a role is delegated to me? Do I always feel I cannot do it? Do I feel less capable\r\nbased on some things that have happened in the past or what people have said to me? Do I\r\nfeel others are better than me?', '2018-12-04 13:37:12'),
(57, 77, 'Have I given in to the threat of the world? Do I feel like I have failed in the game of life? Do I\r\nfeel so ridiculed by being a Christian that I have backslide in my heart? Has the pressure of\r\nwhat my friends would say pushed me to compromise my position in Christ? Have I yielded to\r\nthe fear of the enemy? Has the fear of what will become of my future forced me to do things\r\nthat will not give glory to God? Has the fear of unemployment forced me to change my age or\r\nthe fear of how to meet up with life demands forced me to cut corners?', '2018-12-04 13:49:45'),
(58, 77, 'Is the devil weakening my hand and hindering my progress in the work of the Lord? Have I\r\nallowed others to intimidate me, or discourage me in any way? Have I allowed negative\r\nwords spoken against me to block my heart with roots of bitterness, which are cutting me off\r\nfrom the joy of the Lord?', '2018-12-04 13:49:45'),
(59, 77, 'Do I feel that my spiritual life is balanced? Am I perfectly combining my spiritual demands\r\nwith secular pressures? Am I able to manage time in ways that ensure fulfilling spiritual\r\nexperience coupled with outstanding life results?', '2018-12-04 13:49:45'),
(60, 79, 'Can I discern between the voice of God and the voice of men? Can I discern when I am on\r\nGod\'s path and when I am walking on my own path? Do I hear God clearly or I am just\r\npretending? Am I sure the spirit of the Lord is guiding my life decisions—my current career,\r\nmarital choice, investment decision, relocation, ministry pursuit etc.?', '2018-12-04 19:24:52'),
(61, 79, 'Do I have discernment from God to tell the difference between an enemy who is pretending\r\nto be a friend? Do I always give in to fear and doubt? Am I always intimidated by threats to\r\nthe extent of running away from the work of God or the purpose of God for my life?', '2018-12-04 19:24:52'),
(62, 79, 'Has a fake prophet deceived me? Has a so-called man of God made me do something\r\nunbiblical at any time? Have I yielded to pressure to act outside the word of God in the name\r\nof obeying a “thus saith the Lord” in my marriage, parenting, career, health, finances,\r\nspiritual etc.', '2018-12-04 19:24:52'),
(63, 79, 'Am I a finisher or just a starter? Do I always complete what I start? Do I always like to put my\r\nhands in so many things with no statement of completion? Do I respond to gaps when I see it\r\nor do I run away? Do I act when I see a problem or do I move on with no action?', '2018-12-04 19:24:52'),
(64, 81, 'What areas of my life have I left open and vulnerable to potential attack from the enemy? Is\r\nmy spiritual life strong through prayer, fasting, Bible study, praise and worship? Am I\r\nwatching the gates of my life and that of my physical and spiritual children? Am I awake or\r\nasleep in watching over destinies that are in my care? Am I always spiritually alert or is the\r\ncomfort of success already weakening my spiritual altar? Am I getting too busy to pray\r\nbecause of work pressures, academic demand and marital responsibilities? Am I\r\nwithdrawing from the fellowship because there is a feeling of higher status? Are you cutting\r\noff from revival consecration because of modernity and exposure?', '2018-12-04 19:37:39'),
(65, 81, 'Am I consciously investing in the next generation? How serious do I take the children church\r\nas a platform for raising giants for the Lord? How deliberate do I mentor and disciple those\r\nunder my watch to grow stronger and better in service for the Lord? As a growing Christian,\r\nam I preparing myself as much as possible to carry the torch of revival from those who did it\r\nbefore me? As an older Christian, am I strengthening and preparing members of the next\r\ngeneration who will continue the work that God has been doing through me?', '2018-12-04 19:37:39'),
(66, 82, 'Do I minister from my head or from the heart of grace? Do I prepare for every opportunity to\r\nspeak the word of God or do I just take it for granted that it will just flow? Do I come from the\r\nplace of prayer to undertake divine assignment? Do I pray through every divine task given to\r\nme?', '2018-12-04 19:47:33'),
(67, 82, 'Does my ministry produce the desired result? Does the delivery of the word through me\r\nproduce the result of genuine repentance and consecration? Does the word of God in my\r\nmouth hit targets in the hearts of men or does it miss the target altogether? Am I a preacher\r\nor a storyteller? Am I ministering in song or a song entertainer? Does my drama ministry\r\nproduce a result or is it merely laughed off?', '2018-12-04 19:47:33'),
(68, 82, 'Does the ministry carry the weight of understanding? Do people understand the core\r\nessence of my message? Do I carry people through a journey of impact from beginning to the\r\nend or is it just a flashy show that goes nowhere? Do people get more confused about my\r\nmessage or do they get more convinced of sin and need for righteousness?', '2018-12-04 19:47:33'),
(69, 83, 'Am I praying for the revival of my community? When was the last time I prayed and fasted for\r\ngenuine move of God in my country? Am I birthing the kingdom in the place of deep\r\nintercession or I am in shackles of selfish prayers? Do I have burden for my society? Do I\r\nbelieve things can get better? What practical steps am I taking to activate God\'s consciousness\r\nin the nation?', '2018-12-04 19:56:23'),
(70, 83, 'Can God trust me to bring revival into nations? Can my knees be strong in prayer so that my\r\nfeet can transverse nations for the Lord? Can the Lord use me to build altar of revivals in the\r\nnations of the earth? Can my life activate seasons of repentance, conviction and national\r\nreformation?', '2018-12-04 19:56:23');
(71, 85, 'What sort of relationship do I have with God? Is God a tool that I use when I have a problem or the eternal Father that my heart longs after with fear and true love? Am I in regular fellowship with the Father and His Son Jesus Christ? Do I listen when He speaks to me? Am I being led by His Spirit in my day-to-day life? Do I stand on God’s Word even in this day and age of deception, delusion, and a self-centred world? Are there any false gods which I have made first in my heart and life, while relegating the Creator, God Almighty to second place? Am I really serving God for what I will get or  because I want to genuinely know Him?', '2019-10-31 13:56:23');
(72, 86, 'How close am I to God? Am I an intimate Christian with God or a truant who comes today and faraway next day? Am I the kind that practices outward religion but has never had an encounter with the risen Christ? Am I really born again, and has my heart been regenerated by the Holy Spirit? Am I sure if I die today, I will meet God in heaven? Are my life’s pursuits more important to me than making time to get to know who God is? Am I seeking for more of God? Am I making efforts to be closer to God and to find out deeper things about the infinite God, or am I content with where I am?', '2019-10-31 13:57:23');
(73, 87, 'What is the quality of my prayer life and communion with God? Do I have genuine hunger and thirst for the word of God and prayer? I am always bored when it is time to pray or doze off when it is time to read my Bible. Do I take my quiet time with God very serious? ', '2019-10-31 13:58:23');
(74, 87, 'How do I go about studying the Scripture? Do I allow God’s Spirit to guide me or do I lean on my own understanding ? Am I walking in the accuracy of the word of God or have I unknowingly believed a false doctrine?  Am I applying what God teaches me to my daily practical life?', '2019-10-31 13:59:23');
(75, 88, 'Do I know who I am or I have allowed the world to define me? Am I trying to be like another person, comparing myself to others and trying to become who I am not? Do I know my right and authority in Christ and do I exercise this everyday? Am I so fearful of the devil that I forget that I have already been made an overcomer through Christ? Do I allow circumstances to define my identity or do I hold fast the truth of what God says about me?  Have I accepted defeat or will I rise up and use Jesus’ Name in authority to overcome the opposition? ', '2019-10-31 14:00:23');
(76, 90, 'Am I really born again? Has the impact of salvation really led me to a change of heart and a complete turnaround? Am I a pretender like Simon, who went through a process but was never genuinely born again? ', '2019-10-31 14:01:23');
(77, 90, 'Do I realise what exactly it is that Jesus saved me from? Do I realise the gravity of His sacrifice, and the pain He willingly endured to redeem me from the consequences of sin? Am I aware that I could just as easily have been one of those who end up in hell if not for God’s grace and mercy? Am I living a life to justify this kindness that God has shown me?', '2019-10-31 14:02:23');
(78, 91, 'Do I live in pure conscience towards God and man? Do I feel there are certain things I need to correct now? Are there things I enjoy today that I stole when in the world? Are there people I owe that I have refused to pay? What other wrongs (e.g. lying about someone) am I able to correct? Have I “rationalised” to myself that it has been so long ago that the person would not care anymore? Is God pleased if I just sweep the matter under the rug? Are there things that my spouse must know now? Are there things I must tell my parents about now? Are there things foundation of errors in my education and career that may cause a shipwreck of the future? Are the foundations of errors and deception in my ministry that I must settle now?', '2019-10-31 14:03:23');
(79, 92, 'Am I truly and genuinely a child of God? Do I understand my authority in Christ Jesus? Am I living a life worthy of divine investment of power? Can my prayer and Bible study life command respect in the camp of the enemy? Can I decree a thing and it shall be established? Do I have faith that can command situations and move mountains? Am I studying the word of God enough for me to understand my authority in Christ Jesus? Am I living in fear of tomorrow or fear of some unknown enemies somewhere? Am I walking in wrong mindset that defeats who I am in Christ Jesus? ', '2019-10-31 14:04:23');
(80, 93, 'Am I genuinely seeking the will of God in my life? Do I have my own plans outside God? Am I already obeying His written will in the Bible? Can I honestly say that the Lord is guiding every decision of my life? Am I following the crowd or following the leading of the Lord? Can I hear God accurately? Do I understand the gifts and talent that the Lord has given me and how He wants to use them for His own glory? ', '2019-10-31 14:05:23');
(81, 95, 'Have I cultivated the act of hearing God? Can I say that I know how God speaks to me? What I differentiate between my voice, devil’s voice and God’s voice? Am I willing to spend as much time as necessary alone in God’s presence, waiting on Him to give me a word? Am I willing to cut off ungodly music, which contaminates the mind and compromises my inward purity? Am I guilty of resorting to questionable mediums when I do not hear from God? Am I an emergency seeker or a daily sheep who is walking with the great shepherd?', '2019-10-31 14:05:23');
(82, 96, 'Am I a disciple? Am I a born again Christian? Do l have what it takes to be a true disciple? Can I endure discipleship training? Am I ready to learn from Jesus? Am l submissive enough to learn at His feet? Can I bear the yoke? Am I bearing the cross already? Am l prepared to be crucified? Am l really willing to give up what the world has for me? Am I willing to give up the world's value, entertainment and esteem?', '2019-10-31 14:05:23');
(83, 97, 'Have I personally become a disciple yet or I'm still one of the mixed multitude? Do I mistake conversion for discipleship and think my experience of salvation is tantamount to a discipleship relationship with the Lord Jesus? Is there any evidence of growth in my life or am still a baby who only feeds on milk while I assume that I'm already mature for solid food?', '2019-10-31 14:06:23');
(84, 98, 'Is the great investment of God to have connected me with some disciplers not ending in colossal loss as my life does not bring profit but loss to my maker? Can I point to a particular life I have correctly discipled since I became a disciple myself or do I just remain a fruitless tree without any flower let alone a trace of fruits?', '2019-10-31 14:07:23');
(85, 99, 'Have I truly been to Calvary? Have I laid all down on the altar of sacrifice? Is there anything too difficult for me to let go for the sake of Christ? Have I been completely and totally sold out for Christ or is there a part of me that is still left out? Am I completely immersed in this vision of revival or am I doing part time or eye service? Am I a good ambassador of Christ in my office or am I misrepresenting God in my career path? Have I overcome the power of the flesh in my walk with God? ', '2019-10-31 14:08:23');
(86, 100, 'Are you walking in the Spirit or in the flesh? Do you still enjoy the hangover of sinful desires and habits? Do you normally get bored when praying alone? Is worshipping God a burden for you when alone but exciting when in Church? When last did you obey the prompting of the Spirit of God? Is there a major decision you need to make now to start a fresh walk in the Spirit? Are you taking care of your physical body while you also walk in the spirit?', '2019-10-31 14:08:23');
INSERT INTO `study` (`study-id`, `week-title`, `study-title`, `study-text`, `bible-text`, `weeks`, `year`, `start-date`, `date`) VALUES
(1, 'Week 1: 10 – 16 September 2017', 'Divine Placement For Reasonable Service: Young Timothy In Ephesus', '1 Tim. 1:1–3', 'Paul, an apostle of Jesus Christ by the commandment of God our Saviour, and Lord Jesus Christ, which is our hope; 2 Unto Timothy, my own son in the faith: Grace, mercy, and peace, from God our Father and Jesus Christ our Lord. 3 As I besought thee to abide still at Ephesus, when I went into Macedonia, that thou mightest charge some that they teach no other doctrine,', 1, 2017, '2017-09-10', '2018-02-15 09:21:54'),
(2, 'Week 2: 17–23 September 2017', 'Unreasonable Teachings and Distractions', '1 Tim. 1:3–7', '3 As I besought thee to abide still at Ephesus, when I went into Macedonia, that thou mightest charge some that they teach no other doctrine, 4 Neither give heed to fables and endless genealogies, which minister questions, rather than godly edifying which is in faith: so do. 5 Now the end of the commandment is charity out of a pure heart, and of a good conscience, and of faith unfeigned: 6 From which some having swerved have turned aside unto vain jangling; 7 Desiring to be teachers of the law; understanding neither what they say, nor whereof they affirm.', 1, 2017, '2017-09-17', '2018-02-15 09:25:05'),
(3, 'Week 3: 24–30 September 2017', 'Law and Sound Doctrine', '1 Tim. 1:8–11', '8 But we know that the law is good, if a man use it lawfully; 9 Knowing this, that the law is not made for a righteous man, but for the lawless and disobedient, for the ungodly and for sinners, for unholy and profane, for murderers of fathers and murderers of mothers, for manslayers, 10 For whoremongers, for them that defile themselves with mankind, for menstealers, for liars, for perjured persons, and if there be any other thing that is contrary to sound doctrine; 11 According to the glorious gospel of the blessed God, which was committed to my trust.', 1, 2017, '2017-09-24', '2018-02-15 09:25:05'),
(4, 'Week 4: 1–7 October 2017', 'Transforming grace and reasonable appreciation of the gift of salvation', '1 Tim. 1:12–17', '12 And I thank Christ Jesus our Lord, who hath enabled me, for that he counted me faithful, putting me into the ministry; 13 Who was before a blasphemer, and a persecutor, and injurious: but I obtained mercy, because I did it ignorantly in unbelief. 14 And the grace of our Lord was exceeding abundant with faith and love which is in Christ Jesus. 15 This is a faithful saying, and worthy of all acceptation, that Christ Jesus came into the world to save sinners; of whom I am chief. 16 Howbeit for this cause I obtained mercy, that in me first Jesus Christ might shew forth all longsuffering, for a pattern to them which should hereafter believe on him to life everlasting. 17 Now unto the King eternal, immortal, invisible, the only wise God, be honour and glory for ever and ever. Amen.', 1, 2017, '2017-10-01', '2018-02-15 09:27:27'),
(5, 'Week 5: 8–14 October 2017', 'The role of prophecy and faith in ministerial warfare', '1 Tim. 1:18–20', '18 This charge I commit unto thee, son Timothy, according to the prophecies which went before on thee, that thou by them mightest war a good warfare; 19 Holding faith and a good conscience; which some having put away, concerning faith have made shipwreck: 20 Of whom is Hymenaeus and Alexander; whom I have delivered unto Satan, that they may learn not to blaspheme.', 1, 2017, '2017-10-08', '2018-02-15 09:30:05'),
(6, 'Week 6: 15–21 October 2017', 'Biblical and reasonable prayer practice', '1 Tim. 2:1–8', 'I exhort therefore, that, first of all, supplications, prayers, intercessions, and giving of thanks, be made for all men; 2 For kings, and for all that are in authority; that we may lead a quiet and peaceable life in all godliness and honesty. 3 For this is good and acceptable in the sight of God our Saviour; 4 Who will have all men to be saved, and to come unto the knowledge of the truth. 5 For there is one God, and one mediator between God and men, the man Christ Jesus; 6 Who gave himself a ransom for all, to be testified in due time. 7 Whereunto I am ordained a preacher, and an apostle, (I speak the truth in Christ, and lie not;) a teacher of the Gentiles in faith and verity. 8 I will therefore that men pray every where, lifting up holy hands, without wrath and doubting.', 1, 2017, '2017-10-15', '2018-02-15 09:30:05'),
(7, 'Week 7: 22–28 October 2017', 'Understanding gender roles in the house of God', '1 Tim. 2:8–15', '8 I will therefore that men pray everywhere, lifting up holy hands, without wrath and doubting 9 In like manner also, that women adorn themselves in modest apparel, with shamefacedness and sobriety; not with braided hair, or gold, or pearls, or costly array; 10 But (which becometh women professing godliness) with good works. 11 Let the woman learn in silence with all subjection. 12 But I suffer not a woman to teach, nor to usurp authority over the man, but to be in silence. 13 For Adam was first formed, then Eve. 14 And Adam was not deceived, but the woman being deceived was in the transgression. 15 Notwithstanding she shall be saved in childbearing, if they continue in faith and charity and holiness with sobriety.', 1, 2017, '2017-10-22', '2018-02-15 09:46:25'),
(8, 'Week 8: 29 October–4 November 2017', '“Qualities of reasonable leadership and service”', '1 Tim. 3:1–13', 'This is a true saying, if a man desire the office of a bishop, he desireth a good work. 2 A bishop then must be blameless, the husband of one wife, vigilant, sober, of good behaviour, given to hospitality, apt to teach; 3 Not given to wine, no striker, not greedy of filthy lucre; but patient, not a brawler, not covetous; 4 One that ruleth well his own house, having his children in subjection with all gravity; 5 (For if a man know not how to rule his own house, how shall he take care of the church of God?) 6 Not a novice, lest being lifted up with pride he fall into the condemnation of the devil. 7 Moreover he must have a good report of them which are without; lest he fall into reproach and the snare of the devil. 8 Likewise must the deacons be grave, not double-tongued, not given to much wine, not greedy of filthy lucre; 9 Holding the mystery of the faith in a pure conscience. 10 And let these also first be proved; then let them use the office of a deacon, being found blameless. 11 Even so must their wives be grave, not slanderers, sober, faithful in all things. 12 Let the deacons be the husbands of one wife, ruling their children and their own houses well. 13 For they that have used the office of a deacon well purchase to themselves a good degree, and great boldness in the faith which is in Christ Jesus.', 1, 2017, '2017-10-29', '2018-02-15 09:46:25'),
(9, 'Week 9: 5–11 November 2017', 'Godliness and reasonable conduct in the house of Christ', '1 Tim. 3:14–16', '14 These things write I unto thee, hoping to come unto thee shortly: 15 But if I tarry long, that thou mayest know how thou oughtest to behave thyself in the house of God, which is the church of the living God, the pillar and ground of the truth. 16 And without controversy great is the mystery of godliness: God was manifest in the flesh, justified in the Spirit, seen of angels, preached unto the Gentiles, believed on in the world, received up into glory.', 1, 2017, '2017-11-05', '2018-02-15 09:46:25'),
(10, 'Week 10: 12–18 November 2017', 'Maintaining God’s truth in the midst of end-time apostasy', '1 Tim. 4:1–5', 'Now the Spirit speaketh expressly, that in the latter times some shall depart from the faith, giving heed to seducing spirits, and doctrines of devils; 2 Speaking lies in hypocrisy; having their conscience seared with a hot iron; 3 Forbidding to marry, and commanding to abstain from meats, which God hath created to be received with thanksgiving of them which believe and know the truth. 4 For every creature of God is good, and nothing to be refused, if it be received with thanksgiving: 5 For it is sanctified by the word of God and prayer.', 1, 2017, '2017-11-12', '2018-02-15 09:46:25'),
(11, 'Week 11: 19–25 November 2017', 'The exercise of Godliness', '1 Tim. 4:6–10', '6 If thou put the brethren in remembrance of these things, thou shalt be a good minister of Jesus Christ, nourished up in the words of faith and of good doctrine, whereunto thou hast attained. 7 But refuse profane and old wives\' fables, and exercise thyself rather unto godliness. 8 For bodily exercise profiteth little: but godliness is profitable unto all things, having promise of the life that now is, and of that which is to come. 9 This is a faithful saying and worthy of all acceptation. 10 For therefore we both labour and suffer reproach, because we trust in the living God, who is the Saviour of all men, especially of those that believe.', 1, 2017, '2017-11-19', '2018-02-15 09:46:25'),
(12, 'Week 12 & 13: 26 November–9 December 2017', 'An example of the believers: Upholding God’s standard ', ' 1 Tim. 4:11–16', '11 These things command and teach. 12 Let no man despise thy youth; but be thou an example of the believers, in word, in conversation, in charity, in spirit, in faith, in purity. 13 Till I come, give attendance to reading, to exhortation, to doctrine. 14 Neglect not the gift that is in thee, which was given thee by prophecy, with the laying on of the hands of the presbytery. 15 Meditate upon these things; give thyself wholly to them; that thy profiting may appear to all. 16 Take heed unto thyself, and unto the doctrine; continue in them: for in doing this thou shalt both save thyself, and them that hear thee.', 2, 2017, '2017-11-26', '2018-02-15 09:46:25'),
(13, 'Week 14: 10–16 December 2017', 'Reasonable model of correction and relationship management', '1 Tim. 5:1–2', 'Rebuke not an elder, but entreat him as a father; and the younger men as brethren; 2 The elder women as mothers; the younger as sisters, with all purity.', 1, 2017, '2017-12-10', '2018-02-15 09:54:37'),
(14, 'Week 15: 17–23 December 2017', 'Ministerial compensation for reasonable service', '1 Tim. 5:17–18', '17 Let the elders that rule well be counted worthy of double honour, especially they who labour in the word and doctrine. 18 For the scripture saith, Thou shalt not muzzle the ox that treadeth out the corn. And, The labourer is worthy of his reward.', 1, 2017, '2017-12-17', '2018-02-15 09:54:37'),
(15, 'Week 16: 24–30 December 2017', 'Responsible leadership practices', '1 Tim. 5:19–25', '19 Against an elder receive not an accusation, but before two or three witnesses. 20 Them that sin rebuke before all, that others also may fear. 21 I charge thee before God, and the Lord Jesus Christ, and the elect angels, that thou observe these things without preferring one before another, doing nothing by partiality. 22 Lay hands suddenly on no man, neither be partaker of other men\'s sins: keep thyself pure. 23 Drink no longer water, but use a little wine for thy stomach\'s sake and thine often infirmities. 24 Some men\'s sins are open beforehand, going before to judgment; and some men they follow after. 25 Likewise also the good works of some are manifest beforehand; and they that are otherwise cannot be hid.', 1, 2017, '2017-12-24', '2018-02-15 09:54:37'),
(16, 'Week 17: 31 December 2017–6 January 2018', 'Practical submission in reasonable service', '1 Tim. 6:1–2', 'Let as many servants as are under the yoke count their own masters worthy of all honour, that the name of God and his doctrine be not blasphemed. 2 And they that have believing masters, let them not despise them, because they are brethren; but rather do them service, because they are faithful and beloved, partakers of the benefit. These things teach and exhort.', 1, 2017, '2017-12-31', '2018-02-15 09:54:37'),
(17, 'Week 18: 7–13 January 2018', 'Unreasonable Gospel of prosperity ', '1 Tim. 6:3–5', '3 If anyone teaches otherwise and does not consent to wholesome words, even the words of our Lord Jesus Christ, and to the doctrine which accords with godliness, 4 he is proud, knowing nothing, but is obsessed with disputes and arguments over words, from which come envy, strife, reviling, evil suspicions, 5 useless wranglings of men of corrupt minds and destitute of the truth, who suppose that godliness is a means of gain. From such withdraw yourself.', 1, 2017, '2018-01-07', '2018-02-15 09:54:37'),
(18, 'Week 19: 14–20 January 2018', 'Godliness with contentment: The path of reasonable living', '1 Tim. 6:6–8', '6 But godliness with contentment is great gain. 7 For we brought nothing into this world, and it is certain we can carry nothing out. 8 And having food and raiment let us be therewith content.', 1, 2017, '2018-01-14', '2018-02-15 10:03:39'),
(19, 'Week 20 & 21: 21 January–3 February 2018', 'The snare of the love of money', '1 Tim. 6:9–10', '9 But they that will be rich fall into temptation and a snare, and into many foolish and hurtful lusts, which drown men in destruction and perdition. 10 For the love of money is the root of all evil: which while some coveted after, they have erred from the faith, and pierced themselves through with many sorrows.', 2, 2017, '2018-01-21', '2018-02-15 10:03:39'),
(20, 'Week 22: 4–10 February 2018', 'The reasonable fight of faith', '1 Tim. 6:11–12', '11 But thou, O man of God, flee these things; and follow after righteousness, godliness, faith, love, patience, meekness. 12 Fight the good fight of faith, lay hold on eternal life, whereunto thou art also called, and hast professed a good profession before many witnesses.', 1, 2017, '2018-02-04', '2018-02-15 10:03:39'),
(21, 'Week 23:  11–17 February 2018', 'Integrity through the knowledge of God’s glory', '1 Tim. 6:13–16', '13 I give thee charge in the sight of God, who quickeneth all things, and before Christ Jesus, who before Pontius Pilate witnessed a good confession; 14 That thou keep this commandment without spot, unrebukable, until the appearing of our Lord Jesus Christ: 15 Which in his times he shall shew, who is the blessed and only Potentate, the King of kings, and Lord of lords; 16 Who only hath immortality, dwelling in the light which no man can approach unto; whom no man hath seen, nor can see: to whom be honour and power everlasting. Amen.', 1, 2017, '2018-02-11', '2018-02-15 10:03:39'),
(22, 'Week 24: 18–24 February 2018', 'Reasonable management of godly wealth', '1 Tim. 6:17–21', '17 Charge them that are rich in this world, that they be not high-minded, nor trust in uncertain riches, but in the living God, who giveth us richly all things to enjoy; 18 That they do good, that they be rich in good works, ready to distribute, willing to communicate; 19 Laying up in store for themselves a good foundation against the time to come, that they may lay hold on eternal life. 20 O Timothy, keep that which is committed to thy trust, avoiding profane and vain babblings, and oppositions of science falsely so called: 21 Which some professing have erred concerning the faith. Grace be with thee. Amen.', 1, 2017, '2018-02-18', '2018-02-15 10:03:39'),
(23, 'Week 25: 25 February–3 March 2018', 'Raising transgenerational agents and fearless ministers', '2 Tim. 1:1–7', 'Paul, an apostle of Jesus Christ by the will of God, according to the promise of life which is in Christ Jesus, 2 To Timothy, my dearly beloved son: Grace, mercy, and peace, from God the Father and Christ Jesus our Lord. 3 I thank God, whom I serve from my forefathers with pure conscience, that without ceasing I have remembrance of thee in my prayers night and day; 4 Greatly desiring to see thee, being mindful of thy tears, that I may be filled with joy; 5 When I call to remembrance the unfeigned faith that is in thee, which dwelt first in thy grandmother Lois, and thy mother Eunice; and I am persuaded that in thee also. 6 Wherefore I put thee in remembrance that thou stir up the gift of God, which is in thee by the putting on of my hands. 7 For God hath not given us the spirit of fear; but of power, and of love, and of a sound mind.', 1, 2017, '2018-02-25', '2018-02-15 10:46:44'),
(24, 'Week 26: 4–10 March 2017', 'Partaker of the afflictions of the Gospel', '2 Tim. 1:8–11', '8 Be not thou therefore ashamed of the testimony of our Lord, nor of me his prisoner: but be thou partaker of the afflictions of the gospel according to the power of God; 9 Who hath saved us, and called us with an holy calling, not according to our works, but according to his own purpose and grace, which was given us in Christ Jesus before the world began, 10 But is now made manifest by the appearing of our Saviour Jesus Christ, who hath abolished death, and hath brought life and immortality to light through the gospel: 11 Whereunto I am appointed a preacher, and an apostle, and a teacher of the Gentiles.', 1, 2017, '2018-03-04', '2018-02-15 10:46:44'),
(25, 'Week 27: 11–17 March 2018', 'Preserving the investment through the Spirit', '2 Tim. 1:12–14', '12 For the which cause I also suffer these things: nevertheless I am not ashamed: for I know whom I have believed, and am persuaded that he is able to keep that which I have committed unto him against that day. 13 Hold fast the form of sound words, which thou hast heard of me, in faith and love which is in Christ Jesus. 14 That good thing which was committed unto thee keep by the Holy Ghost which dwelleth in us.', 1, 2017, '2018-03-11', '2018-02-15 10:46:44'),
(26, 'Week 28 & 29: 18–31 March 2018', 'Divine appointment and human disappointment', '2 Tim. 1:15–18', '15 This thou knowest, that all they which are in Asia be turned away from me; of whom are Phygellus and Hermogenes. 16 The Lord give mercy unto the house of Onesiphorus; for he oft refreshed me, and was not ashamed of my chain: 17 But, when he was in Rome, he sought me out very diligently, and found me. 18 The Lord grant unto him that he may find mercy of the Lord in that day: and in how many things he ministered unto me at Ephesus, thou knowest very well.', 2, 2017, '2018-03-18', '2018-02-15 10:46:44'),
(27, 'Week 30 & 31: 1–14 April 2018', 'Strength and grace for reasonable service', '2 Tim. 2:1', 'Thou therefore, my son, be strong in the grace that is in Christ Jesus.', 2, 2017, '2018-04-01', '2018-02-15 10:46:44'),
(28, 'Week 32 & 33: 15–28 April 2018', 'Raising faithful men through reasonable practice of discipleship', '2 Tim. 2:2', '2 And the things that thou hast heard of me among many witnesses, the same commit thou to faithful men, who shall be able to teach others also.', 2, 2017, '2018-04-15', '2018-02-15 10:54:43'),
(29, 'Week 34 & 35: 29 April–12 May 2018', 'Enduring hardness (hardship) as an act of reasonable service', '2 Tim. 2:3–7', '3 Thou therefore endure hardness (hardship), as a good soldier of Jesus Christ. 4 No man that warreth entangleth himself with the affairs of this life; that he may please him who hath chosen him to be a soldier. 5 And if a man also strive for masteries, yet is he not crowned, except he strive lawfully. 6 The husbandman that laboureth must be first partaker of the fruits. 7 Consider what I say; and the Lord give thee understanding in all things.', 2, 2017, '2018-04-29', '2018-02-15 10:54:43'),
(30, 'Week 36: 13–19 May 2018', 'Enduring through Christ', '2 Tim. 2:8–13', '8 Remember that Jesus Christ of the seed of David was raised from the dead according to my gospel: 9 Wherein I suffer trouble, as an evil doer, even unto bonds; but the word of God is not bound. 10 Therefore I endure all things for the elect’s sake, that they may also obtain the salvation which is in Christ Jesus with eternal glory. 11 It is a faithful saying: For if we be dead with him, we shall also live with him: 12 If we suffer, we shall also reign with him: if we deny him, he also will deny us: 13 If we believe not, yet he abideth faithful: he cannot deny himself.', 1, 2017, '2018-05-13', '2018-02-15 10:54:43'),
(31, 'Week 37 & 38: 20 May–2 June 2018', 'Reasonable Ministry of the Word of God', '2 Tim. 2:14–19', '14 Of these things put them in remembrance, charging them before the Lord that they strive not about words to no profit, but to the subverting of the hearers. 15 Study to shew thyself approved unto God, a workman that needeth not to be ashamed, rightly dividing the word of truth. 16 But shun profane and vain babblings: for they will increase unto more ungodliness. 17 And their word will eat as doth a canker: of whom is Hymenaeus and Philetus; 18 Who concerning the truth have erred, saying that the resurrection is past already; and overthrow the faith of some. 19 Nevertheless the foundation of God standeth sure, having this seal, The Lord knoweth them that are his. And, let everyone that nameth the name of Christ depart from iniquity.', 2, 2017, '2018-05-20', '2018-02-15 10:54:43'),
(32, 'Week 39: 3–9 June 2017', 'A reasonable vessel in a great house', '2 Tim. 2:20–22', '20 But in a great house there are not only vessels of gold and of silver, but also of wood and of earth; and some to honour, and some to dishonour. 21 If a man therefore purge himself from these, he shall be a vessel unto honour, sanctified, and meet for the master\'s use, and prepared unto every good work. 22 Flee also youthful lusts: but follow righteousness, faith, charity, peace, with them that call on the Lord out of a pure heart.', 1, 2017, '2018-06-03', '2018-02-15 10:54:43'),
(33, 'Week 40: 10–16 June 2018', 'The character of a reasonable servant of God', '2 Tim. 2:23–26', '23 But foolish and unlearned questions avoid, knowing that they do gender strifes. 24 And the servant of the Lord must not strive; but be gentle unto all men, apt to teach, patient, 25 In meekness instructing those that oppose themselves; if God peradventure will give them repentance to the acknowledging of the truth; 26 And that they may recover themselves out of the snare of the devil, who are taken captive by him at his will.', 1, 2017, '2018-06-10', '2018-02-15 10:54:43'),
(34, 'Week 41: 17–23 June 2018', 'Escaping false Christianity in the perilous times', '2 Tim. 3:1–9', 'Full Bible Reference:\r\nThis know also, that in the last days perilous times shall come. 2 For men shall be lovers of their own selves, covetous, boasters, proud, blasphemers, disobedient to parents, unthankful, unholy, 3 Without natural affection, trucebreakers, false accusers, incontinent, fierce, despisers of those that are good, 4 Traitors, heady, high-minded, lovers of pleasures more than lovers of God; 5 Having a form of godliness, but denying the power thereof: from such turn away. 6 For of this sort are they which creep into houses, and lead captive silly women laden with sins, led away with divers lusts, 7 Ever learning, and never able to come to the knowledge of the truth. 8 Now as Jannes and Jambres withstood Moses, so do these also resist the truth: men of corrupt minds, reprobate concerning the faith. 9 But they shall proceed no further: for their folly shall be manifest unto all men, as theirs also was.\r\n', 1, 2017, '2018-06-17', '2018-02-15 11:03:37'),
(35, 'Week 42: 24–30 June 2018', 'Consistency in our Christian walk amidst persecution', '2 Tim. 3:10–15', '10 But thou hast fully known my doctrine, manner of life, purpose, faith, longsuffering, charity, patience, 11 Persecutions, afflictions, which came unto me at Antioch, at Iconium, at Lystra; what persecutions I endured: but out of them all the Lord delivered me. 12 Yea, and all that will live godly in Christ Jesus shall suffer persecution. 13 But evil men and seducers shall wax worse and worse, deceiving, and being deceived. 14 But continue thou in the things which thou hast learned and hast been assured of, knowing of whom thou hast learned them; 15 And that from a child thou hast known the holy scriptures, which are able to make thee wise unto salvation through faith which is in Christ Jesus.', 1, 2017, '2018-06-24', '2018-02-15 11:03:37'),
(36, 'Week 43: 1–7 July 2018', 'Biblical equipping for reasonable service', '2 Tim. 3:16–17', '16 All Scripture is given by inspiration of God, and is profitable for doctrine, for reproof, for correction, for instruction in righteousness: 17 That the man of God may be perfect, thoroughly furnished unto all good works.', 1, 2017, '2018-07-01', '2018-02-15 11:03:37'),
(37, 'Week 44: 8–14 July 2018', 'Reasonable consistency in Christian ministry', '2 Tim. 4:1–5', 'I charge thee therefore before God, and the Lord Jesus Christ, who shall judge the quick and the dead at his appearing and his kingdom; 2 Preach the word; be instant in season, out of season; reprove, rebuke, exhort with all long suffering and doctrine. 3 For the time will come when they will not endure sound doctrine; but after their own lusts shall they heap to themselves teachers, having itching ears; 4 And they shall turn away their ears from the truth, and shall be turned unto fables. 5 But watch thou in all things, endure afflictions, do the work of an evangelist, make full proof of thy ministry.', 1, 2017, '2018-07-08', '2018-02-15 11:03:37'),
(38, 'Week 45 & 46: 15–28 July 2018', 'Finishing well and strong', '2 Tim. 4:6–8', '6 For I am now ready to be offered, and the time of my departure is at hand. 7 I have fought a good fight, I have finished my course, I have kept the faith: 8 Henceforth there is laid up for me a crown of righteousness, which the Lord, the righteous judge, shall give me at that day: and not to me only, but unto all them also that love his appearing.', 2, 2017, '2018-07-15', '2018-02-15 11:03:37'),
(39, 'Week 47, 48, & 49: 29 July–18 August 2018 ', 'Reasonable life preparation for shocks and surprises', '2 Tim. 4:9–22', '9 Do thy diligence to come shortly unto me: 10 For Demas hath forsaken me, having loved this present world, and is departed unto Thessalonica; Crescens to Galatia, Titus unto Dalmatia. 11 Only Luke is with me. Take Mark, and bring him with thee: for he is profitable to me for the ministry. 12 And Tychicus have I sent to Ephesus. 13 The cloak that I left at Troas with Carpus, when thou comest, bring with thee, and the books, but especially the parchments. 14 Alexander the coppersmith did me much evil: the Lord reward him according to his works: 15 Of whom be thou ware also; for he hath greatly withstood our words. 16 At my first answer no man stood with me, but all men forsook me: I pray God that it may not be laid to their charge. 17 Notwithstanding the Lord stood with me, and strengthened me; that by me the preaching might be fully known, and that all the Gentiles might hear: and I was delivered out of the mouth of the lion. 18 And the Lord shall deliver me from every evil work, and will preserve me unto his heavenly kingdom: to whom be glory for ever and ever. Amen. 19 Salute Prisca and Aquila, and the household of Onesiphorus. 20 Erastus abode at Corinth: but Trophimus have I left at Miletum sick. 21 Do thy diligence to come before winter. Eubulus greeteth thee, and Pudens, and Linus, and Claudia, and all the brethren. 22 The Lord Jesus Christ be with thy spirit. Grace be with you. Amen.', 3, 2017, '2018-07-29', '2018-02-15 11:07:49'),
(40, 'Week1: 2 – 15 September 2018', 'Lost in a Strange Land', 'Lev 26 vs 27-33', '[27]And if ye will not for all this hearken unto me, but walk contrary unto me;<br/>[28] Then I will\r\nwalk contrary unto you also in fury; and I, even I, will chastise you seven times for your sins.\r\n<br/>[29] And ye shall eat the flesh of your sons, and the flesh of your daughters shall ye eat.\r\n<br/>[30] And I will destroy your high places, and cut down your images, and cast your carcases\r\nupon the carcases of your idols, and my soul shall abhor you. <br/>[31] And I will make your cities\r\nwaste, and bring your sanctuaries unto desolation, and I will not smell the savour of your\r\nsweet odours. <br/>[32] And I will bring the land into desolation: and your enemies which dwell\r\ntherein shall be astonished at it.<br/>\r\n[33] And I will scatter you among the heathen, and will draw out a sword after you: and your\r\nland shall be desolate, and your cities waste.', 2, 2018, '2018-09-02', '2018-10-03 11:07:49'),
(41, 'Week 3: 16-22 September 2018', 'Seeking Revival While in a Strange Land', 'Psalm 137:1-6', '[1] By the rivers of Babylon, there we sat down, yea, we wept when we remembered Zion. [2]\r\nWe hung our harps upon the willows in the midst of it. [3] For there those who carried us\r\naway captive asked of us a song, And those who plundered us requested mirth, Saying, “Sing\r\nus one of the songs of Zion!” [4] How shall we sing the Lord\'s song In a foreign land? [5] If I\r\nforget you, O Jerusalem, Let my right hand forget its skill! [6] If I do not remember you, Let my\r\ntongue cling to the roof of my mouth—If I do not exalt Jerusalem above my chief joy.', 1, 2018, '2018-09-16', '2018-10-03 11:07:49'),
(42, 'Week 4: 23-29 September 2018', 'Understanding the Times— it is Time to Return to Jerusalem.', 'Ezra 1:1', 'Now in the first year of Cyrus king of Persia, that the word of the LORD by the mouth of\r\nJeremiah might be fulfilled, the LORD stirred up the spirit of Cyrus king of Persia, that he made\r\na proclamation throughout all his kingdom, and put it also in writing…', 1, 2018, '2018-09-23', '2018-10-03 21:50:24'),
(43, 'Week 5: 30 September – 6 October', '2018Fellowship Reflection & Tarry\r\nMeeting', '', '', 1, 2018, '2018-09-30', '2018-10-03 21:53:03'),
(44, 'Week 6: 7-13 October 2018', 'God\'s Sovereignty Over the Affairs of Men', 'Ezra 1:1-2', '[1] Now in the first year of Cyrus king of Persia, that the word of the Lord by the mouth of\r\nJeremiah might be fulfilled, the Lord stirred up the spirit of Cyrus king of Persia, that he made\r\na proclamation throughout all his kingdom, and put it also in writing, saying, [2] Thus saith\r\nCyrus king of Persia, The Lord God of heaven hath given me all the kingdoms of the earth; and\r\nhe hath charged me to build him a house at Jerusalem, which is in Judah.', 1, 2018, '2018-10-07', '2018-10-03 21:57:53'),
(45, 'Week 7: 14-20 October 2018', 'Many Are Called But Few Are Chosen: Answering God\'s Call unto Revival', 'Ezra 1:3, 5', '[3] Who is there among you of all his people? his God be with him, and let him go up to\r\nJerusalem, which is in Judah, and build the house of the Lord God of Israel, (he is the God,)\r\nwhich is in Jerusalem.<br/>\r\n[5] Then rose up the chief of the fathers of Judah and Benjamin, and the priests, and the\r\nLevites, with all them whose spirit God had raised, to go up to build the house of the Lord\r\nwhich is in Jerusalem.', 1, 2018, '2018-10-14', '2018-10-03 21:57:53'),
(46, 'Week 8: 21-27 October 2018', 'Divine Provision For The Mandate of Revival', 'Ezra 1:4, 6', '[4] And whoever is left in any place where he dwells, let the men of his place help him with\r\nsilver and gold, with goods and livestock, besides the freewill offerings for the house of God\r\nwhich is in Jerusalem.<br/>\r\n[6] And all those who were around them encouraged them with articles of silver and gold,\r\nwith goods and livestock, and with precious things, besides all that was willingly offered.\r\n(NKJV)', 1, 2018, '2018-10-21', '2018-10-03 21:57:53'),
(47, 'Week 9: 28 October – 3 November 2018', 'Fellowship Reflection & Tarry\r\nMeeting', '', '', 1, 2018, '2018-10-28', '2018-10-03 22:02:05'),
(48, 'Week 10: 4-10 November 2018', 'Bringing Back the Lost Instruments of Worship', 'Ezra 1:7-11', '[7] Also Cyrus the king brought forth the vessels of the house of the Lord, which\r\nNebuchadnezzar had brought forth out of Jerusalem and had put them in the house of his\r\ngods; [8] even those did Cyrus king of Persia bring forth by the hand of Mithredath the\r\ntreasurer, and counted them over to Sheshbazzar, the prince of Judah. [9] And this is the\r\nnumber of them: thirty chargers of gold, a thousand chargers of silver, nine and twenty\r\nknives, [10] thirty basins of gold, four hundred and ten silver basins of a second sort, and\r\nother vessels a thousand. [11] All the vessels of gold and of silver were five thousand and four\r\nhundred. All these did Sheshbazzar bring up with those of the captivity, who were brought up\r\nfrom Babylon unto Jerusalem.', 1, 2018, '2018-11-04', '2018-10-03 22:02:05'),
(49, 'Week 11: 11-17 November 2018', 'The Returnees: Profile, Passion, and the Missing Identities', 'Ezra 2:1-67', '[1]Now these are the people of the province who came back from the captivity, of those who\r\nhad been carried away, whom Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon had carried away to\r\nBabylon, and who returned to Jerusalem and Judah, everyone to his own city.[2] Those who\r\ncame with Zerubbabel were Jeshua, Nehemiah, Seraiah, Reelaiah, Mordecai, Bilshan,\r\nMispar,[b] Bigvai, Rehum,[c] and Baanah. The number of the men of the people of Israel: [3]\r\nthe people of Parosh, two thousand one hundred and seventy-two; [4] the people of\r\nShephatiah, three hundred and seventy-two; [5] the people of Arah, seven hundred and\r\nseventy-five; [6] the people of Pahath-Moab, of the people of Jeshua and Joab, two\r\nthousand eight hundred and twelve; [7] the people of Elam, one thousand two hundred and\r\nfifty-four; [8] the people of Zattu, nine hundred and forty-five; [9] the people of Zaccai, seven\r\nhundred and sixty; [10] the people of Bani,[d] six hundred and forty-two; [11] the people of\r\nBebai, six hundred and twenty-three; [12] the people of Azgad, one thousand two hundred\r\nand twenty-two; [13] the people of Adonikam, six hundred and sixty-six; [14] the people of\r\nBigvai, two thousand and fifty-six; [15] the people of Adin, four hundred and fifty-four; [16]\r\nthe people of Ater of Hezekiah, ninety-eight; [17] the people of Bezai, three hundred and\r\ntwenty-three; [18] the people of Jorah,[e] one hundred and twelve; [19] the people of\r\nHashum, two hundred and twenty-three; [20] the people of Gibbar,[f] ninety-five; [21] the\r\npeople of Bethlehem, one hundred and twenty-three; [22] the men of Netophah, fifty-six;\r\n[23] the men of Anathoth, one hundred and twenty-eight; [24] the people of Azmaveth,[g]\r\nforty-two; [25] the people of Kirjath Arim,[h] Chephirah, and Beeroth, seven hundred and\r\nforty-three; [26] the people of Ramah and Geba, six hundred and twenty-one; [27] the men\r\nof Michmas, one hundred and twenty-two; [28] the men of Bethel and Ai, two hundred and\r\ntwenty-three; [29] the people of Nebo, fifty-two; [30] the people of Magbish, one hundred\r\nand fifty-six; [31] the people of the other Elam, one thousand two hundred and fifty-four;\r\n[32] the people of Harim, three hundred and twenty; [33] the people of Lod, Hadid, and Ono,\r\nseven hundred and twenty-five; [34] the people of Jericho, three hundred and forty-five; [35]\r\nthe people of Senaah, three thousand six hundred and thirty.[36] The priests: the sons of\r\nJedaiah, of the house of Jeshua, nine hundred and seventy-three; [37] the sons of Immer, one\r\nthousand and fifty-two; [38] the sons of Pashhur, one thousand two hundred and fortyseven;\r\n[39] the sons of Harim, one thousand and seventeen.[40] The Levites: the sons of\r\nJeshua and Kadmiel, of the sons of Hodaviah,[i] seventy-four.[41] The singers: the sons of\r\nAsaph, one hundred and twenty-eight.[42] The sons of the gatekeepers: the sons of Shallum,\r\nthe sons of Ater, the sons of Talmon, the sons of Akkub, the sons of Hatita, and the sons of\r\nShobai, one hundred and thirty-nine in all.[43] The Nethinim: the sons of Ziha, the sons of\r\nHasupha, the sons of Tabbaoth, [44] the sons of Keros, the sons of Siaha,[j] the sons of\r\nPadon, [45] the sons of Lebanah, the sons of Hagabah, the sons of Akkub, [46] the sons of\r\nHagab, the sons of Shalmai, the sons of Hanan, [47] the sons of Giddel, the sons of Gahar, the\r\nsons of Reaiah, [48] the sons of Rezin, the sons of Nekoda, the sons of Gazzam, [49] the sons\r\nof Uzza, the sons of Paseah, the sons of Besai, [50] the sons of Asnah, the sons of Meunim, the\r\nsons of Nephusim,[k] [51] the sons of Bakbuk, the sons of Hakupha, the sons of Harhur, [52]\r\nthe sons of Bazluth,[l] the sons of Mehida, the sons of Harsha, [53] the sons of Barkos, the\r\nsons of Sisera, the sons of Tamah, [54] the sons of Neziah, and the sons of Hatipha.[55] The\r\nsons of Solomon\'s servants: the sons of Sotai, the sons of Sophereth, the sons of Peruda,[m]\r\n[56] the sons of Jaala, the sons of Darkon, the sons of Giddel, [57] the sons of Shephatiah, the\r\nsons of Hattil, the sons of Pochereth of Zebaim, and the sons of Ami.[n] [58] All the Nethinim\r\nand the children of Solomon\'s servants were three hundred and ninety-two.[59]And these\r\nwere the ones who came up from Tel Melah, Tel Harsha, Cherub, Addan,[o] and Immer; but\r\nthey could not identify their father\'s house or their genealogy,[p] whether they were of Israel:\r\n[60] the sons of Delaiah, the sons of Tobiah, and the sons of Nekoda, six hundred and fiftytwo;\r\n[61] and of the sons of the priests: the sons of Habaiah, the sons of Koz,[q] and the sons\r\nof Barzillai, who took a wife of the daughters of Barzillai the Gileadite, and was called by their\r\nname. [62] These sought their listing among those who were registered by genealogy, but\r\nthey were not found; therefore they were excluded from the priesthood as defiled. [63] And\r\nthe governor[r] said to them that they should not eat of the most holy things till a priest could\r\nconsult with the Urim and Thummim.[64] The whole assembly together was forty-two\r\nthousand three hundred and sixty, [65] besides their male and female servants, of whom\r\nthere were seven thousand three hundred and thirty-seven; and they had two hundred men\r\nand women singers. [66] Their horses were seven hundred and thirty-six, their mules two\r\nhundred and forty-five, [67] their camels four hundred and thirty-five, and their donkeys six\r\nthousand seven hundred and twenty. (NKJV)', 1, 2018, '2018-11-11', '2018-10-03 22:02:05'),
(50, 'Week 12: 18-24 November 2018', 'Arriving Jerusalem: The Power of Focus on Divine Assignment', 'Ezra 2:68-70', '[68] And some of the chiefsof the fathers, when they came to the house of the Lord which is at\r\nJerusalem, offered freely for the house of God to set it up in his place.[69] They gave according\r\nto their ability to the treasury of the work, threescore and one thousand drams of gold, and\r\nfive thousand pounds of silver, and one hundred priests\' garments.[70] So the priests and the\r\nLevites and some of the people, and the singers and the gatekeepers and the Nethinim, dwelt\r\nin their cities, and all Israel in their cities.', 1, 2018, '2018-11-18', '2018-10-03 22:07:20'),
(51, 'Week 13: 25 November – 1 December 2018', 'Fellowship Reflection &\r\nTarry Meeting', '', '', 1, 2018, '2018-11-25', '2018-10-03 22:07:20'),
(52, 'Week 14: 2-8 December 2018', 'The Place of the Altar: Beginning of True Revival', 'Ezra 3:1-6', '[1 ]When the seventh month came and the Israelites had settled in their towns, the people\r\nassembled together as one in Jerusalem. [2] Then Joshua son of Jozadak and his fellow priests\r\nand Zerubbabel son of Shealtiel and his associates began to build the altar of the God of Israel\r\nto sacrifice burnt offerings on it, in accordance with what is written in the Law of Moses the\r\nman of God. [3] Despite their fear of the peoples around them, they built the altar on its\r\nfoundation and sacrificed burnt offerings on it to the Lord, both the morning and evening\r\nsacrifices. [4] Then in accordance with what is written, they celebrated the Festival of\r\nTabernacles with the required number of burnt offerings prescribed for each day. [5] After\r\nthat, they presented the regular burnt offerings, the New Moon sacrifices and the sacrifices\r\nfor all the appointed sacred festivals of the Lord, as well as those brought as freewill offerings\r\nto the Lord. [6] On the first day of the seventh month they began to offer burnt offerings to the\r\nLord, though the foundation of the Lord\'s temple had not yet been laid. (NIV)', 1, 2018, '2018-12-02', '2018-10-03 22:07:20'),
(53, 'Week 15 &16: 9-22 December', 'Rebuilding the Foundation of Worship', 'Ezra 3:8-13', '[8] Now in the second year of their coming unto the house of God at Jerusalem, in the second\r\nmonth, began Zerubbabel the son of Shealtiel, and Jeshua the son of Jozadak, and the\r\nremnant of their brethren the priests and the Levites, and all they that were come out of the\r\ncaptivity unto Jerusalem; and appointed the Levites, from twenty years old and upward, to set\r\nforward the work of the house of the Lord.[9] Then stood Jeshua with his sons and his\r\nbrethren, Kadmiel and his sons, the sons of Judah, together, to set forward the workmen in the\r\nhouse of God: the sons of Henadad, with their sons and their brethren the Levites.[10] And\r\nwhen the builders laid the foundation of the temple of the Lord, they set the priests in their\r\napparel with trumpets, and the Levites the sons of Asaph with cymbals, to praise the Lord,\r\nafter the ordinance of David king of Israel.[11] And they sang together by course in praising\r\nand giving thanks unto the Lord; because he is good, for his mercy endureth for ever toward\r\nIsrael. And all the people shouted with a great shout, when they praised the Lord, because the\r\nfoundation of the house of the Lord was laid.[12] But many of the priests and Levites and chief\r\nof the fathers, who were ancient men, that had seen the first house, when the foundation of\r\nthis house was laid before their eyes, wept with a loud voice; and many shouted aloud for\r\njoy:[13] So that the people could not discern the noise of the shout of joy from the noise of the\r\nweeping of the people: for the people shouted with a loud shout, and the noise was heard afar\r\noff.', 2, 2018, '2018-12-09', '2018-10-03 22:07:20'),
(54, 'Week 17: 23-29 December 2018', 'Beware of Fake Revival', 'Ezra 4:1-3', '[1]Now when the adversaries of Judah and Benjamin heard that the children of the captivity\r\nbuilded the temple unto the Lord God of Israel;[2] Then they came to Zerubbabel, and to the\r\nchief of the fathers, and said unto them, Let us build with you: for we seek your God, as ye do;\r\nand we do sacrifice unto him since the days of Esarhaddon king of Assur, which brought us up\r\nhither.[3] But Zerubbabel, and Jeshua, and the rest of the chief of the fathers of Israel, said\r\nunto them, Ye have nothing to do with us to build ahouse unto our God; but we ourselves\r\ntogether will build unto the Lord God of Israel, as king Cyrus the king of Persia hath\r\ncommanded us.', 1, 2018, '2018-12-23', '2018-10-03 22:21:28'),
(55, 'Week 18: 30 December 2018 – 5 January 2019', 'Fellowship Reflection &\r\nTarry Meeting', '', '', 1, 2018, '2018-12-30', '2018-10-03 22:21:28'),
(56, 'Week 19: 6-12 January 2019', 'How the Enemy Frustrates Revival', 'Ezra 4:4-5', '[4] Then the people of the land weakened the hands of the people of Judah, and troubled\r\nthem in building,[5] And hired counsellors against them, to frustrate their purpose, all the\r\ndays of Cyrus king of Persia, even until the reign of Darius king of Persia.', 1, 2018, '2019-01-06', '2018-10-03 22:21:28'),
(57, 'Week 20: 13-19 January 2019', 'Advancing despite Opposition in Revival', 'Ezra 4:6-24', '[6] And in the reign of Ahasuerus, in the beginning of his reign, wrote they unto him an\r\naccusation against the inhabitants of Judah and Jerusalem.[7] And in the days of Artaxerxes\r\nwrote Bishlam, Mithredath, Tabeel, and the rest of their companions, unto Artaxerxes king of\r\nPersia; and the writing of the letter was written in the Syrian tongue, and interpreted in the\r\nSyrian tongue.[8] Rehum the chancellor and Shimshai the scribe wrote a letter against\r\nJerusalem to Artaxerxes the king in this sort:[9] Then wrote Rehum the chancellor, and\r\nShimshai the scribe, and the rest of their companions; the Dinaites, the Apharsathchites, the\r\nTarpelites, the Apharsites, the Archevites, the Babylonians, the Susanchites, the Dehavites,\r\nand the Elamites,[10] And the rest of the nations whom the great and noble Asnapper\r\nbrought over, and set in the cities of Samaria, and the rest that are on this side the river, and at\r\nsuch a time.[11] This is the copy of the letter that they sent unto him, even unto Artaxerxes the\r\nking; Thy servants the men on this side of the river, and at such a time.[12] Be it known unto\r\nthe king, that the Jews which came up from thee to us are come unto Jerusalem, building the\r\nrebellious and the bad city, and have set up the walls thereof, and joined the foundations.[13]\r\nBe it known now unto the king, that, if this city be builded, and the walls set up again, then will\r\nthey not pay toll, tribute, and custom, and so thou shalt endamage the revenue of the\r\nkings.[14] Now because we have maintenance from the king\'s palace, and it was not meet for\r\nus to see the king\'s dishonour, therefore have we sent and certified the king;[15] That search\r\nmay be made in the book of the records of thy fathers: so shalt thou find in the book of the\r\nrecords, and know that this city is a rebellious city, and hurtful unto kings and provinces, and\r\nthat they have moved sedition within the same of old time: for which cause was this city\r\ndestroyed.[16] We certify the king that, if this city be builded again, and the walls thereof set\r\nup, by this means thou shalt have no portion on this side of the river.[17] Then, sent the king\r\nan answer unto Rehum the chancellor, and to Shimshai the scribe, and to the rest of their\r\ncompanions that dwell in Samaria, and unto the rest beyond the river, Peace, and at such a\r\ntime.[18] The letter which ye sent unto us hath been plainly read before me.[19] And I\r\ncommanded, and search hath been made, and it is found that this city of old time hath made\r\ninsurrection against kings, and that rebellion and sedition have been made therein.[20]\r\nThere have been mighty kings also over Jerusalem, which have ruled over all countries\r\nbeyond the river; and toll, tribute, and custom, was paid unto them.[21] Give ye now\r\ncommandment to cause these men to cease, and that this city be not builded, until another\r\ncommandment shall be given from me.[22] Take heed now that ye fail not to do this: why\r\nshould damage grow to the hurt of the kings?[23] Now when the copy of king Artaxerxes\'\r\nletter was read before Rehum, and Shimshai the scribe, and their companions, they went up\r\nin haste to Jerusalem unto the Jews, and made them to cease by force and power.[24] Then\r\nceased the work of the house of God which is at Jerusalem. So it ceased unto the second year\r\nof the reign of Darius king of Persia.', 1, 2018, '2019-01-13', '2018-10-03 22:21:28'),
(58, 'Week 21: 20-26 January, 2019', 'Fellowship Reflection & Tarry Meeting', '', '', 1, 2018, '2019-01-20', '2018-10-03 22:26:15'),
(59, 'Week 22&23: 27 January – 9 February 2019', 'Prophetic Guidance in Revival', 'Ezra chapter 5, Haggai 1', '[1]Then the prophets, Haggai the prophet, and Zechariah the son of Iddo, prophesied unto\r\nthe Jews that were in Judah and Jerusalem in the name of the God of Israel, even unto\r\nthem.[2] Then rose up Zerubbabel the son of Shealtiel, and Jeshua the son of Jozadak, and\r\nbegan to build the house of God which is at Jerusalem: and with them were the prophets of\r\nGod helping them.[3] At the same time came to them Tatnai, governor on this side the river,\r\nand Shetharboznai and their companions, and said thus unto them, Who hath commanded\r\nyou to build this house, and to make up this wall?[4] Then said we unto them after this\r\nmanner, What are the names of the men that make this building?[5] But the eye of their God\r\nwas upon the elders of the Jews, that they could not cause them to cease, till the matter came\r\nto Darius: and then they returned answer by letter concerning this matter.[6] The copy of the\r\nletter that Tatnai, governor on this side the river, and Shetharboznai and his companions the\r\nApharsachites, which were on this side the river, sent unto Darius the king:[7] They sent a\r\nletter unto him, wherein was written thus; Unto Darius the king, all peace.[8] Be it known\r\nunto the king, that we went into the province of Judea, to the house of the great God, which is\r\nbuilded with great stones, and timber is laid in the walls, and this work goeth fast on, and\r\nprospereth in their hands.[9] Then asked we those elders, and said unto them thus, Who\r\ncommanded you to build this house, and to make up these walls?[10] We asked their names\r\nalso, to certify thee, that we might write the names of the men that were the chief of\r\nthem.[11] And thus they returned us answer, saying, We are the servants of the God of\r\nheaven and earth, and build the house that was builded these many years ago, which a great\r\nking of Israel builded and set up.[12] But after that our fathers had provoked the God of\r\nheaven unto wrath, he gave them into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon, the\r\nChaldean, who destroyed this house, and carried the people away into Babylon.[13] But in\r\nthe first year of Cyrus the king of Babylon the same king Cyrus made a decree to build this\r\nhouse of God.[14] And the vessels also of gold and silver of the house of God, which\r\nNebuchadnezzar took out of the temple that was in Jerusalem, and brought them into the\r\ntemple of Babylon, those did Cyrus the king take out of the temple of Babylon, and they were\r\ndelivered unto one, whose name was Sheshbazzar, whom he had made governor;[15] And\r\nsaid unto him, Take these vessels, go, carry them into the temple that is in Jerusalem, and let\r\nthe house of God be builded in his place.[16] Then came the same Sheshbazzar, and laid the\r\nfoundation of the house of God which is in Jerusalem: and since that time even until now hath\r\nit been in building, and yet it is not finished.[17] Now, therefore, if it seem good to the king, let\r\nthere be search made in the king\'s treasure house, which is there at Babylon, whether it be\r\nso, that a decree was made of Cyrus the king to build this house of God at Jerusalem, and let\r\nthe king send his pleasure to us concerning this matter.', 2, 2018, '2019-01-27', '2018-10-03 22:26:15'),
(60, 'Week 24: 10-16 February 2019', 'Determination that Provokes Divine Intervention', 'Ezra 6:1-15', '[1]Then Darius the king made a decree, and search was made in the house of the rolls, where\r\nthe treasures were laid up in Babylon.[2] And there was found at Achmetha, in the palace\r\nthat is in the province of the Medes, a roll, and therein was a record thus written:[3] In the first\r\nyear of Cyrus the king the same Cyrus the king made a decree concerning the house of God at\r\nJerusalem, Let the house be builded, the place where they offered sacrifices, and let the\r\nfoundations thereof be strongly laid; the height thereof threescore cubits, and the breadth\r\nthereof threescore cubits;[4] With three rows of great stones, and a row of new timber: and\r\nlet the expenses be given out of the king\'s house:[5] And also let the golden and silver vessels\r\nof the house of God, which Nebuchadnezzar took forth out of the temple which is at\r\nJerusalem, and brought unto Babylon, be restored, and brought again unto the temple which\r\nis at Jerusalem, everyone to his place, and place them in the house of God.[6] Now, therefore,\r\nTatnai, governor beyond the river, Shetharboznai, and your companions the Apharsachites,\r\nwhich are beyond the river, be ye far from thence:[7] Let the work of this house of God alone;\r\nlet the governor of the Jews and the elders of the Jews build this house of God in his place.[8]\r\nMoreover I make a decree what ye shall do to the elders of these Jews for the building of this\r\nhouse of God: that of the king\'s goods, even of the tribute beyond the river, forthwith\r\nexpenses be given unto these men, that they be not hindered.[9] And that which they have\r\nneed of, both young bullocks, and rams, and lambs, for the burnt offerings of the God of\r\nheaven, wheat, salt, wine, and oil, according to the appointment of the priests which are at\r\nJerusalem, let it be given them day by day without fail:[10] That they may offer sacrifices of\r\nsweet savours unto the God of heaven, and pray for the life of the king, and of his sons.[11]\r\nAlso I have made a decree, that whosoever shall alter this word, let timber be pulled down\r\nfrom his house, and being set up, let him be hanged thereon; and let his house be made a\r\ndunghill for this.[12] And the God that hath caused his name to dwell there destroy all kings\r\nand peoplethat shall put to their hand to alter and to destroy this house of God which is at\r\nJerusalem. I Darius have made a decree; let it be done with speed.[13] Then Tatnai, governor\r\non this side the river, Shetharboznai, and their companions, according to that which Darius\r\nthe king had sent, so they did speedily.[14] And the elders of the Jews builded, and they\r\nprospered through the prophesying of Haggai the prophet and Zechariah the son of Iddo. And\r\nthey builded, and finished it, according to the commandment of the God of Israel, and\r\naccording to the commandment of Cyrus, and Darius, and Artaxerxes king of Persia.[15] And\r\nthis house was finished on the third day of the month Adar, which was in the sixth year of the\r\nreign of Darius the king.', 1, 2018, '2019-02-10', '2018-10-03 22:26:15'),
(61, 'Week 25: 17-23 February 2019', 'Victory at Last: The Temple Completed', 'Ezra 6:13-22', '[13] Then Tatnai, governor on this side the river, Shetharboznai, and their companions,\r\naccording to that which Darius the king had sent, so they did speedily.[14] And the elders of\r\nthe Jews builded, and they prospered through the prophesying of Haggai the prophet and\r\nZechariah the son of Iddo. And they builded, and finished it, according to the commandment\r\nof the God of Israel, and according to the commandment of Cyrus, and Darius, and Artaxerxes\r\nking of Persia.[15] And this house was finished on the third day of the month Adar, which was\r\nin the sixth year of the reign of Darius the king.[16] And the children of Israel, the priests, and\r\nthe Levites, and the rest of the children of the captivity, kept the dedication of this house of\r\nGod with joy.[17] And offered at the dedication of this house of God an hundred bullocks, two\r\nhundred rams, four hundred lambs; and for a sin offering for all Israel, twelve he-goats,\r\naccording to the number of the tribes of Israel.[18] And they set the priests in their divisions,\r\nand the Levites in their courses, for the service of God, which is at Jerusalem; as it is written in\r\nthe book of Moses.[19] And the children of the captivity kept the Passover upon the\r\nfourteenth day of the first month.[20] For the priests and the Levites were purified together,\r\nall of them were pure, and killed the Passover for all the children of the captivity, and for their\r\nbrethren the priests, and for themselves.[21] And the children of Israel, which were come\r\nagain out of captivity, and all such as had separated themselves unto them from the filthiness\r\nof the heathen of the land, to seek the Lord God of Israel, did eat,[22] And kept the feast of\r\nunleavened bread seven days with joy: for the Lord had made them joyful, and turned the\r\nheart of the king of Assyria unto them, to strengthen their hands in the work of the house of\r\nGod, the God of Israel.', 1, 2018, '2019-02-17', '2018-10-03 22:30:22'),
(62, 'Week 26: 24 February – 2 March 2019', 'Fellowship Reflection & Tarry\r\nMeeting', '', '', 1, 2018, '2019-02-24', '2018-10-03 22:30:22'),
(63, 'Week 27: 3-9 March 2019', 'The Word of God as the Catalyst for Revival', 'Ezra 7', '[1] Now after these things, in the reign of Artaxerxes king of Persia, Ezra the son of Seraiah,\r\nthe son of Azariah, the son of Hilkiah,[2] The son of Shallum, the son of Zadok, the son of\r\nAhitub,[3] The son of Amariah, the son of Azariah, the son of Meraioth,[4] The son of\r\nZerahiah, the son of Uzzi, the son of Bukki,[5] The son of Abishua, the son of Phinehas, the son\r\nof Eleazar, the son of Aaron the chief priest:[6] This Ezra went up from Babylon; and he was a\r\nready scribe in the law of Moses, which the Lord God of Israel had given: and the king granted\r\nhim all his request, according to the hand of the Lord his God upon him.[7] And there went up\r\nsome of the children of Israel, and of the priests, and the Levites, and the singers, and the\r\nporters, and the Nethinims, unto Jerusalem, in the seventh year of Artaxerxes the king.[8]\r\nAnd he came to Jerusalem in the fifth month, which was in the seventh year of the king.[9] For\r\nupon the first day of the first month began he to go up from Babylon, and on the first day of\r\nthe fifth month came he to Jerusalem, according to the good hand of his God upon\r\nhim.[10]For Ezra had prepared his heart to seek the law of the Lord, and to do it, and to\r\nteach in Israel statutes and judgments.[11] Now this is the copy of the letter that the king\r\nArtaxerxes gave unto Ezra the priest, the scribe, even a scribe of the words of the\r\ncommandments of the Lord, and of his statutes to Israel.[12] Artaxerxes, king of kings, unto\r\nEzra the priest, a scribe of the law of the God of heaven, perfect peace, and at such a time.[13]\r\nI make a decree, that all they of the people of Israel, and of his priests and Levites, in my\r\nrealm, which are minded of their own freewill to go up to Jerusalem, go with thee.[14]\r\nForasmuch as thou art sent of the king, and of his seven counsellors, to enquire concerning\r\nJudah and Jerusalem, according to the law of thy God which is in thine hand;[15] And to carry\r\nthe silver and gold, which the king and his counsellors have freely offered unto the God of\r\nIsrael, whose habitation is in Jerusalem,[16] And all the silver and gold that thou canst find in\r\nall the province of Babylon, with the freewill offering of the people, and of the priests,\r\noffering willingly for the house of their God which is in Jerusalem:[17] That thou mayest buy\r\nspeedily with this money bullocks, rams, lambs, with their meat offerings and their drink\r\nofferings, and offer them upon the altar of the house of your God which is in Jerusalem.[18]\r\nAnd whatsoever shall seem good to thee, and to thy brethren, to do with the rest of the silver\r\nand the gold, that do after the will of your God.[19] The vessels also that are given thee for\r\nthe service of the house of thy God, those deliver thou before the God of Jerusalem.[20] And\r\nwhatsoever more shall be needful for the house of thy God, which thou shalt have occasion to\r\nbestow, bestow it out of the king\'s treasure house.[21] And I, even I Artaxerxes the king, do\r\nmake a decree to all the treasurers which are beyond the river, that whatsoever Ezra the\r\npriest, the scribe of the law of the God of heaven, shall require of you, it be done speedily,[22]\r\nUnto an hundred talents of silver, and to an hundred measures of wheat, and to an hundred\r\nbaths of wine, and to an hundred baths of oil, and salt without prescribing how much.[23]\r\nWhatsoever is commanded by the God of heaven, let it be diligently done for the house of the\r\nGod of heaven: for why should there be wrath against the realm of the king and his sons?[24]\r\nAlso we certify you, that touching any of the priests and Levites, singers, porters, Nethinims,\r\nor ministers of this house of God, it shall not be lawful to impose toll, tribute, or custom, upon\r\nthem.[25] And thou, Ezra, after the wisdom of thy God, that is in thine hand, set magistrates\r\nand judges, which may judge all the people that are beyond the river, all such as know the\r\nlaws of thy God; and teach ye them that know them not.[26] And whosoever will not do the\r\nlaw of thy God, and the law of the king, let judgment be executed speedily upon him, whether\r\nit be unto death, or to banishment, or to confiscation of goods, or to imprisonment.[27]\r\nBlessed be the Lord God of our fathers, which hath put such a thing as this in the king\'s heart,\r\nto beautify the house of the Lord which is in Jerusalem:[28] And hath extended mercy unto\r\nme before the king, and his counsellors, and before all the king\'s mighty princes. And I was\r\nstrengthened as the hand of the Lord my God was upon me, and I gathered together out of\r\nIsrael chief men to go up with me.', 1, 2018, '2019-03-03', '2018-10-03 22:30:22'),
(64, 'Week 28: 10-16 March 2019', 'Recruiting Ministers for Revival', 'Ezra 8:1-20', '[1]These are now the chief of their fathers, and this is the genealogy of them that went up\r\nwith me from Babylon, in the reign of Artaxerxes the king.[2] Of the sons of Phinehas;\r\nGershom: of the sons of Ithamar; Daniel: of the sons of David; Hattush.[3] Of the sons of\r\nShechaniah, of the sons of Pharosh; Zechariah: and with him were reckoned by genealogy of\r\nthe males an hundred and fifty.[4] Of the sons of Pahathmoab; Elihoenai the son of Zerahiah,\r\nand with him two hundred males.[5] Of the sons of Shechaniah; the son of Jahaziel, and with\r\nhim three hundred males.[6] Of the sons also of Adin; Ebed the son of Jonathan, and with him\r\nfifty males.[7] And of the sons of Elam; Jeshaiah the son of Athaliah, and with him seventy\r\nmales.[8] And of the sons of Shephatiah; Zebadiah the son of Michael, and with him\r\nfourscore males.[9] Of the sons of Joab; Obadiah the son of Jehiel, and with him two hundred\r\nand eighteen males.[10] And of the sons of Shelomith; the son of Josiphiah, and with him an\r\nhundred and threescore males.[11] And of the sons of Bebai; Zechariah the son of Bebai, and\r\nwith him twenty and eight males.[12] And of the sons of Azgad; Johanan the son of\r\nHakkatan, and with him an hundred and ten males.[13] And of the last sons of Adonikam,\r\nwhose names are these, Eliphelet, Jeiel, and Shemaiah, and with them threescore males.[14]\r\nOf the sons also of Bigvai; Uthai, and Zabbud, and with them seventy males.[15] And I\r\ngathered them together to the river that runneth to Ahava; and there abode we in tents three\r\ndays: and I viewed the people, and the priests, and found there none of the sons of Levi.[16]\r\nThen sent I for Eliezer, for Ariel, for Shemaiah, and for Elnathan, and for Jarib, and for\r\nElnathan, and for Nathan, and for Zechariah, and for Meshullam, chief men; also for Joiarib,\r\nand for Elnathan, men of understanding.[17] And I sent them with commandment unto Iddo\r\nthe chief at the place Casiphia, and I told them what they should say unto Iddo, and to his\r\nbrethren the Nethinims, at the place Casiphia, that they should bring unto us ministers for\r\nthe house of our God.[18] And by the good hand of our God upon us they brought us a man of\r\nunderstanding, of the sons of Mahli, the son of Levi, the son of Israel; and Sherebiah, with his\r\nsons and his brethren, eighteen;[19] And Hashabiah, and with him Jeshaiah of the sons of\r\nMerari, his brethren and their sons, twenty;[20] Also of the Nethinims, whom David and the\r\nprinces had appointed for the service of the Levites, two hundred and twenty Nethinims: all\r\nof them were expressed by name.', 1, 2018, '2019-03-10', '2018-10-04 03:00:32'),
(65, 'Week 29: 17-23 March 2019', 'Spiritual Preparation for the Journey of Revival', 'Ezra 8:21-23', '[21] Then I proclaimed a fast there, at the river of Ahava, that we might afflict ourselves\r\nbefore our God, to seek of him a right way for us, and for our little ones, and for all our\r\nsubstance.[22] For I was ashamed to require of the king a band of soldiers and horsemen to\r\nhelp us against the enemy in the way: because we had spoken unto the king, saying, The\r\nhand of our God is upon all them for good that seek him; but his power and his wrath is\r\nagainst all them that forsake him.[23] So we fasted and besought our God for this: and he\r\nwas intreated of us.', 1, 2018, '2019-03-17', '2018-10-04 03:00:32'),
(66, 'Week 30: 24-30 March 2019:', 'Fellowship Reflection & Tarry Meeting', '', '', 1, 2018, '2019-03-24', '2018-10-04 03:00:32'),
(67, 'Week 31 & 32: 31 March – 13 April 2019', 'Requirement for Separation in the Call of Revival and Rebuilding', 'Ezra 9', '[1]Now when these things were done, the princes came to me, saying, The people of Israel,\r\nand the priests, and the Levites, have not separated themselves from the people of the lands,\r\ndoing according to their abominations, even of the Canaanites, the Hittites, the Perizzites,\r\nthe Jebusites, the Ammonites, the Moabites, the Egyptians, and the Amorites.[2] For they\r\nhave taken of their daughters for themselves, and for their sons: so that the holy seed have\r\nmingled themselves with the people of those lands: yea, the hand of the princes and rulers\r\nhath been chief in this trespass.[3] And when I heard this thing, I rent my garment and my\r\nmantle, and plucked off the hair of my head and of my beard, and sat down astonied.[4] Then\r\nwere assembled unto me every one that trembled at the words of the God of Israel, because\r\nof the transgression of those that had been carried away; and I sat astonied until the evening\r\nsacrifice.[5] And at the evening sacrifice I arose up from my heaviness; and having rent my\r\ngarment and my mantle, I fell upon my knees, and spread out my hands unto the Lord my\r\nGod,[6] And said, O my God, I am ashamed and blush to lift up my face to thee, my God: for\r\nour iniquities are increased over our head, and our trespass is grown up unto the heavens.[7]\r\nSince the days of our fathers have we been in a great trespass unto this day; and for our\r\niniquities have we, our kings, and our priests, been delivered into the hand of the kings of the\r\nlands, to the sword, to captivity, and to a spoil, and to confusion of face, as it is this day.[8]\r\nAnd now for a little space grace hath been shewed from the Lord our God, to leave us a\r\nremnant to escape, and to give us a nail in his holy place, that our God may lighten our eyes,\r\nand give us a little reviving in our bondage.[9] For we were bondmen; yet our God hath not\r\nforsaken us in our bondage, but hath extended mercy unto us in the sight of the kings of\r\nPersia, to give us a reviving, to set up the house of our God, and to repair the desolations\r\nthereof, and to give us a wall in Judah and in Jerusalem.[10] And now, O our God, what shall\r\nwe say after this? for we have forsaken thy commandments,[11] Which thou hast\r\ncommanded by thy servants the prophets, saying, The land, unto which ye go to possess it, is\r\nan unclean land with the filthiness of the people of the lands, with their abominations, which\r\nhave filled it from one end to another with their uncleanness.[12] Now therefore give not\r\nyour daughters unto their sons, neither take their daughters unto your sons, nor seek their\r\npeace or their wealth for ever: that ye may be strong, and eat the good of the land, and leave\r\nit for an inheritance to your children for ever.[13] And after all that is come upon us for our evil\r\ndeeds, and for our great trespass, seeing that thou our God hast punished us less than our\r\niniquities deserve, and hast given us such deliverance as this;[14] Should we again break thy\r\ncommandments, and join in affinity with the people of these abominations? wouldest not\r\nthou be angry with us till thou hadst consumed us, so that there should be no remnant nor\r\nescaping?[15] O Lord God of Israel, thou art righteous: for we remain yet escaped, as it is this\r\nday: behold, we are before thee in our trespasses: for we cannot stand before thee because of\r\nthis.', 2, 2018, '2019-03-31', '2018-10-04 03:00:32'),
(68, 'Week 33:14-20 April 2019', 'Activating Revival through Repentance and Restitution', 'Ezra 10', '[1]Now when Ezra had prayed, and when he had confessed, weeping and casting himself\r\ndown before the house of God, there assembled unto him out of Israel a very great\r\ncongregation of men and women and children: for the people wept very sore.[2] And\r\nShechaniah the son of Jehiel, one of the sons of Elam, answered and said unto Ezra, We have\r\ntrespassed against our God, and have taken strange wives of the people of the land: yet now\r\nthere is hope in Israel concerning this thing.[3] Now, therefore, let us make a covenant with\r\nour God to put away all the wives, and such as are born of them, according to the counsel of\r\nmy lord, and of those that tremble at the commandment of our God; and let it be done\r\naccording to the law.[4] Arise; for this matter belongeth unto thee: we also will be with thee:\r\nbe of good courage, and do it.[5] Then arose Ezra, and made the chief priests, the Levites, and\r\nall Israel, to swear that they should do according to this word. And they sware.[6] Then Ezra\r\nrose up from before the house of God, and went into the chamber of Johanan the son of\r\nEliashib: and when he came thither, he did eat no bread, nor drink water: for he mourned\r\nbecause of the transgression of them that had been carried away.[7] And they made\r\nproclamation throughout Judah and Jerusalem unto all the children of the captivity, that they\r\nshould gather themselves together unto Jerusalem;[8] And that whosoever would not come\r\nwithin three days, according to the counsel of the princes and the elders, all his substance\r\nshould be forfeited, and himself separated from the congregation of those that had been\r\ncarried away.[9] Then all the men of Judah and Benjamin gathered themselves together unto\r\nJerusalem within three days. It was the ninth month, on the twentieth day of the month; and\r\nall the people sat in the street of the house of God, trembling because of this matter, and for\r\nthe great rain.[10] And Ezra the priest stood up, and said unto them, Ye have transgressed,\r\nand have taken strange wives, to increase the trespass of Israel.[11] Now therefore make\r\nconfession unto the Lord God of your fathers, and do his pleasure: and separate yourselves\r\nfrom the people of the land, and from the strange wives.[12] Then all the congregation\r\nanswered and said with a loud voice, As thou hast said, so must we do.[13] But the people are\r\nmany, and it is a time of much rain, and we are not able to stand without, neither is this a work\r\nof one day or two: for we are many that have transgressed in this thing.[14] Let now our rulers\r\nof all the congregation stand, and let all them which have taken strange wives in our cities\r\ncome at appointed times, and with them the elders of every city, and the judges thereof, until\r\nthe fierce wrath of our God for this matter be turned from us.[15] Only Jonathan the son of\r\nAsahel and Jahaziah the son of Tikvah were employed about this matter: and Meshullam and\r\nShabbethai the Levite helped them.[16] And the children of the captivity did so. And Ezra the\r\npriest, with certain chief of the fathers, after the house of their fathers, and all of them by\r\ntheir names, were separated, and sat down in the first day of the tenth month to examine the\r\nmatter.[17] And they made an end with all the men that had taken strange wives by the first\r\nday of the first month.[18] And among the sons of the priests there were found that had taken\r\nstrange wives: namely, of the sons of Jeshua the son of Jozadak, and his brethren; Maaseiah,\r\nand Eliezer, and Jarib, and Gedaliah.[19] And they gave their hands that they would put away\r\ntheir wives; and being guilty, they offered a ram of the flock for their trespass.[20] And of the\r\nsons of Immer; Hanani, and Zebadiah.[21] And of the sons of Harim; Maaseiah, and Elijah,\r\nand Shemaiah, and Jehiel, and Uzziah.[22] And of the sons of Pashur; Elioenai, Maaseiah,\r\nIshmael, Nethaneel, Jozabad, and Elasah.[23] Also of the Levites; Jozabad, and Shimei, and\r\nKelaiah, (the same is Kelita,) Pethahiah, Judah, and Eliezer.[24] Of the singers also; Eliashib:\r\nand of the porters; Shallum, and Telem, and Uri.[25] Moreover of Israel: of the sons of Parosh;\r\nRamiah, and Jeziah, and Malchiah, and Miamin, and Eleazar, and Malchijah, and\r\nBenaiah.[26] And of the sons of Elam; Mattaniah, Zechariah, and Jehiel, and Abdi, and\r\nJeremoth, and Eliah.[27] And of the sons of Zattu; Elioenai, Eliashib, Mattaniah, and\r\nJeremoth, and Zabad, and Aziza.[28] Of the sons also of Bebai; Jehohanan, Hananiah, Zabbai,\r\nand Athlai.[29] And of the sons of Bani; Meshullam, Malluch, and Adaiah, Jashub, and Sheal,\r\nand Ramoth.[30] And of the sons of Pahathmoab; Adna, and Chelal, Benaiah, Maaseiah,\r\nMattaniah, Bezaleel, and Binnui, and Manasseh.[31] And of the sons of Harim; Eliezer,\r\nIshijah, Malchiah, Shemaiah, Shimeon,[32] Benjamin, Malluch, and Shemariah.[33] Of the\r\nsons of Hashum; Mattenai, Mattathah, Zabad, Eliphelet, Jeremai, Manasseh, and\r\nShimei.[34] Of the sons of Bani; Maadai, Amram, and Uel,[35] Benaiah, Bedeiah,\r\nChelluh,[36] Vaniah, Meremoth, Eliashib,[37] Mattaniah, Mattenai, and Jaasau,[38] And\r\nBani, and Binnui, Shimei,[39] And Shelemiah, and Nathan, and Adaiah,[40] Machnadebai,\r\nShashai, Sharai,[41] Azareel, and Shelemiah, Shemariah,[42] Shallum, Amariah, and\r\nJoseph.[43] Of the sons of Nebo; Jeiel, Mattithiah, Zabad, Zebina, Jadau, and Joel,\r\nBenaiah.[44] All these had taken strange wives: and some of them had wives by whom they\r\nhad children.', 1, 2018, '2018-10-14', '2018-10-04 03:04:29'),
(69, 'Week 34: 21-27 April 2019', 'Nehemiah: Carrying Revival Burden in the King\'s Palace', 'Nehemiah 1:1-3', '[1]The words of Nehemiah the son of Hachaliah. And it came to pass in the month of Chislev,\r\nin the twentieth year, as I was in the palace at Shushan,[2] that Hanani one of my brethren\r\ncame, he and certain men of Judah; and I asked them concerning the Jews who had escaped,\r\nwho were left behind from the captivity, and concerning Jerusalem.[3] And they said unto\r\nme, “The remnant who are left behind from the captivity there in the province are in great\r\naffliction and reproach. The wall of Jerusalem also is broken down, and the gates thereof are\r\nburned with fire”.', 1, 2018, '2019-04-21', '2018-10-04 03:04:29'),
(70, 'Week 35: 28 April- 4 May 2019', 'Fellowship Reflection & Tarry Meeting', '', '', 1, 2018, '2019-04-28', '2018-10-04 03:08:48'),
(71, 'Week 36: 5-11 May 2019', 'Nehemiah: From Cup Bearer to Burden Bearer', 'Nehemiah 1:4', 'And it came to pass when I heard these words, that I sat down and wept, and mourned\r\ncertain days and fasted, and prayed before the God of heaven', 1, 2018, '2019-05-05', '2018-10-04 03:08:48'),
(72, 'Week 37: 12-18 May 2019', 'Preparation for the mandate of Revival', 'Nehemiah 1:4-11', '[4]And it came to pass, when I heard these words, that I sat down and wept, and mourned\r\ncertain days, and fasted, and prayed before the God of heaven,[5]And said, I beseech thee, O\r\nLORD God of heaven, the great and terrible God, that keepeth covenant and mercy for them\r\nthat love him and observe his commandments:[6]Let thine ear now be attentive, and thine\r\neyes open, that thou mayest hear the prayer of thy servant, which I pray before thee now, day\r\nand night, for the children of Israel thy servants, and confess the sins of the children of Israel,\r\nwhich we have sinned against thee: both I and my father\'s house have sinned.[7]We have\r\ndealt very corruptly against thee, and have not kept the commandments, nor the statutes,\r\nnor the judgments, which thou commandedst thy servant Moses.[8]Remember, I beseech\r\nthee, the word that thou commandedst thy servant Moses, saying, If ye transgress, I will\r\nscatter you abroad among the nations:[9]But if ye turn unto me, and keep my\r\ncommandments, and do them; though there were of you cast out unto the uttermost part of\r\nthe heaven, yet will I gather them from thence, and will bring them unto the place that I have\r\nchosen to set my name there.[10]Now these are thy servants and thy people, whom thou\r\nhast redeemed by thy great power, and by thy strong hand.[11]O Lord, I beseech thee, let\r\nnow thine ear be attentive to the prayer of thy servant, and to the prayer of thy servants, who\r\ndesire to fear thy name: and prosper, I pray thee, thy servant this day, and grant him mercy in\r\nthe sight of this man. For I was the king\'s cupbearer.', 1, 2018, '2019-05-12', '2018-10-04 03:08:48'),
(73, 'Week 38: 19-25 May 2019', 'Dynamics of Communication in Activating Revival', 'Nehemiah 2:1-5', '[1]And it came to pass in the month Nisan, in the twentieth year of Artaxerxes the king, that\r\nwine was before him: and I took up the wine, and gave it unto the king. Now I had not been\r\nbeforetime sad in his presence.[2]Wherefore the king said unto me, Why is thy countenance\r\nsad, seeing thou art not sick? this is nothing else but sorrow of heart. Then I was very sore\r\nafraid,[3]And said unto the king, Let the king live for ever: why should not my countenance be\r\nsad, when the city, the place of my fathers\' sepulchres, lieth waste, and the gates thereof are\r\nconsumed with fire?[4]Then the king said unto me, For what dost thou make request? So I\r\nprayed to the God of heaven.[5]And I said unto the king, If it please the king, and if thy servant\r\nhave found favour in thy sight, that thou wouldest send me unto Judah, unto the city of my\r\nfathers\' sepulchres, that I may build it.', 1, 2018, '2019-05-19', '2018-10-04 03:08:48'),
(74, 'Week 39: 26 May-1 June 2019', 'Fellowship Reflection & Tarry Meeting', '', '', 1, 2018, '2019-05-26', '2018-10-04 03:14:20'),
(75, 'Week 40: 2-8 June 2019', 'Planning and Counting the Cost: A Critical Process in Rebuilding', 'Nehemiah 2:11-18', '[11]So I came to Jerusalem, and was there three days.[12]And I arose in the night, I and some\r\nfew men with me; neither told I any man what my God had put in my heart to do at Jerusalem:\r\nneither was there any beast with me, save the beast that I rode upon.[13]And I went out by\r\nnight by the gate of the valley, even before the dragon well, and to the dung port, and viewed\r\nthe walls of Jerusalem, which were broken down, and the gates thereof were consumed with\r\nfire.[14]Then I went on to the gate of the fountain, and to the king\'s pool: but there was no\r\nplace for the beast that was under me to pass.[15]Then went I up in the night by the brook,\r\nand viewed the wall, and turned back, and entered by the gate of the valley, and so\r\nreturned.[16]And the rulers knew not whither I went, or what I did; neither had I as yet told it\r\nto the Jews, nor to the priests, nor to the nobles, nor to the rulers, nor to the rest that did the\r\nwork.[17]Then said I unto them, Ye see the distress that we are in, how Jerusalem lieth waste,\r\nand the gates thereof are burned with fire: come, and let us build up the wall of Jerusalem,\r\nthat we be no more a reproach.[18]Then I told them of the hand of my God which was good\r\nupon me; as also the king\'s words that he had spoken unto me. And they said, Let us rise up\r\nand build. So they strengthened their hands for this good work.', 1, 2018, '2019-06-02', '2018-10-04 03:14:20'),
(76, 'Week 41: 9-15 June 2019', 'Effective Delegation in Doing God\'s Work', 'Nehemiah 3', '[1]Then Eliashib the high priest rose up with his brethren the priests, and they built the Sheep\r\nGate. They sanctified it and set up the doors of it; even unto the Tower of Meah they sanctified\r\nit, unto the Tower of Hananeel.[2] And next to him built the men of Jericho. And next to them\r\nbuilt Zaccur the son of Imri.[3] But the Fish Gate did the sons of Hassenaah build, who also laid\r\nthe beams thereof and set up the doors thereof, the locks thereof and the bars thereof.[4] And\r\nnext unto them repaired Meremoth the son of Urijah, the son of Koz. And next unto them\r\nrepaired Meshullam the son of Berechiah, the son of Meshezabeel. And next unto them\r\nrepaired Zadok the son of Baana.[5] And next unto them the Tekoites repaired; but their\r\nnobles put not their necks to the work of their Lord.[6] Moreover Jehoiada the son of Paseah\r\nand Meshullam the son of Besodeiah repaired the Old Gate; they laid the beams thereof, and\r\nset up the doors thereof and the locks thereof and the bars thereof.[7] And next unto them\r\nMelatiah the Gibeonite and Jadon the Meronothite, the men of Gibeon and of Mizpah,\r\nrepaired unto the throne of the governor on this side of the river.[8] Next unto him Uzziel the\r\nson of Harhaiah, of the goldsmiths, repaired. Next unto him also repaired Hananiah the son of\r\none of the apothecaries; and they fortified Jerusalem unto the Broad Wall.[9] And next unto\r\nthem Rephaiah the son of Hur, the ruler of the half part of Jerusalem, repaired.[10] And next\r\nunto them Jedaiah the son of Harumaph repaired, even opposite his house. And next unto him\r\nHattush the son of Hashabniah repaired.[11] Malchijah the son of Harim and Hashub the son\r\nof Pahathmoab repaired the other piece, and the Tower of the Furnaces.[12] And next unto\r\nhim Shallum the son of Hallohesh, the ruler of the half part of Jerusalem, repaired—he and his\r\ndaughters.[13] The Valley Gate was repaired by Hanun and the inhabitants of Zanoah; they\r\nbuilt it and set up the doors thereof, the locks thereof and the bars thereof, and a thousand\r\ncubits on the wall unto the Dung Gate.[14] But Malchijah the son of Rechab, the ruler of part\r\nof Bethhaccerem repaired the Dung Gate; he built it and set up the doors thereof, the locks\r\nthereof and the bars thereof.[15] But the Gate of the Fountain Shallun the son of Colhozeh,\r\nthe ruler of part of Mizpah, repaired; he built it and covered it, and set up the doors thereof,\r\nthe locks thereof and the bars thereof, and the wall of the Pool of Shelah by the king\'s garden\r\nand unto the stairs that go down from the City of David.[16] After him Nehemiah the son of\r\nAzbuk, the ruler of the half part of Bethzur, repaired unto the place opposite the sepulchres of\r\nDavid, and to the pool that was made and unto the House of the Mighty.[17] After him\r\nrepaired the Levites, Rehum the son of Bani. Next unto him repaired Hashabiah, the ruler of\r\nthe half part of Keilah, in his part.[18] After him repaired their brethren, Bavai the son of\r\nHenadad, the ruler of the half part of Keilah.[19] And next to him Ezer the son of Jeshua, the\r\nruler of Mizpah, repaired another piece opposite the ascent to the armory at the turning of\r\nthe wall.[20] After him Baruch the son of Zabbai earnestly repaired the other piece, from the\r\nturning of the wall unto the door of the house of Eliashib the high priest.[21] After him\r\nMeremoth the son of Urijah the son of Koz repaired another piece, from the door of the house\r\nof Eliashib even to the end of the house of Eliashib.[22] And after him repaired the priests, the\r\nmen of the plain.[23] After him repaired Benjamin and Hashub opposite their house. After\r\nhim repaired Azariah the son of Maaseiah, the son of Ananiah, by his house.[24] After him\r\nBinnui the son of Henadad repaired another piece, from the house of Azariah unto the\r\nturning of the wall, even unto the corner.[25] Palal the son of Uzai made repairs opposite the\r\nturning of the wall, and the tower which lieth out from the king\'s high house that was by the\r\ncourt of the prison; after him Pedaiah the son of Parosh.[26] Moreover the Nethinim dwelt in\r\nOphel unto the place opposite the Water Gate toward the east, and the tower that lieth\r\nout.[27] After them the Tekoites repaired another piece, opposite the great tower that lieth\r\nout, even unto the wall of Ophel.[28] From above the Horse Gate repaired the priests, every\r\none opposite his house.[29] After them Zadok the son of Immer repaired opposite his house.\r\nAfter him repaired also Shemaiah the son of Shechaniah, the keeper of the East Gate.[30]\r\nAfter him Hananiah the son of Shelemiah and Hanun the sixth son of Zalaph repaired another\r\npiece. After him repaired Meshullam the son of Berechiah opposite his chamber.[31] After\r\nhim Malchijah the goldsmith\'s son repaired unto the place of the Nethinim and of the\r\nmerchants, opposite the Gate Miphkad and to the ascent of the corner chamber.32 And\r\nbetween the ascent of the corner unto the Sheep Gate repaired the goldsmiths and the\r\nmerchants.', 1, 2018, '2019-06-09', '2018-10-04 03:14:20'),
(77, 'Week 42&43: 16-29 June 2019', 'Opposition and Counter-opposition in Rebuilding', 'Nehemiah 2:19-20& 4:1-23', '[19]But when Sanballat the Horonite, and Tobiah the servant, the Ammonite, and Geshem\r\nthe Arabian, heard it, they laughed us to scorn, and despised us, and said, What is this thing\r\nthat ye do? will ye rebel against the king? [20]Then answered I them, and said unto them, The\r\nGod of heaven, he will prosper us; therefore we his servants will arise and build: but ye have\r\nno portion, nor right, nor memorial, in Jerusalem.<br/><br/>\r\n[1]But it came to pass, that when Sanballat heard that we builded the wall, he was wroth, and\r\ntook great indignation, and mocked the Jews.[2]And he spake before his brethren and the\r\narmy of Samaria, and said, What do these feeble Jews? will they fortify themselves? will they\r\nsacrifice? will they make an end in a day? will they revive the stones out of the heaps of the\r\nrubbish which are burned?[3]Now Tobiah the Ammonite was by him, and he said, Even that\r\nwhich they build, if a fox go up, he shall even break down their stone wall.[4]Hear, O our God;\r\nfor we are despised: and turn their reproach upon their own head, and give them for a prey in\r\nthe land of captivity:[5]And cover not their iniquity, and let not their sin be blotted out from\r\nbefore thee: for they have provoked thee to anger before the builders.[6]So built we the wall;\r\nand all the wall was joined together unto the half thereof: for the people had a mind to\r\nwork.[7]But it came to pass, that when Sanballat, and Tobiah, and the Arabians, and the\r\nAmmonites, and the Ashdodites, heard that the walls of Jerusalem were made up, and that\r\nthe breaches began to be stopped, then they were very wroth,[8]And conspired all of them\r\ntogether to come and to fight against Jerusalem, and to hinder it.[9]Nevertheless we made\r\nour prayer unto our God, and set a watch against them day and night, because of\r\nthem.[10]And Judah said, The strength of the bearers of burdens is decayed, and there is\r\nmuch rubbish; so that we are not able to build the wall.[11]And our adversaries said, They\r\nshall not know, neither see, till we come in the midst among them, and slay them, and cause\r\nthe work to cease.[12]And it came to pass, that when the Jews which dwelt by them came,\r\nthey said unto us ten times, From all places whence ye shall return unto us they will be upon\r\nyou.[13]Therefore set I in the lower places behind the wall, and on the higher places, I even set\r\nthe people after their families with their swords, their spears, and their bows.[14]And I\r\nlooked, and rose up, and said unto the nobles, and to the rulers, and to the rest of the people,\r\nBe not ye afraid of them: remember the Lord, which is great and terrible, and fight for your\r\nbrethren, your sons, and your daughters, your wives, and your houses.[15]And it came to\r\npass, when our enemies heard that it was known unto us, and God had brought their counsel\r\nto nought, that we returned all of us to the wall, every one unto his work.[16]And it came to\r\npass from that time forth, that the half of my servants wrought in the work, and the other half\r\nof them held both the spears, the shields, and the bows, and the habergeons; and the rulers\r\nwere behind all the house of Judah.[17]They which builded on the wall, and they that bare\r\nburdens, with those that laded, everyone with one of his hands wrought in the work, and with\r\nthe other hand held a weapon.[18]For the builders, everyone had his sword girded by his\r\nside, and so builded. And he that sounded the trumpet was by me.[19]And I said unto the\r\nnobles, and to the rulers, and to the rest of the people, The work is great and large, and we\r\nare separated upon the wall, one far from another.[20]In what place therefore ye hear the\r\nsound of the trumpet, resort ye thither unto us: our God shall fight for us.[21]So we laboured\r\nin the work: and half of them held the spears from the rising of the morning till the stars\r\nappeared.[22]Likewise at the same time said I unto the people, Let everyone with his servant\r\nlodge within Jerusalem, that in the night they may be a guard to us, and labour on the\r\nday.[23]So neither I, nor my brethren, nor my servants, nor the men of the guard which\r\nfollowed me, none of us put off our clothes, saving that everyone put them off for washing.', 2, 2018, '2019-06-16', '2018-10-04 03:14:20'),
(78, 'Week 44: 30 June- 6 July', 'Fellowship Reflection & Tarry Meeting', '', '', 1, 2018, '2019-06-30', '2018-10-04 03:16:45'),
(79, 'Week 45&46: 7-20 July 2019', 'The Walls of Jerusalem Completed', 'Nehemiah 6', '[1]Now it came to pass, when Sanballat and Tobiah and Geshem the Arabian and the rest of\r\nour enemies heard that I had built the wall and that there was no breach left therein (though\r\nat that time I had not set up the doors upon the gates),[2] that Sanballat and Geshem sent\r\nunto me, saying, “Come, let us meet together in one of the villages in the plain of Ono.” But\r\nthey thought to do me mischief.[3] And I sent messengers unto them, saying, “I am doing a\r\ngreat work, so that I cannot come down. Why should the work cease, whilst I leave it and\r\ncome down to you?”[4] Yet they sent unto me four times in this manner, and I answered them\r\nin the same manner.[5] Then Sanballat sent his servant unto me in like manner the fifth time\r\nwith an open letter in his hand,[6] wherein was written: “It is reported among the heathen,\r\nand Geshem saith it, that thou and the Jews think to rebel; for which cause thou buildest the\r\nwall, that thou mayest be their king according to these words.[7] And thou hast also\r\nappointed prophets to preach of thee at Jerusalem, saying, \'There is a king in Judah!\' And now\r\nshall it be reported to the king according to these words. Come now therefore, and let us take\r\ncounsel together.”[8] Then I sent unto him, saying, “There are no such things done as thou\r\nsayest, but thou feignest them out of thine own heart.”[9] For they all made us afraid, saying,\r\n“Their hands shall be weakened from the work, that it be not done.” Now therefore, O God,\r\nstrengthen my hands.[10] Afterward I came unto the house of Shemaiah the son of Delaiah\r\nthe son of Mehetabeel, who was shut up; and he said, “Let us meet together in the house of\r\nGod, within the temple, and let us shut the doors of the temple; for they will come to slay thee,\r\nyea, in the night will they come to slay thee.”[11] And I said, “Should such a man as I flee? And\r\nwho is there that, being as I am, would go into the temple to save his life? I will not go in.”[12]\r\nAnd lo, I perceived that God had not sent him, but that he pronounced this prophecy against\r\nme; for Tobiah and Sanballat had hired him.[13] Therefore was he hired, that I should be\r\nafraid, and do so, and sin, and that they might have cause for an evil report, that they might\r\nreproach me.[14] My God, think Thou upon Tobiah and Sanballat according to these their\r\nworks, and on the prophetess Noadiah and the rest of the prophets who would have put me in\r\nfear.[15] So the wall was finished in the twenty and fifth day of the month of Elul, in fifty and\r\ntwo days.[16] And it came to pass that when all our enemies heard thereof, and all the\r\nheathen who were about us saw these things, they were much cast down in their own eyes;\r\nfor they perceived that this work was wrought by our God.[17] Moreover in those days the\r\nnobles of Judah sent many letters unto Tobiah, and the letters of Tobiah came unto them.[18]\r\nFor there were many in Judah sworn unto him, because he was the son-in-law of Shechaniah\r\nthe son of Arah, and his son Jehohanan had taken the daughter of Meshullam the son of\r\nBerechiah.[19] Also they reported his good deeds before me, and uttered my words to him.\r\nAnd Tobiah sent letters to put me in fear.', 2, 2018, '2019-07-07', '2018-10-04 03:16:45'),
(80, 'Week 47: 21- 27 July 2019', 'Fellowship Reflection & Tarry Meeting', '', '', 1, 2018, '2019-07-21', '2018-10-04 03:22:44'),
(81, 'Week 48 &49: 28 July -10 August 2019', 'Watchmen On the Walls', 'Nehemiah 7', '[1]Then it was, when the wall was built and I had hung the doors, when the gatekeepers, the\r\nsingers, and the Levites had been appointed, [2] that I gave the charge of Jerusalem to my\r\nbrother Hanani, and Hananiah the leader of the [a]citadel, for he was a faithful man and\r\nfeared God more than many.[3] And I said to them, “Do not let the gates of Jerusalem be\r\nopened until the sun is hot; and while they stand guard, let them shut and bar the doors; and\r\nappoint guards from among the inhabitants of Jerusalem, one at his watch station and\r\nanother in front of his own house.”[4] Now the city was large and spacious, but the people in it\r\nwere few, and the houses were not rebuilt. [5] Then my God put it into my heart to gather the\r\nnobles, the rulers, and the people, that they might be registered by genealogy. And I found a\r\nregister of the genealogy of those who had come up in the first return, and found written in\r\nit:[6] These are the people of the province who came back from the captivity, of those who\r\nhad been carried away, whom Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon had carried away, and\r\nwho returned to Jerusalem and Judah, everyone to his city.[7] Those who came with\r\nZerubbabel were Jeshua, Nehemiah, [b]Azariah, Raamiah, Nahamani, Mordecai, Bilshan,\r\n[c]Mispereth, Bigvai, Nehum, and Baanah.The number of the men of the people of Israel: [8]\r\nthe sons of Parosh, two thousand one hundred and seventy-two;[9] the sons of Shephatiah,\r\nthree hundred and seventy-two;[10] the sons of Arah, six hundred and fifty-two;[11] the sons\r\nof Pahath-Moab, of the sons of Jeshua and Joab, two thousand eight hundred and\r\neighteen;[12] the sons of Elam, one thousand two hundred and fifty-four;[13] the sons of\r\nZattu, eight hundred and forty-five;[14] the sons of Zaccai, seven hundred and sixty;[15] the\r\nsons of [d]Binnui, six hundred and forty-eight;[16] the sons of Bebai, six hundred and twentyeight;[\r\n17] the sons of Azgad, two thousand three hundred and twenty-two;[18] the sons of\r\nAdonikam, six hundred and sixty-seven;[19] the sons of Bigvai, two thousand and sixtyseven;[\r\n20] the sons of Adin, six hundred and fifty-five;[21] the sons of Ater of Hezekiah,\r\nninety-eight;[22] the sons of Hashum, three hundred and twenty-eight;[23] the sons of Bezai,\r\nthree hundred and twenty-four;[24] the sons of [e]Hariph, one hundred and twelve;[25] the\r\nsons of [f]Gibeon, ninety-five;[26] the men of Bethlehem and Netophah, one hundred and\r\neighty-eight;[27] the men of Anathoth, one hundred and twenty-eight;[28] the men of\r\n[g]Beth Azmaveth, forty-two;[29] the men of [h]Kirjath Jearim, Chephirah, and Beeroth,\r\nseven hundred and forty-three;[30] the men of Ramah and Geba, six hundred and twentyone;[\r\n31] the men of Michmas, one hundred and twenty-two;[32] the men of Bethel and Ai,\r\none hundred and twenty-three;[33] the men of the other Nebo, fifty-two;[34] the sons of the\r\nother Elam, one thousand two hundred and fifty-four;[35] the sons of Harim, three hundred\r\nand twenty;[36] the sons of Jericho, three hundred and forty-five;[37] the sons of Lod, Hadid,\r\nand Ono, seven hundred and twenty-one;[38] the sons of Senaah, three thousand nine\r\nhundred and thirty.[39] The priests: the sons of Jedaiah, of the house of Jeshua, nine hundred\r\nand seventy-three;[40] the sons of Immer, one thousand and fifty-two;[41] the sons of\r\nPashhur, one thousand two hundred and forty-seven;[42] the sons of Harim, one thousand\r\nand seventeen.[43] The Levites: the sons of Jeshua, of Kadmiel,and of the sons of [i]Hodevah,\r\nseventy-four.[44] The singers: the sons of Asaph, one hundred and forty-eight.[45] The\r\ngatekeepers: the sons of Shallum,the sons of Ater,the sons of Talmon,the sons of Akkub,the\r\nsons of Hatita,the sons of Shobai, one hundred and thirty-eight.[46] The Nethinim: the sons\r\nof Ziha,the sons of Hasupha,the sons of Tabbaoth,[47] the sons of Keros,the sons of [j]Sia,the\r\nsons of Padon,[48] the sons of [k]Lebana,the sons of [l]Hagaba,the sons of [m]Salmai,[49]\r\nthe sons of Hanan,the sons of Giddel,the sons of Gahar,[50] the sons of Reaiah,the sons of\r\nRezin,the sons of Nekoda,[51] the sons of Gazzam,the sons of Uzza,the sons of Paseah,[52]\r\nthe sons of Besai,the sons of Meunim,the sons of [n]Nephishesim,[53] the sons of Bakbuk,the\r\nsons of Hakupha,the sons of Harhur,[54] the sons of [o]Bazlith,the sons of Mehida,the sons of\r\nHarsha,[55] the sons of Barkos,the sons of Sisera,the sons of Tamah,[56] the sons of\r\nNeziah,and the sons of Hatipha.[57] The sons of Solomon\'s servants: the sons of Sotai,the\r\nsons of Sophereth,the sons of [p]Perida,[58] the sons of Jaala,the sons of Darkon,the sons of\r\nGiddel,[59] the sons of Shephatiah,the sons of Hattil,the sons of Pochereth of Zebaim,and the\r\nsons of [q]Amon.[60] All the Nethinim, and the sons of Solomon\'s servants, were three\r\nhundred and ninety-two.[61] And these were the ones who came up from Tel Melah, Tel\r\nHarsha, Cherub, [r]Addon, and Immer, but they could not identify their father\'s house nor\r\ntheir lineage, whether they were of Israel: [62] the sons of Delaiah,the sons of Tobiah,the sons\r\nof Nekoda, six hundred and forty-two;[63] and of the priests: the sons of Habaiah,the sons of\r\n[s]Koz,the sons of Barzillai, who took a wife of the daughters of Barzillai the Gileadite, and\r\nwas called by their name.[64] These sought their listing among those who were registered by\r\ngenealogy, but it was not found; therefore they were excluded from the priesthood as defiled.\r\n[65] And the [t]governor said to them that they should not eat of the most holy things till a\r\npriest could consult with the Urim and Thummim.[66] Altogether the whole assembly was\r\nforty-two thousand three hundred and sixty, [67] besides their male and female servants, of\r\nwhom there were seven thousand three hundred and thirty-seven; and they had two\r\nhundred and forty-five men and women singers. [68] Their horses were seven hundred and\r\nthirty-six, their mules two hundred and forty-five, [69] their camels four hundred and thirtyfive,\r\nand donkeys six thousand seven hundred and twenty.[70] And some of the heads of the\r\nfathers\' houses gave to the work. The [u]governor gave to the treasury one thousand gold\r\ndrachmas, fifty basins, and five hundred and thirty priestly garments. [71] Some of the heads\r\nof the fathers\' houses gave to the treasury of the work twenty thousand gold drachmas, and\r\ntwo thousand two hundred silver minas. [72] And that which the rest of the people gave was\r\ntwenty thousand gold drachmas, two thousand silver minas, and sixty-seven priestly\r\ngarments.[73] So the priests, the Levites, the gatekeepers, the singers, some of the people,\r\nthe Nethinim, and all Israel dwelt in their cities.When the seventh month came, the children\r\nof Israel were in their cities.', 2, 2018, '2019-07-28', '2018-10-04 03:22:44'),
(82, 'Week 50: 11-17 August 2019', 'The Place of the Word and Spirit in Revival', 'Nehemiah 8', '[1]And all the people gathered themselves together as one man into the street that was\r\nbefore the Water Gate; and they spoke unto Ezra the scribe to bring the Book of the Law of\r\nMoses, which the Lord had commanded to Israel.[2] And Ezra the priest brought the law\r\nbefore the congregation both of men and women, and all who could hear with\r\nunderstanding, upon the first day of the seventh month.[3] And he read therein before the\r\nstreet that was before the Water Gate from the morning until midday, before the men and the\r\nwomen and those who could understand; and the ears of all the people were attentive unto\r\nthe Book of the Law.[4] And Ezra the scribe stood upon a pulpit of wood which they had made\r\nfor the purpose. And beside him stood Mattithiah and Shema and Anaiah, and Urijah and\r\nHilkiah and Maaseiah, on his right hand; and on his left hand, Pedaiah and Mishael and\r\nMalchijah, and Hashum and Hashbadana,Zechariah and Meshullam.[5] And Ezra opened the\r\nbook in the sight of all the people (for he was above all the people), and when he opened it all\r\nthe people stood up.[6] And Ezra blessed the Lord, the great God. And all the people\r\nanswered, “Amen, Amen,” while lifting up their hands; and they bowed their heads, and\r\nworshiped the Lord with their faces to the ground.[7] Also Jeshua and Bani and Sherebiah,\r\nJamin, Akkub, Shabbethai, Hodijah, Maaseiah, Kelita, Azariah, Jozabad, Hanan, Pelaiah, and\r\nthe Levites, caused the people to understand the law; and the people stood in their place.[8]\r\nSo they read in the book, in the law of God, distinctly, and gave the sense and caused them to\r\nunderstand the reading.[9] And Nehemiah, who is the governor, and Ezra the priest the\r\nscribe, and the Levites who taught the people, said unto all the people, “This day is holy unto\r\nthe Lord your God; mourn not, nor weep.” For all the people wept when they heard the words\r\nof the law.[10] Then he said unto them, “Go your way, eat the fat and drink the sweet, and\r\nsend portions unto those for whom nothing is prepared, for this day is holy unto our Lord;\r\nneither be ye sorry, for the joy of the Lord is your strength.”[11] So the Levites stilled all the\r\npeople, saying, “Hold your peace, for the day is holy; neither be ye grieved.”[12] And all the\r\npeople went their way to eat and to drink and to send portions and to make great mirth,\r\nbecause they had understood the words that were declared unto them.[13] And on the\r\nsecond day were gathered together the chief of the fathers of all the people, the priests, and\r\nthe Levites, unto Ezra the scribe, even to understand the words of the law.[14] And they found\r\nwritten in the law, which the Lord had commanded by Moses, that the children of Israel\r\nshould dwell in booths in the feast of the seventh month;[15] and that they should publish and\r\nproclaim in all their cities and in Jerusalem, saying, “Go forth unto the mount, and fetch olive\r\nbranches and pine branches and myrtle branches, and palm branches and branches of thick\r\ntrees to make booths, as it is written.”[16] So the people went forth, and brought them and\r\nmade themselves booths, every one upon the roof of his house, and in their courts and in the\r\ncourts of the house of God, and in the street of the Water Gate and in the street of the Gate of\r\nEphraim.[17] And all the congregation of those who had come again out of the captivity\r\nmade booths and sat under the booths; for since the days of Joshua the son of Nun unto that\r\nday had not the children of Israel done so. And there was very great gladness.[18] Also day by\r\nday, from the first day unto the last day, he read in the Book of the Law of God. And they kept\r\nthe feast seven days; and on the eighth day was a solemn assembly, according unto the\r\nmanner.', 1, 2018, '2019-08-11', '2018-10-04 03:22:44'),
(83, 'Week 51: 18-24 August 2019', 'National Repentance in the Process of Revival', 'Nehemiah 9 & 10', '<h4>9</h4>Now in the twenty and fourth day of this month the children of Israel were assembled with\r\nfasting and with sackcloth and earth upon them.[2] And the seed of Israel separated\r\nthemselves from all strangers, and stood and confessed their sins and the iniquities of their\r\nfathers.[3] And they stood up in their place and read in the Book of the Law of the Lord their\r\nGod for onefourth part of the day; and another fourth part they confessed and worshiped the\r\nLord their God.[4] Then stood up upon the stairs of the Levites, Jeshua and Bani, Kadmiel,\r\nShebaniah, Bunni, Sherebiah, Bani, and Chenani, and cried with a loud voice unto the Lord\r\ntheir God.[5] Then the Levites, Jeshua and Kadmiel, Bani, Hashabniah, Sherebiah, Hodijah,\r\nShebaniah, and Pethahiah, said: “Stand up and bless the Lord your God for ever and ever!\r\nAnd blessed be Thy glorious name, which is exalted above all blessing and praise![6] Thou,\r\neven Thou, art Lord alone; Thou hast made heaven, the heaven of heavens with all their host,\r\nthe earth and all things that are therein, the seas and all that is therein; and Thou preservest\r\nthem all; and the host of heaven worshipeth Thee.[7] Thou art the Lord the God, who didst\r\nchoose Abram, and broughtest him forth out of Ur of the Chaldees, and gavest him the name\r\nof Abraham;[8] and foundest his heart faithful before Thee, and madest a covenant with him\r\nto give the land of the Canaanites, the Hittites, the Amorites and the Perizzites, and the\r\nJebusites and the Girgashites—to give it, I say, to his seed, and hast performed Thy words, for\r\nThou art righteous”[9] and didst see the affliction of our fathers in Egypt, and heardest their\r\ncry by the Red Sea;[10] and showedst signs and wonders upon Pharaoh and on all his\r\nservants and on all the people of his land. For Thou knewest that they dealt proudly against\r\nthem. So didst Thou get Thee a name, as it is this day.[11] And Thou didst divide the sea before\r\nthem, so that they went through the midst of the sea on the dry land; and their persecutors\r\nThou threwest into the deep, as a stone into the mighty waters.[12] Moreover Thou leddest\r\nthem in the day by a cloudy pillar, and in the night by a pillar of fire, to give them light in the\r\nway wherein they should go.[13] Thou camest down also upon Mount Sinai and spokest with\r\nthem from heaven, and gavest them right judgments and true laws, good statutes and\r\ncommandments;[14] and madest known unto them Thy holy Sabbath, and commandedst\r\nthem precepts, statutes, and laws by the hand of Moses Thy servant;[15] and gavest them\r\nbread from heaven for their hunger, and broughtest forth water for them out of the rock for\r\ntheir thirst, and promisedst them that they should go in to possess the land which Thou hadst\r\nsworn to give them.[16] “But they and our fathers dealt proudly, and hardened their necks\r\nand hearkened not to Thy commandments.[17] And they refused to obey, neither were\r\nmindful of Thy wonders that Thou didst among them; but hardened their necks, and in their\r\nrebellion appointed a captain to return to their bondage. But Thou art a God ready to pardon,\r\ngracious and merciful, slow to anger and of great kindness, and forsookest them not.[18]\r\nYea, when they had made them a molten calf and said, \'This is thy God who brought thee up\r\nout of Egypt,\' and had wrought great provocations,[19] yet Thou in Thy manifold mercies\r\nforsookest them not in the wilderness. The pillar of the cloud departed not from them by day,\r\nto lead them in the way; neither the pillar of fire by night, to show them light and the way\r\nwherein they should go.[20] Thou gavest also Thy good Spirit to instruct them, and\r\nwithheldest not Thy manna from their mouth, and gavest them water for their thirst.[21]\r\nYea, forty years didst Thou sustain them in the wilderness, so that they lacked nothing; their\r\nclothes waxed not old and their feet swelled not.[22] Moreover Thou gavest them kingdoms\r\nand nations, and didst divide them into corners; so they possessed the land of Sihon and the\r\nland of the king of Heshbon and the land of Og, king of Bashan.[23] Their children also did\r\nThou multiply as the stars of heaven, and broughtest them into the land which Thou hadst\r\npromised to their fathers, that they should go in to possess it.[24] So the children went in and\r\npossessed the land, and Thou did subdue before them the inhabitants of the land, the\r\nCanaanites, and gavest them into their hands, with their kings and the people of the land,\r\nthat they might do with them as they would.[25] And they took strong cities and a fat land,\r\nand possessed houses full of all goods, wells dug out, vineyards and olive yards, and fruit\r\ntrees in abundance. So they ate, and were filled, and became fat, and delighted themselves\r\nin Thy great goodness.[26] “Nevertheless they were disobedient and rebelled against Thee,\r\nand cast Thy law behind their backs, and slew Thy prophets who testified against them to\r\nturn them to Thee; and they wrought great provocations.[27] Therefore Thou deliveredst\r\nthem into the hand of their enemies, who vexed them. And in the time of their trouble when\r\nthey cried unto Thee, Thou heardest them from heaven; and according to Thy manifold\r\nmercies Thou gavest them saviors who saved them out of the hand of their enemies.[28]\r\n“But after they had rest, they did evil again before Thee. Therefore leftest Thou them in the\r\nhand of their enemies, so that they had the dominion over them; yet when they returned and\r\ncried unto Thee, Thou heardest them from heaven. And many times didst Thou deliver them\r\naccording to Thy mercies,[29] and testifiedst against them, that Thou mightest bring them\r\nagain unto Thy law. Yet they dealt proudly and hearkened not unto Thy commandments, but\r\nsinned against Thy judgments (which if a man do, he shall live in them), and withdrew the\r\nshoulder and hardened their neck and would not hear.[30] “Yet many years didst Thou\r\nforbear them, and testifiedst against them by Thy Spirit in Thy prophets. Yet would they not\r\ngive ear; therefore gavest Thou them into the hand of the people of the lands.[31]\r\nNevertheless for Thy great mercies\' sake Thou did not utterly consume them nor forsake\r\nthem, for Thou art a gracious and merciful God. [32] “Now therefore, our God, the great, the\r\nmighty, and the fearsome God, who keepest covenant and mercy, let not all the trouble seem\r\nlittle before Thee that hath come upon us—on our kings, on our princes, and on our priests,\r\nand on our prophets, and on our fathers, and on all Thy people since the time of the kings of\r\nAssyria unto this day.[33] Nevertheless, Thou art just in all that is brought upon us; for Thou\r\nhast done right, but we have done wickedly.[34] Neither have our kings, our princes, our\r\npriests, nor our fathers kept Thy law, nor hearkened unto Thy commandments and Thy\r\ntestimonies, wherewith Thou didst testify against them.[35] For they have not served Thee in\r\ntheir kingdom, and in Thy great goodness that Thou gavest them, and in the large and fat\r\nland which Thou gavest before them, neither turned they from their wicked works.[36]\r\nBehold, we are servants this day; and for the land that Thou gavest unto our fathers to eat\r\nthe fruit thereof and the good thereof, behold, we are servants in it.[37] And it yieldeth much\r\nincrease unto the kings whom Thou hast set over us because of our sins; also they have\r\ndominion over our bodies and over our cattle at their pleasure, and we are in great\r\ndistress.[38] “And because of all this, we make a sure covenant, and write it; and our princes,\r\nLevites, and priests set their seal unto it.”<br/>\r\n<h4>10</h4> Now those who sealed were: Nehemiah the governor, the son of Hachaliah, and\r\nZedekiah,[2] Seraiah, Azariah, Jeremiah,[3] Pashhur, Amariah, Malchijah,[4] Hattush,\r\nShebaniah, Malluch,[5] Harim, Meremoth, Obadiah,[6] Daniel, Ginnethon, Baruch,[7]\r\nMeshullam, Abijah, Mijamin,[8] Maaziah, Bilgai, Shemaiah; these were the priests.[9] And\r\nthe Levites: both Jeshua the son of Azaniah, Binnui of the sons of Henadad, Kadmiel.[10] And\r\ntheir brethren: Shebaniah, Hodijah, Kelita, Pelaiah, Hanan,[11] Micha, Rehob,\r\nHashabiah,[12] Zaccur, Sherebiah, Shebaniah,[13] Hodijah, Bani, Beninu.[14] The chief of the\r\npeople: Parosh, Pahathmoab, Elam, Zattu, Bani,[15] Bunni, Azgad, Bebai,[16] Adonijah,\r\nBigvai, Adin,[17] Ater, Hezekiah, Azzur,[18] Hodijah, Hashum, Bezai,[19] Hariph, Anathoth,\r\nNebai,[20] Magpiash, Meshullam, Hezir,[21] Meshezabeel, Zadok, Jaddua,[22] Pelatiah,\r\nHanan, Anaiah,[23] Hoshea, Hananiah, Hasshub,[24] Hallohesh, Pilha, Shobek,[25] Rehum,\r\nHashabnah, Maaseiah,[26] and Ahijah, Hanan, Anan,[27] Malluch, Harim, Baanah.[28] And\r\nthe rest of the people —the priests, the Levites, the gatekeepers, the singers, the Nethinim,\r\nand all those who had separated themselves from the people of the lands unto the law of God,\r\ntheir wives, their sons and their daughters, every one having knowledge and having\r\nunderstanding[29] they cleaved to their brethren, their nobles, and entered into a curse and\r\ninto an oath to walk in God\'s law, which was given by Moses the servant of God, and to\r\nobserve and do all the commandments of the Lord our Lord, and His judgments and His\r\nstatutes;[30] and that we would not give our daughters unto the people of the land, nor take\r\ntheir daughters for our sons;[31] and if the people of the land bring wares or any victuals on\r\nthe Sabbath day to sell, that we would not buy it from them on the Sabbath or on the holy day;\r\nand that we would leave the seventh year and the exaction of every debt.[32] Also we made\r\nordinances for us to charge ourselves yearly with the third part of a shekel for the service of\r\nthe house of our God:[33] for the showbread, and for the continual meat offering, and for the\r\ncontinual burnt offering of the Sabbaths, of the new moons, for the set feasts, and for the holy\r\nthings, and for the sin offerings to make an atonement for Israel, and for all the work of the\r\nhouse of our God.[34] And we cast the lots among the priests, the Levites, and the people for\r\nthe wood offering, to bring it into the house of our God according to the houses of our fathers,\r\nat times appointed year by year to burn upon the altar of the Lord our God, as it is written in\r\nthe law;[35] and to bring the firstfruits of our ground and the firstfruits of all fruit of all trees,\r\nyear by year, unto the house of the Lord;[36] also the firstborn of our sons, and of our cattle (as\r\nit is written in the law) and the firstlings of our herds and of our flocks, to bring to the house of\r\nour God, unto the priests who minister in the house of our God;[37] and that we should bring\r\nthe firstfruits of our dough, and our offerings, and the fruit of all manner of trees, of wine and\r\nof oil, unto the priests to the chambers of the house of our God, and the tithes of our ground\r\nunto the Levites, that the same Levites might have the tithes in all the cities of our tillage.[38]\r\nAnd the priest the son of Aaron shall be with the Levites when the Levites take tithes; and the\r\nLevites shall bring up a tenth of the tithes unto the house of our God, to the chambers, into the\r\ntreasure house.[39] For the children of Israel and the children of Levi shall bring the offering of\r\nthe corn, of the new wine, and the oil, unto the chambers where are the vessels of the\r\nsanctuary and the priests who minister and the gatekeepers and the singers. And we will not\r\nforsake the house of our God.', 1, 2018, '2019-08-18', '2018-10-04 03:22:44'),
(84, 'Week 52: 25-31 August 2019', 'Convention 2019 preparation, Fellowship\r\nReflection & Tarry Meeting', '', '', 1, 2018, '2019-08-25', '2018-10-04 03:22:44');
INSERT INTO `summary` (`summary-id`, `study-id`, `row`, `date`) VALUES
(1, 40, 'We must always know that a strange land is a type of Babylon where a Christian loses his\r\nsense of identity, purpose and destination. When Daniel and the three Hebrew boys came\r\ninto Babylon as slaves, Nebuchadnezzar changed their names to take away their allegiance\r\nfrom the God of Israel and give allegiance to the Babylonian gods. Daniel, whose name\r\nmeans, “God is my Judge” was changed to Belshazzar meaning \"Bel protect the King\" (Bel\r\nwas a Babylonian god). Daniel 1 vs 7.', '2018-11-02 11:59:04'),
(2, 40, 'A life of sin takes a man away from the protectionof God into a strange land. A strange land is\r\na place of spiritual exposure full of risk and uncertainties. It is a place where a prince lives like\r\na servant and sons of honour live like beggars. It is a place of captivity, limitation,\r\nconfinement and frustration. No matter how long a man stays in a strange land, he or she can\r\nnever fulfil a purpose or promises toGod. He or she remains disconnected from grace, life\r\nand joy. It is a life of deficit!', '2018-11-02 11:59:04'),
(3, 40, 'Seeing the painful loss of falling into sin, we can conclude that it is better for Christians to\r\npermanently depart from evil (Job 28:28) and abstain from all appearances of evil (1Thess.\r\n5:22), than to suffer the consequences of sin. Look at everything the Jews had to go through.\r\nIt could have all been avoided if only they knew the calamities that their sins would bring\r\nupon them.', '2018-11-02 11:59:04'),
(4, 41, 'The Psalmist was in Babylon but longed for Jerusalem. What about us today? Have we sunk\r\ninto the comfort in Babylon, and developed a lukewarm attitude towards God\'s kingdom?\r\nNow there is no difference between a believer and unbeliever. Modernity has reduced our\r\nconsecration and wehave mingled with the world, losing our identities with ease. It is painful\r\nthat our academic, family, professional and social lives are becoming a great threat with a\r\nhuge tendency to shift our gaze away from our spirituality.', '2018-11-02 12:24:01'),
(5, 41, 'In order for revival to come to the church, Christians must:', '2018-11-02 12:24:01'),
(6, 41, '<li>Realise that this present world in which we live (\r\nsymbolised by Babylon), is only\r\ntemporary and therefore not our true or permanent home. The apostle Paul directs\r\nus to “look not at the things which are seen, but at the things which are not seen. For\r\nthe things which are seen are temporary, but the things which are not seen are\r\neternal” (2Cor. 4:18). Abraham “looked for a city which has foundations, whose\r\nbuilder and maker is God” (Heb. 11:10).</li>', '2018-11-02 12:24:01'),
(7, 41, '<li>Decisions to serve God must be firm and resolute. Consecration and commitment to\r\nstand for God must be rooted in strong experiences that can hold our heads high\r\neven in the midst of life\'s many demands. When it has become normal to have sex\r\nbefore marriage, a man and women of consecration will stand with God even if it\r\nmeans to lose everything.</li>', '2018-11-02 12:24:01'),
(8, 42, 'The word of the Lord by the mouth of Jeremiah (Jer. 29:10) was fulfilled at the appointed\r\ntime (Ezra 1:1). We can count on God to bring to pass all that He has promised us according to\r\nHis good pleasure. Numbers 23:19—\"God is not a man that He should lie, neither the son of\r\nman that He should repent [change his counsel]: has He said, and shall He not do? Or has He\r\nspoken, and shall He not make it good?”', '2018-11-02 12:35:14'),
(9, 42, 'The Church today has God\'s Word which He has spoken by the mouth of His prophets and\r\napostles. Those of us who have been paying attention can see some of those signs which the\r\nprophets spoke of already coming to pass. For example, Daniel 12 is explicitly about the end\r\ntimes, and two of the signs wesee today are found in verse 4—“But you, O Daniel, shut up the\r\nwords and seal the book, even to the time of the end: many shall travel to and fro, and\r\nknowledge shall be increased.” There are two prophecies in that one verse which are being\r\nfulfilled as we speak: (1) The earth has never known a time in history where humans travel\r\nlike they do today, whether by aeroplane, train, cars, etc. It is unprecedented, and the world\r\nwill most likely become more and more of a “global village” in the years ahead. (2)\r\nKnowledge shall be increased. This is happening tremendously in two ways. First, the\r\nInternet age has opened up a vast library and wealth of knowledge which individual people\r\nhad previously never had access to, all, literally, at our fingertips. Even little children go on\r\nthe internet nowadays and dig up knowledge that they would never have had access to\r\notherwise. Second, the Hebrew word da?ath means knowledge in English and the English\r\nword comes directly from the Latin scientia which means “science” or “knowledge”. The\r\nprophecy literally says “...science shall be increased.” Today, Biblical prophecies are already\r\nbeing whispered in the news as science headlines. For example, some celestial bodies from\r\nouter space are predicted in Matthew and Revelation to strike the earth during the last days,\r\nand NASA (National Aeronautical Space Agency of America) has reported objects close to\r\nearth with attendant threat. Some different parts of the world sit on major fault-lines that\r\nhave caused massive earthquakes in the past, but earthquake geologists predict that we\r\nhave not experienced the highest possible magnitude earthquakes yet. Many other\r\nexamples can be given, but the matter at hand is that God\'s people need to keep their eyes\r\nopen as the Lord commanded us to do in Matthew 24:32-33. The more we study the Bible\r\nand the end-time prophecy, the more we are informed when these events come to pass, and\r\nthis can only spark our faith and encourage us to draw nearer to God. This will also fire our\r\nenergy to propagate the gospel of revival. When you imagine how many adults and children\r\nin our local churches and communities who will go into Christ-less eternity, there will be a\r\nsincere push for deeper intercession, consistent discipleship through local fellowships and\r\nstrategic outreaches to lead many to Jesus.', '2018-11-02 12:35:14'),
(10, 42, '', '2018-11-02 12:35:14'),
(11, 44, 'The application of today\'s study is twofold:', '2018-11-02 12:54:30'),
(12, 44, '<li>We must believe that God is the Sovereign Creator, therefore He is “\r\nthe God of the\r\nspirits of all flesh” (Num. 16:22, 27:16). This means that He has power to influence\r\nthe hearts of men, and to turn them whithersoever He pleases (Prov. 21:1). We can\r\ntrust Him to influence every decision in our favour. We do not need a godfather\r\nbecause He is our God the Father.</li>', '2018-11-02 12:54:30'),
(13, 131, '<li>We must pray to God concerning rulers and those in authority, that God will give\r\nthem faith to believe in Christ Jesus (John 6:44, 65) for salvation. We must keep in\r\nmind that God is willing to also use non-Christians to bring all His counsel to pass,\r\nhence we must have excellent relationshipswith all kinds of people that we meet in\r\nour path. Christianity is not the reason why you should not be nice to your gateman\r\nbecause he may be the one that God will use to receive theletter that will take you to\r\nthe next level. We should not look down on unbelieving neighbours or dismiss their\r\nrole in God\'s larger plan.</li>', '2018-11-02 12:54:30'),
(14, 131, 'In a government like that of Nigeria, Christians need to put in extra prayers if wewant to see\r\nthings change for the better (both in the secular and spiritual dimensions). Though Daniel\r\nknew that God is sovereign and had already determined a seventy-year schedule for His\r\npeople\'s restoration, he still prayed fervently for the change he wanted to see (Daniel 9).\r\nCarnal religious methods and deceitful baiting, which we see today are mere fake revival, a\r\nsuperficial substitute for a real move of the Spirit, which can only be facilitated by praying\r\naccording to God\'s will (Rom. 8:26-27, 1John 5:14). This kind of prayer is the catalyst for\r\nsupernatural chain reactions in the realm of the Spirit. “The effectual fervent prayer of a\r\nrighteous man availeth much” (James 5:16). If the effectual fervent prayer of one righteous\r\nman avails much, then surely where two or three are gathered together in Jesus Name, He is\r\nright there in the midst, and if even two such people can agree on earth as touching\r\nanything they shall ask, it shall be done for them by our heavenly Father (Matt. 18:19-20).', '2018-11-02 12:54:30'),
(15, 45, 'We saw from the wedding invitation that many are indeed being called by God unto His\r\nkingdom. We also saw that many will allow worldly concerns to cause them to miss the\r\ninvitation, like the majority of Jews who chose to remain in Babylon. Of course they have valid\r\nexcuses of their investment in Babylon or those born in Babylon who may claim that they\r\ncannot go into uncertainty. For this reason, God is opening the door to “whosoever will”, as\r\nlong as they are willing to put off the garment of the old man (Eph. 4:22) and put on the\r\nwedding garment of the new man (Eph. 4:24). God invites us by first getting our attention\r\n(i.e., arousing our hearts). For some of us, this may be a proverbial mild tap on the shoulder,\r\nwhich means that God will gently call us to the project of spiritual rebuilding. For others, it\r\nmay require God taking something we value away from us so that we can give Him our\r\nundivided attention. In both cases, the choice still falls on us to respond by rising up with zeal\r\nand responding wholeheartedly. The call of revival demands that we rise to face the\r\nuncertainty of moving to a “place” where we have never been before by faith as a revival\r\narmy, whose life is completely sold out to the Lord.', '2018-11-02 13:02:54'),
(16, 45, '<h3>WHAT CAN WE DO?</h3>', '2018-11-02 13:03:53'),
(17, 45, '<li>Humble ourselves: by expressing gratitude to God for even calling us into fellowship\r\nand partnership with Him. We are not worthy since all have sinned and come short of\r\nHis glory, but He still wants us anyway, and thus the invitation through His Son Jesus\r\nChrist. Humility and thanksgiving are our prerequisites for revival.</li>', '2018-11-02 13:05:58'),
(18, 45, '<li>Forsake worldliness and ungodliness: We have wasted enough time in Babylon. We\r\nhave wasted enough time in disobedience. We have wasted time in the wrong place\r\ndoing what God has not called us to do.</li>', '2018-11-02 13:05:58'),
(19, 45, '<li>Rise up: by taking positive action through prayer, obedience, witnessing to others,\r\nBible study, fasting, living by example, exercising faith in the supernatural, and other\r\npractical deeds that build God\'s kingdom.</li>', '2018-11-02 13:05:58'),
(20, 46, 'There are two parts to the application of what wehave learned from this study.\r\n<ol>', '2018-11-02 13:29:50'),
(21, 46, '<li>SPIRITUAL APPLICATION: Hearts and minds must first be willing to go up to\r\nJerusalem to build God\'s temple. We must prepare ourselves spiritually by making\r\nuse of the resources God has made available to us.<ul>', '2018-11-02 13:29:50'),
(22, 46, '<li>Bible Study—how can a man or woman who claims to be on a mission for\r\nChrist not care to know His Scripture? “Ye do err, not knowing the Scriptures,\r\nnor the power of God” (Matt. 22:29).<li>', '2018-11-02 13:29:50'),
(23, 46, '<li>Cooperation with the Holy Spirit—“Grieve not the Holy Spirit of God,\r\nwhereby you are sealed unto the day of redemption” (Eph. 4:30). When we\r\ncommit sins, we grieve the Holy Spirit, and short-circuit the flow of His\r\npower in us and through us.</li>', '2018-11-02 13:29:50'),
(24, 46, '<li>Prayer and fasting—this is a powerful combination that deals critical blows\r\nto the camp of the enemy. Jesus said there are certain kinds of demons that\r\ncannot be handled except by mixing our prayer life with regular fasting\r\n(Mark 9:29).</li>', '2018-11-02 13:29:50'),
(25, 46, '<li>Other spiritual exercises—these include preaching the Gospel, meditating\r\non things above rather than things on earth, fellowshipping with other\r\nbelievers, and anything else that positions us to see revival.</li></ul></li>', '2018-11-02 13:29:50'),
(26, 46, '<li>MATERIAL APPLICATION: God is able to meet our needs as we set out to go for Him,\r\nHe is sufficiently able to touch the hearts of men to support every project that He\r\nhascommitted into our hands. He cares for us and wewill not lack what is needed to\r\nsustain the mandate.</li></ol>', '2018-11-02 13:29:50'),
(27, 46, 'Ultimately, we should not focus on our own needs alone or that of our immediate family alone. God has a larger program going on which will need financing. It is a spiritual disaster when your progress in life does not translate into the expansion of the work of God.', '2018-11-02 13:29:50'),
(28, 48, 'Nebuchadnezzar was wrong for putting the holy vessels of God into the temple of his own\r\ngods, and Christians are wrong for allowing themselves to backslide into ungodliness. But\r\nthe road to revival begins when we start bringing back the articles necessary for a spiritual\r\nlife that is acceptable to God. We must bring back a consistent and fervent prayer life, bring\r\nback the lost act of fasting, bring back diligent Bible study, preaching of sound doctrine, and\r\nrenewed faith/confidence in the miracle-working ability of our God. But as the articles of\r\ntemple worship were incomplete without the covenantal Ark of Covenant, so is a move of\r\nrevival incomplete if our very heart is not involved. Mental repentance is needed but is\r\ninsufficient. There has to be a heart that is remorseful for sins committed and on fire for the\r\nthings of the Spirit.', '2018-11-02 13:41:08'),
(29, 49, 'A summary and application of what we\'ve just seen:', '2018-11-02 13:57:06'),
(30, 49, '<li>The Jews left Babylon (representing our modern worldly sophistication) to return to Judah, “everyone to his own city.” God is calling us out of our comfort zone into the specific purposes He has for every one of us. It may come at a cost. It may require you to relocate from a city to a village, break up a wrong relationship, or anything similar which hinders the fulfilment of God\'s ultimate call on your life.</li>', '2018-11-02 13:57:06'),
(31, 49, '<li>God cares about the details of our lives. His numbering of His people and things that\r\npertain to them are evidence of that truth.</li>', '2018-11-02 13:57:06'),
(32, 49, 'The Biblical revelation shows us that God is a God of order, and we see that\r\ndemonstrated in our study text today. Unfortunately, certain people who assumed\r\nthey were priests couldn\'t be found in the register, thus causing them to lose their place in the priesthood', '2018-11-02 13:57:06'),
(33, 50, 'True revival requires focus and seriousness. We saw this clearly in the lives of the Jews who returned to Jerusalem. They came in with a sense of urgency to do God\'s work. They did not come to Jerusalem to look for titles and recognition, they came to work and they were single minded on the work of building temples—building temples in the lives of men for the Lord to dwell in. Focus is the key—keeping our eyes on the target. Some missionaries have turned their foreign assignments into a part-time kind of tourism. Others have divided their attention by taking care of personal business on God\'s time. Many who are sent on a campus visitation have turned it into an opportunity for merchandising by recruiting many would-be revival agents into some Ponzi schemes and many who are planted in local churches as revival agents have become distracted to run after church politics at the detriment of the mandate of preserving destinies of men.', '2018-11-02 14:22:02'),
(34, 50, 'Secondly, we saw clearly the push towards setting up the temple. The house of God had to be set up in its place. Christians are now the temple, so we have to set up our lives by ordering them according to God\'s will. They have to be grounded in the truth. Our hearts and minds, along with the different areas of our external lives, must be brought into alignment and agreement with the Word of God.', '2018-11-02 14:22:02'),
(35, 50, 'Giving above and beyond is the only way to unlock the power that births true revival. Show me a man who has achieved much for God, such has gone beyond the average line. This must come through in our sacrificial giving. Everything that we are and have belongs to God, and we are really just stewards of His resources. This is why we always say that we are privileged treasurers of God\'s resources in the great house and we must hold nothing back from the owner. We must give the Lord our time, money, physical energy, intellect, and material possessions, in good service for His kingdom. We must use what He has given us, small or big, to serve Him. He owns us and owns everything we have or we will ever have.', '2018-11-02 14:22:02'),
(36, 52, 'Revival cannot happen until we build altars as a place of connection between heaven and earth. Altars of true intercession are the base upon which the move of God can be built.', '2018-11-02 14:33:46'),
(37, 52, 'We also saw clearly the need for unity—the need to be united inone purpose. No personal\r\nagenda, no selfish ambition. They were all willing to leave their comfort zones to unite when\r\nand where necessary to build the foundation of the Lord\'s house. We cannot be in\r\ndisagreement, or pursue different agendas and expect a move of God. We cannot allow\r\ngrudges, rancour or bitterness to cut us off from the move of God. The Holy Spirit is birthed in\r\nrevival, only when we are in one accord.', '2018-11-02 14:33:46'),
(38, 52, 'It is also important to understand the place of the right foundation in building lives for the\r\nLord. We cannot build anyhow; it has to be on the right foundation. For no other foundation\r\ncan anyone lay than that which is laid down, which is Jesus Christ. Any effort to build outside\r\nChrist is error and idolatry. We must build lives on Jesus. We must build them on the truth of\r\nthe cross, genuine salvation, true repentance and total consecration. They must be built line\r\nupon line and precept upon precept, on the sure foundation of Christ\'scharacter and nature.\r\nWe cannot serve God based on our own terms; it must always be on His terms.', '2018-11-02 14:33:46'),
(39, 53, 'True revival is built on the foundation of NO SIN, which in essence means that if we permit\r\nthe operation of iniquity, the move of revival will die. This truth must remain fresh in our\r\nminds as custodians of the work of revival. We must remind ourselves that we destroy the\r\nwork of God when sin is allowed to thrive or hibernate in our secret domains. Like Jesus said,\r\nwe must dig deep in God and not be shallow if we want to stand the test of the pressures and\r\ntemptations of life. Our footing must be sure. We must be rooted in the word of God.<br/>\r\nThe work of revival must blend the wisdom of the elders and the energy of the youths. Elders\r\nhere are not defined by physical age but spiritual experience with God. Any young man who\r\nwants to build on a work must be abreast of its history and masterplan, so that he is not\r\ndistracted by what he sees around as a new template worth being copied. It has been said\r\nrepeatedly that TACEF Campus fellowships, for example, cannot attempt to operate like\r\ntraditional campus fellowships. Every fellowship came in to being for a reason and it will be\r\ncounterproductive to want to be like those with different assignments, albeit divine. Every\r\nwork has an original plan and we must always reference it as we labour. A successful young\r\nman in this case seeks mentors and guidance. Their pride is in being guided and corrected.<br/>\r\nAs a believer, it is important that you do not associate with any work that you do not\r\nunderstand its history. Your energy as a young man will be best fulfilled if it is properly\r\nconnected with the cries of the old, such that both produce a symphony of a great voice that\r\nbrings glory unto the Lord.', '2018-11-02 14:49:58'),
(40, 53, 'As TACEFites, we must not lose the sense of our beginning. The legacy of our yesteryears, the memorial of God\'s move in our midst and the testimonials of our paths from nothing-to something\r\nmust remain fresh and treasured. We must continue to be told of the making of\r\nthis vision—we must not lose the memory as it provides a guide to our accurate future.\r\nIndeed, “to communicate the truths of history is an act of hope for the future”. The same\r\nfeeling we always have when we lose the memory card of our phones or other gadgets,\r\nwhere we have stored our past photos and documents is the way heaven feels when we seem to have lost our sense of history and sense of our path with God. Our memorial with God is\r\nthe reference points we blend the best of times to enrich the core of the vision that the Lord\r\nhas given unto us.', '2018-11-02 14:49:58'),
(41, 54, 'The devil is always on the lookout for every revival move with an intent to destroy it, even at\r\nits infancy. His approach may not be violent, but through friendly alliance aimed to destroy\r\nthe core of the truth. This calls for discernment and a need to see beyond the veil. The devil is\r\na father of lies and he is good in diluting the truth by seeking to mix the truth with error.', '2018-11-02 15:03:12'),
(42, 54, 'We must, therefore, be aware of this act of idolatry, where the devil seeks to bring another\r\n“god” into our act of service unto God. This modern day idolatry does not come like it did in\r\nthe past. It now comes in different masks either through love of money (turning the church\r\ninto a business), worldly entertainment (spirit of Jezebel), watering down Biblical\r\ninstructions, allowing ungodliness to continue in the church without rebuke, etc.', '2018-11-02 15:03:12'),
(43, 54, 'The only way we can survive this threat is to stand bythe truth that we have always known\r\nand not be carried away by new revelation aimed at shifting our focus away from the major to\r\nthe minor. We must remain firm to the timeless Bible truth, without giving in to the pressure\r\nto fit into popular trends. Don\'t be compliant with men, only be valid with God. Always\r\nremember that if you deny Him before men, He will also deny you in His father\'s kingdom\r\n(Matt 10 vs 33).', '2018-11-02 15:03:12'),
(44, 54, 'Be careful of new doctrines from friends and even spiritual leaders that you respect. Be\r\nassured of what you have known in Christ and do not be deceived into seeking a middle point.\r\nDo not be tempted to say you want to visit these churches or buy their tapes or indulge in\r\nwatching their videos on your WhatsApp or Facebook page. Don\'t be politically correct and\r\nheavenly wrong. Do not allow the fact that you want everyone to like you to make you a hater\r\nof God. Zerubbabel\'s approach id a clear NO. He will not pretend or stand in the middle\r\nground.', '2018-11-02 15:03:12'),
(45, 56, 'For every position that God has given us, there will be opposition. This study has\r\ndemonstrated the need to stand firm in the midst of fierce battles of life when men will rise\r\nagainst the good work we are doing for the Lord. We must, therefore,not be ignorant of the\r\ndevil\'s devices to weaken our hands (2Cor. 2:11). We must realise that the last thing he wants\r\nis to see us build our lives unto God and become a temple where God\'s presence dwells.\r\nBeloved, do not get discouraged when the devil uses illness, poverty, loneliness, and such\r\nthings to make us question God. The worst attack is when people you have always trusted\r\nturn their backs against you and the people you have relied on turn their sword to hit the\r\npainful part of your heart.', '2018-12-03 19:05:15'),
(46, 56, 'Always remember that man can fail. Only God will stand by you throughout. Blessed is he\r\nwho expects nothing, for he shall never be disappointed. Instead, trust the Lord during trying\r\ntimes. Encouragement comes from the comfort of the Holy Spirit, from God\'s written Word,\r\nand from genuine brothers or sisters in Christ whom the Lord will bring your way in the time\r\nof pain. Do not close your heart to them because someone had previously failed you.', '2018-12-03 19:05:15'),
(47, 56, 'This study has also raised the issue of fear. The fear of what my friends will say, the fear of\r\nrejection or the fear of being called old school. Never compromise your faith because of fear.\r\nNever allow the fear of losing your job todrive you to sin in your place of work, or the fear of\r\nsurvival shift your values. Never succumb to pressures. Be firm, be true and resolute. Why\r\nwill you see an error of doctrine being perpetuated in your local church and you are afraid to\r\nexpress your Biblical opinion to your minister? You will try to “blend” and weaken the faith of\r\nmany who look up to you in your local church because you are afraid of what others will say\r\nabout you. If you spend your life concentrating on what everyone else thought of you, you\r\nwill forget who you really are.<br/>\r\nIn addition, do not make a god out of men that God has used for you. It is always better to\r\ntrust in the Lord than to put confidence in man. Destiny helpers, supporters and promisegivers\r\nwill always come our way like Cyrus, but do not be surprised or shocked when they\r\nwithdraw their support or deny what they had promised. This was the mistake the Jews\r\nmade with Cyrus, and it led to a long delay of several years in their restoration.', '2018-12-03 19:05:15'),
(48, 56, 'Beloved, when we look wholeheartedly to God and abide in Him, He will encourage us,\r\ndismiss fear from our hearts, and supply all our spiritual and material needs according to His\r\nriches in glory by Christ Jesus. We need not fear man, the devil, or the world\'s challenges, but\r\nrather, we should expect God to be there for us as we move away from worldliness and\r\ncarnality into full worship and revival.\r\nAlways remember that every adversity, every failure, every heartache carries with it the seed\r\nof an equal or greater benefit.', '2018-12-03 19:05:15'),
(49, 57, 'Not only does Satan accuse us before God, he also uses human vessels in our lives who like to\r\naccuse us of past misdeeds. The past may hunt our future but it must never define it. The\r\nerrors that we made in the past must not become a weight that pushes us back from\r\nadvancing to the next level of God\'s demand. The fact that a brother or a sister had been\r\nknown for a wayward life in the past must not make him or her discouraged from starting a\r\nwork for the Lord. The fact that you were sent away from the choir many years ago because of\r\nembezzlement does not mean you must not go back on the better platform of your salvation\r\nto correct the past and use the impact of Jesus to make a difference to others. Of course,\r\nsome people may remind others about your past with statements like, “don\'t follow that\r\nbrother, he did X, Y, Z to some teenagers in the past”. When this happens, seek for grace and\r\nnot accept it as a disgrace.', '2018-12-03 19:15:43'),
(50, 57, 'Let your past become your best testimony and remember that it is not how far you fall, but\r\nhow high you bounce that counts.', '2018-12-03 19:15:43'),
(51, 57, 'In addition, the enemy can try to make life difficult using written documentation of facts and\r\nfigures that can ruin our names and reputations. This is why in TACEF, we encourage God-led\r\nrestitution, where you resolve some issues of the past with the wisdom of God and with\r\ncounsel guided by the Holy Spirit. If a lady has had a terrible past in worldliness and fails to\r\ncommunicate such to her partner in marriage, it will be a big shock when this comes to light\r\nto her shame.', '2018-12-03 19:15:43'),
(52, 57, 'We now live in a world of social media and every picture taken in different circumstances is\r\nforever kept, even after you think you deleted it. Recently some students were denied\r\nadmission to the highly rated Harvard University because of bad things they had posted on\r\nsocial media a long time ago.', '2018-12-03 19:15:43'),
(53, 59, 'The summary and application of this study is that we are under obligation to do God\'s will\r\nbefore our own. When we fail and leave God\'s work stagnant, He will sometimes use a\r\nprophetic voice to wake us up. In our modern era, this voice can come via a number of\r\nchannels such as a live face-to-face encounter with a real man or woman of God, a TV or radio\r\nbroadcast, a phone call, an online message, or even through a simple book. The prophetic\r\nvoice of the Lord is written all over the scripture as we meditatively reflect on the word of\r\nGod. God will always speak but we must have an open mind to hear and to respond with the\r\ndesired action. Here we also see that prophetic ministry is not an exploitative ministry that is\r\nfocused on prophesying for money but on mobilising God\'s people unto consciousness of\r\nGod\'s demand. Any prophet whose ministry does not draw men unto God is a liar. Any\r\nprophet whose prophesy is to draw us unto himself for selfish gain is a cheat and not of the\r\nLord. Be careful of any prophet that turns you into an ATM. Run away from a prophet who\r\nsays you must give money to receive a prophesy. Flee from self-acclaimed prophets whose\r\nprophecies do not agree with the word of God. For example, a prophet who says a child of\r\nGod should lie at work, go to a river to bath, bring an egg or candles for prayers etc. are not\r\ndrawing us unto God or revival and therefore is an antichrist.', '2018-12-03 19:31:08'),
(54, 59, 'In addition, our desire for personal comfort should not get in our way to serve the Lord. We\r\nmust be resolute and focus on what is important at all times. We must not put the cart before\r\nthe horse. If your life as a temple of the Lord is not built, nothing else can work. Serving God is\r\nthe foundation upon which every great thing can be built. A man who is building his future at\r\nthe detriment of the Lord\'s work is only pouring water into a \'leaking\' basket. May the Lord\r\nhelp us to focus and put what is No 1 as No 1. Knowing that my life is the sum total of all the\r\ndecisions I make every day, and those decisions must be determined by my priorities—by\r\nwhat is important,by a scale of preference on the weights of God and eternity.', '2018-12-03 19:31:08'),
(55, 60, 'The idea of revival, restoration, and rebuilding demands that we are willing to lay down our\r\nlives for the cause of Christ. Jesus said,“Whosoever will save his life shall lose it, but\r\nwhosoever shall lose his life for my sake and the Gospel\'s, the same shall save it” (Mark\r\n8:35). When we “lose our lives” for the sake of the Gospel, God\'s eyes are automatically\r\nupon us for good, intervening at different turns and corners to help us in fulfilling our mission\r\n(Rom. 8:28). This must be the anchor of our determination, where we take a risk for the\r\nkingdom on an understanding that God will never cheat us. We must be firm in our\r\ncommitment and consecration no matter how tough the battle becomes.', '2018-12-03 19:46:12'),
(56, 60, 'God cares for every detail of our lives. For the Israelites, He will never allow them to be\r\nridiculed, hence He brought light into the darkness so that the missing scroll that contained\r\nthe needed instruction is found. He is the Lord who is able to search into all mysteries and\r\nassist us when the enemy tries to push us into a corner and make us vulnerable. He has\r\nsorted many with missing CVs, documents, legal cases etc. in an unexplainable manner.', '2018-12-03 19:46:12'),
(57, 60, 'This calls for us to take a stand. God will not take a stand over a life that is not committed.\r\nPaul said we must be steadfast and unmovable, always abounding in the work of the Lord. It\r\nimplies that there are no excuses why we should not remain at our duty posts no matter how\r\nintense the battle is. There is no reason why we should allow the enemy\'s opposition to stop\r\nus. Lack of finances should not stop us. Physical ailments must not stop us. Government\r\npolicy is not an excuse as we can see Christians in China growing from grace to grace in the\r\nfiercest of battle of their lives. The will of God will not take us where the grace of God cannot\r\nsustain us.', '2018-12-03 19:46:12'),
(58, 60, 'When God sees our determination, He will see to it Himself that all our needs are divinely\r\nsupplied (Phil. 4:19), and He will remove every obstacle from the way to ensure that our\r\nwork for Him gets done.\r\n', '2018-12-03 19:46:12'),
(59, 61, 'This study centres on revival at individual and corporate levels, with specific regard to\r\n<b>separation</b> from worldliness and ungodliness.', '2018-12-03 19:58:34'),
(60, 61, 'The dedication of the temple meant that it was set apart unto God. That is why the\r\nSamaritans from Ezra 4 were not allowed to be partakers of the building, because they had a\r\nmixed and perverted form of godliness, partially worshipping God of Israel while\r\nsimultaneously worshipping idols. Individual Christians and the Church as a whole must\r\nseparate from mixing modern-day idolatry with pure worship. Many of our contemporary\r\nchurches today have mixed God with worldliness. As our Lord Jesus drove out the hustlers\r\nand money changers, so must we do. Plus, we must drive out and separate anything else that\r\nhinders the flow of the Spirit of God. These may include things within the Church such as\r\njealousy, spiritual pride, gossip, sexual immorality, dishonesty, provocative dressing, etc.', '2018-12-03 19:58:34'),
(61, 61, 'Preparing ourselves for revival will also require that we seek to have real encounters and\r\nexperiences of God. After separating and putting away uncleanness, we must follow through\r\nin prayer, asking God to reveal Himself to us in a profound way, like Moses once prayed: “I\r\nbeseech thee, show me thy glory” (Ex. 33:18). A great man of God once said “It seems that\r\nGod will do nothing except His people pray” (John Wesley). But we must separate from\r\nungodliness first, as the Scriptures reveal that iniquity hinders God from responding (Psalm\r\n66:18, Isa. 59:2).', '2018-12-03 19:58:34'),
(62, 61, 'We will begin to experience a foretaste of the latter rain Outpouring if we do these two\r\nthings— (1) separate from ungodliness and (2) seek supernatural encounters from God.', '2018-12-03 19:58:34'),
(63, 63, 'Most revivals were birthed during the process of teaching. The Pentecostal revival that\r\noccurred around 1901 started through a Bible school seminary lecturer, named Charles\r\nParham in England. He was teaching the students about the Acts Chapter two experiences.\r\nThe point of contention was that the baptism of the Holy Ghost was just for the early Church\r\nand it was not present again. That was the teaching that was on board as at then. They looked\r\ncarefully at the Scripture to discover that it was a gift that was given to the church to function\r\nin all generation. The lecturer asked them to begin to desire the baptism of the Spirit though\r\nhe as their lecturer had not experienced it. The students desired and prayed for this gift of the\r\nSpirit and the Power of God hit them. In the first encounter,a woman Agnes spoke in tongues\r\nfor several days, speaking pure Chinese yet she was not from China. From that meeting\r\nmighty men and women were raised and they went all over the world propelling the revival\r\nprocess. One of the men from that seminary was the man William D. Seymour, the one-eyed\r\nblack man that piloted the popular Azusa Street Revival around 1906 in the United States of\r\nAmerica. The essence of this brief history is to point to the fact that the place of studying,\r\npractising and teaching the Word in the process of revival cannot be overemphasised.\r\nThe more of the word of God we know, the more of God we are able to activate into physical\r\nreality.', '2018-12-03 20:09:34'),
(64, 64, 'There is a need for strategic recruitment of workforce for revival through focused outreach\r\nlike Ezra did. We must be able to evaluate what we have, identify the gaps and map out a clear\r\nplan on where and how to get the required workforce. Just as Ezra sent eleven men to recruit\r\nLevites for the work of God, we also must practically tap into the talents that are lying\r\ndormant and idle. We cannot be lamenting that subgroups are declining or not growing\r\nwhen we are not consciously searching and investing in new workforce. If you are a member\r\nof a local fellowship, reach out and recruit more revival agents through one-on-one\r\nevangelism. There are many who are indeed hungry for salvation but they are waiting for\r\nsomeone who will draw close in love and not in condemnation to communicate the message\r\nof hope. Please note that this is beyond \'church\' invitation, but a call to revival and a personal\r\nimpact where you share Jesus and lead unto salvation.', '2018-12-03 21:05:01'),
(65, 64, 'As a team leader in any subgroup, do not continue to make excuses that people are not\r\njoining a subgroup, you must reach out and not sit down expecting people to come like Ezra\r\ndid.', '2018-12-03 21:05:01'),
(66, 64, 'Do not continue with the blame game and lament that the work is getting bigger when you\r\nare just struggling to do it alone when you can reach out for more men with better skills and\r\ncapacities than you to help and take it further.', '2018-12-03 21:05:01'),
(67, 64, 'The place of unity and corporate anointing is critical in revival. After a person has set his heart\r\nto seek, do, and teach God\'s Word, he must then look for like-minded people with whom\r\nthere can be fellowship on a consistent basis. Revival is first personal, then corporate. There is\r\nalso a great harvest of souls which will require joint efforts in reaping. Moses, Ezra, Paul, and\r\neven our Lord Jesus Himself all knew this and connected with others in doing the work of God.\r\nThe more God\'s people come into agreement and unity, the more impact we can make in our\r\nworld for His kingdom.', '2018-12-03 21:05:01'),
(68, 65, 'The place of fasting and prayer is critical if we want to make a great impact for the Lord in our\r\ncall of revival. Any revival move that is not backed by consistent practice of self-denial and\r\nhumbleness of heart through fasting cannot last. TACEF, as a fellowship was birthed in many\r\ndays of fasting and prayers and its future relevance will also be determined by a consistent\r\nattitude of staying long with God in the place of waiting for guidance, instruction and\r\ndirection on a consistent basis. <b>A fellowship is not greater than the powerhouse of prayer\r\nand fasting it can access. The ability to wait long with God will determine how far a destiny\r\nwill go.</b>', '2018-12-03 21:22:38'),
(69, 65, 'It must, however, be noted that fasting is not a mechanical act. It starts first from the heart\r\nwith a genuine heart of submission and humbleness. You cannot live in sin and be fasting. It is\r\nnothing but a hunger strike. People who fast while living in immorality are essentially shortcircuiting\r\nthe spiritual activity and wasting their time. Fasting is supposed to be a time of\r\ncleansing and abstinence, not just from food, but from uncleanness of thoughts, words, and\r\ndeeds. This means that even if you abstain from food for days but your heart and actions are\r\nnot right with God, then your fasting has become an ineffective andfutile exercise.', '2018-12-03 21:22:38'),
(70, 65, 'Sincere, humble fasting attracts God\'s attention because He sees that the person is denying\r\nhimself from something pleasurable in order to fine-tune his spiritual antenna. When we\r\nfast this way, we have confidence that the Holy Spirit will flow through us unhindered, and all\r\nprincipalities and powers are defeated.', '2018-12-03 21:22:38'),
(71, 65, 'The need to trust in God alone is a critical matter in revival. If truly God is sending a man, He\r\nmust also be trusted to provide. It becomes shameful when we turn every need in the house\r\nof God into fundraising like the people of the world. It gets most painful when unbelievers\r\nare brought into the church to donate to the work of God. This is an error because God is\r\nsufficient to provide for the work that He himself has commissioned. Let us stop ridiculing\r\nGod by cheapening His ability to do His work through us.', '2018-12-03 21:22:38'),
(72, 67, 'The Bible is clear that God wants His people to be set apart unto Himself in holiness and\r\nrighteousness. Israel\'s greatest error was ignoring this truth. Christians today must not be\r\nunequally yoked together with unbelievers both socially and in matrimony. The world we live\r\nin now is just as filthy as it was back in the time when Israel was surrounded by pagan tribes,\r\nand Christians who do not take heed of God\'s instruction of separation will find themselves\r\ninfluenced and eventually participating in ungodly practices. Separation for us must also\r\nextend to digital separation where we avoid associating with sin through wrong online\r\nassociation, social networks and virtual interactions that corrupt the essence of our faith in\r\nChrist Jesus. It must also be noted that separation does not mean that we do not associate\r\nwith people of this world, but rather it means we do not think, live, desire and act like them as\r\nthere must be a clear boundary in our dealings and interactions with them. They must be able\r\nto say of us that, “these ones do not belong to their spiritual domain and will never act, think\r\nor live like them”. They must be able to “certify” that you will never collect a bribe even when\r\nthey do. They must be able to say without any iota of doubt that you do not cheat, steal, come\r\nlate to work, be lazy, unfaithful, unruly etc. Their testimony of us must always be that our lives\r\nshow them the best of God and trigger a desire to know the God we serve even unto genuine\r\nsalvation. Our quest for revival means we must engage the world but not be influenced by it\r\nbut to positively influence it for the Lord. This must be our standpoint of engagement at all\r\ntimes.', '2018-12-03 21:36:54'),
(73, 67, 'In addition, Intercession is key in the ministry of revival. If there is no man to fill the gap, it\r\nmeans the gap will not be closed but opened to divine judgement. Like Ezra, we must be\r\nagents of revival who are conscious of the sins of our fellow humans, not in a negative\r\njudgemental way, but in a way that the feeling of the pain of sin can propel us to pray more and\r\neven fast until more people know Jesus as their Lord and Saviour. It takes burden on our\r\nhearts to be motivated and mobilised as fishers of men (Matt. 4:19), soul winners (Prov.\r\n11:30), and agents of revival who turn many to righteousness (Dan. 12:3). History speaks of\r\ngreat revival agents like John Knox, known for his prayer “Give me Scotland, or I die.” Knox\'s\r\nprayer was not an arrogant demand, but the passionate plea of a man willing to die for the\r\nsake of the pure preaching of the gospel and the salvation of his countrymen. He was a man of\r\ndeep burden for the soul of men.', '2018-12-03 21:36:54'),
(74, 68, 'This study is a vignette of what the ministry of any TACEFite must be as a true revival agent\r\ncalled to raise an army with a vision of revival. There is no ministry of revival without\r\nconviction of sin, genuine repentance and sincere acts of restitution.\r\nLike Ezra, our personal encounter with God is the first basis of a ministry that can touch the\r\nhearts of men unto genuine repentance. A man who does not have a deep prayer life\r\npowered by a deep burden of sin of men cannot have a ministry that touches the hearts of\r\nmen unto genuine salvation. <b><i>A revival agent who is not revived in prayer and word is a\r\nmistake waiting to happen.</i></b>', '2018-12-03 21:49:15'),
(75, 68, 'In our study, we have seen how revival happens when the Spirit of God convicts of sin, propels\r\nconfession and drives the process of making a commitment to God which must be\r\ncomplemented by a conscious effort to make amends for the wrong done. Beyond the\r\nconvictions for sinners is the need for continuous self-evaluation and repentance as a\r\nChristian. Like the great evangelist Charles Spurgeon said, “Repentance is necessary in every\r\ncase; there must be this radical change which shall make you hate what you once loved, and\r\nlove what you once hated”.', '2018-12-03 21:49:15'),
(76, 68, 'One of the most practical applications of this study will be the part where we take practical\r\nactions in putting our lives and our relationships in order after repentance. God will not\r\naccept confession of sins that is not followed by correcting our wrongs. Each of us know\r\nwhere we have harmed others in the past, so we must do all we can to do right by those\r\npeople we have harmed. There have been cases where nothing could be done, an example\r\nbeing a convicted murderer who repented and got saved, but could not bring the victim back.\r\nBesides such extreme cases, we can usually do something to correct our wrongs and clear\r\nour conscience from guilt. Some situations will be more demanding to fix than others. Some\r\nmay cause us serious embarrassment. A guilty penitent has no room for pride in his or her\r\nheart. God resists the proud, but gives grace to the humble (1Pet. 5:5). We may have to\r\nconfess that it was us who did something long ago which someone else had been blamed for\r\nand wrongfully suffered for. Ultimately, God will be pleased when He sees us take the pains of\r\nmaking amends even when it is not easy. He knows that it will give us real freedom in the end.\r\nRepentance is never complete without a deep godly desire to make restitution. It must also\r\nbe stated here that this act is not done for self-show, hence there is a need to be guided and\r\nled of the spirit on how to do it. <b>There are certain acts that have legal implications and thus\r\na need for a leader to guide on how best to do it in a manner that honour God and not bring\r\npain and regret.</b>', '2018-12-03 21:49:15'),
(77, 68, 'Finally, as we drive the ministry of conviction of sin, let our message always be, “We are a\r\ngreat sinner, but Jesus is a greater Saviour”, emphasising the magnanimity of God\'s\r\nunmerited grace and ability to save, deliver and change a life for good.', '2018-12-03 21:49:15'),
(78, 69, 'Our calling is to carry the burden of the Lord everywhere and every time irrespective of our\r\nsecular demands. Our work must never diminish our ability to remain connected to heaven.\r\nThe ambience of our progress in life must not disconnect us from seeking the welfare of many\r\nsouls whose lives remain in ruins and on ravage of hell. The comforting and relaxing air conditioning\r\nin our workplaces must never insulate us from feeling the heat of the hellfire\r\nthat is taking many unto Christ-less eternity. We must remain connected to the burden of the\r\nLord while we build excellent professional or business careers.', '2018-12-03 22:01:13'),
(79, 69, 'In the same vein, our work must not suffer because we are carrying the burden of the Lord.\r\nThe fact that we are busy for the Lord must not be a reason why we are an under performing\r\nstudent or low-quality worker who is known for laziness, lack of ingenuity or creative\r\nthinking and bereft of superior performance. Nehemiah was an excellent worker and\r\nspiritual burden bearer. He maintained a high sense of professionalism and had the respect\r\nof the King. His burden and service to the Lord did not stop him from doing his job effectively\r\nand efficiently. <b><i>We can carry a great burden in our heart for the work of God yet maintain\r\nexcellence in our sphere of influence.</i></b>', '2018-12-03 22:01:13'),
(80, 69, 'It is a disgrace to the cross when we neglect excellent performance in our secular work in the\r\nname of spirituality. Our work tends to become our worth, hence we do it as unto the Lord,\r\nas Paul said even a lowly servant should serve his boss well as if he was doing it for the Lord\r\n(Col. 3:22-23). This is how Nehemiah served the king, while there was still a burden in his\r\nheart for God\'s kingdom.', '2018-12-03 22:01:13'),
(81, 69, 'We should seek to glorify God in all things (1Cor. 10:31), which means professionalism in the\r\nworkplace and spiritual zeal for the cause of Christ. As we shall see in a later study, Nehemiah\r\nfound grace with the king Artaxerxes because he was an excellent servant, which granted\r\nhim his request to go to Jerusalem. God used his diligent service in the secular realm as a\r\nspringboard to activate his leadership role in Jerusalem\'s revival. Our God wants us to\r\nrepresent Him well in our sphere of influence, so He can use that to open other doors and do\r\nbigger things through us.', '2018-12-03 22:01:13'),
(82, 71, 'There is no revival without risk-taking. The foundation of the move of God is laid on the\r\nplatform of men and women who have chosen to risk their lives for the sake of the Lord.\r\nToday, there are many parts of the world where Christians are threatened with death\r\nbecause of their commitment to the King of kings. Many have been killed, while many others\r\nare vulnerable to physical and emotional risks. Churches and homes have been burnt or\r\nbombed. Some live day-to-day not knowing which will be their last on earth, but are\r\nnevertheless content, knowing that they have a crown of life waiting for them in heaven (Rev.\r\n2:10). Nehemiah was a cup-bearer, ready to die for his king. For him, his allegiance could cost\r\nhim his life, yet he was prepared to make the ultimate sacrifice.', '2018-12-04 07:11:47'),
(83, 71, 'We also see how Nehemiah knows the taste and preference of his king as a cup-bearer. He\r\nknows what must not come near the king. He knows the wine for every moment and the best\r\ncondiment for every season. He is a man who can discern and respond to the demands of the\r\nking with accuracy and precision. The king can trust him and taste whatever he brings\r\nwithout question. Do you know the taste of the king and what tobring to the Lord through\r\nyour life to service the best for the King of kings? Can the Lord drink from your hand without\r\nbeing poisoned by your life of secret sins and immoralities?', '2018-12-04 07:11:47'),
(84, 71, 'In addition, we must understand the need to have what it takes to stand in the courts and\r\npalace of the king. It is the place to learn and build capacity and not live in the past tense of\r\nknowledge. Every opportunity that God gives us to learn or gain useful experience should be\r\nsomething we value and make the most of. Every NYSC member can learn extra skills during\r\nthe service year. A student of Mechanical Engineering must comfortably use his holiday\r\nperiod to learn as a mechanic\'s apprentice at a nearby mechanic\'s village and not continue to\r\nboast of a degree that has no practical application. Other life skills like hair-dressing, barbing,\r\ncatering, driving, computing, music practical (piano, guitar etc.) must be a common\r\naspiration of everyone to learn when there is opportunity.', '2018-12-04 07:11:47'),
(85, 72, 'Great work of God starts from men whose hearts connect with the heartbeat of God per time.\r\nNo work of revival can go far if there are men who do not feel the pain of the welfare of\r\npeople—the agony, shame and pain of people whose lives are in the ruins of sin, exposed to\r\nthe attacks of life,and the danger of eternal damnation. This heartbeat of God comes to us as\r\na burden, and we have to take it through a season of prayers and fasting before it becomes a\r\nclear vision which gives us a clear picture of God-desired future that we can run with.\r\nNehemiah was able to clarify this in Nehemiah 2:17, <i>“You know very well what trouble we are\r\nin. Jerusalem lies in ruins, and its gates have been destroyed by fire. Let us rebuild the wall of\r\nJerusalem and end this disgrace!”</i> No revival happens when a clear vision is absent because\r\nwhen there is no vision, the people perish (Proverbs 29 vs 18).', '2018-12-04 07:23:01'),
(86, 72, 'The process by which a burden becomes a vision is very important and it is a process that\r\nmust not be missed or else the burden can die prematurely or lead a person in a wrong\r\ndirection. Every burden is an egg which must mature under the warmth of prayers and fasting\r\nor else it will not “hatch” into the desired chick. Every burden must go through a consistent\r\nperiod of prayer, fasting, and Bible study so that they are birthed in the place of God\'s sure\r\nleading.', '2018-12-04 07:23:01'),
(87, 72, 'This study has also shown us the importance of excellent leadership spirit whose life can\r\npositively influence and motivate others to naturally follow and not be coerced. True\r\nleadership is much more than authority and recognition. It is not by carrying a title or by age.\r\nInstead, leadership is all about inspiring people and being a source of motivation that\r\ndraws the best out of people to deliver on a collective objective. It\'s about breaking down\r\nbarriers and leading others through the uncertainty of the future by being a true champion of\r\nthe desired outcome.', '2018-12-04 07:23:01'),
(88, 73, 'No revival or work of repair of breach in a life, family, church or generation can happen\r\nwithout clear and concise communication of the vision. You may have a big vision, but if you\r\ncannot communicate it, you are no different from a man who has the best car in the world but\r\nhas no key to open or drive it. Vision requires communication that is simple, compelling and\r\nmotivating. It is the clarity of the picture of the future that captures the hearts of men to\r\nsacrifice their lives in the pursuit of a vision that represents their future. Like a popular quote\r\nIn TACEF reads, <b><i>“In the vision, we find our future”.</i>\r\nEvery leader at home, work, ministry etc. must consciously develop his communication skills,\r\nso as not to waste the opportunity when the king calls. Nehemiah could have wasted time\r\ntelling generational stories that do not make sense. He did not waste time as a good\r\ncommunicator, he was focussed, clear, precise and definite—and this worked with great\r\nresults. A good leader must be clear about the what, why, when and how of every\r\nassignment. He must be able to factually communicate in ways that motivate and do not\r\ndemoralise.', '2018-12-04 07:32:55'),
(89, 73, 'As we build the skills of a great communicator who does not waste words, we must also\r\nrecognise the place of favour with God and with men. In God, we find the best favour, having\r\nenjoyed the biggest unmerited favour called Grace, which has connected us from death unto\r\nthe life of God through Jesus death and resurrection. God\'s favour must be what we seek\r\nbecause it will manifest in the favour that we receive from men. We must never put the cart\r\nbefore the horse. God must be our source at all times. In activating the vision, we need men\r\nwho will rise for our sake and this is where favour with man comes, which also responds to\r\nour good relationships with others, excellent work ethics, God-glorifying relationships with\r\ncolleagues/neighbours, inspiring testimonies among friends/old students etc. <b>Be a man that\r\nothers will like to help because of the nice, positive and warm personality that you radiate.</b>', '2018-12-04 07:32:55'),
(90, 75, 'Nehemiah understood the need to take some time alone with God in order to internally\r\nnurture the assignment that God had placed in his heart. Telling others about our plans in an\r\nuntimely manner is unwise and can actually derail the vision and cut short the assignment.\r\nWe must first work out all the details of our vision and divine assignment that has been given\r\nus, and even after that it is always better to tell it only to those whom the situation\r\nnecessitates and only at the leading of the Lord. Always understand that the instructions and\r\nrevelations that God has trusted you with is not for show and never to impress anyone.', '2018-12-04 13:16:32'),
(91, 75, 'Kingdom assignment requires excellent planning which comes only by a full investigation or\r\n“dissection” of a matter, an issue or an assignment. A man who wants to succeed on a divine\r\nassignment uses rich information, statistics, facts, details and reports to understand what\r\nhappened before, what is happening now, and how he can make the future better than the\r\npresent or past. He is an example of a man who has been tasked to plan an Easter retreat,\r\nwho starts first by taking time to carefully reflect on past reports, watch/listen to recordings,\r\nask attendees questions on what worked and what did not work, analyse attendance pattern\r\nin the last 3 years, review every possible improvement in accommodation, feeding, sleeping,\r\ntechnical issues etc. Men who have accomplished things of value for God are men who pay\r\nattention to details.', '2018-12-04 13:16:32'),
(92, 76, 'In this study, Nehemiah described a number of geographical locations and listed 10 gates\r\nthat were repaired along with towers and important structures, with each being completed\r\nby different people with their individual attributes. We can see how the powerof trusting\r\npeople to work through delegation facilitated a smooth delivery of the task. But first,\r\nNehemiah was clear about the big picture which he broke down into small elements and was\r\nable to hand over these bits and pieces to people to execute. The work of revival and\r\nrepairing require teamwork, cooperation and high sense of collective destiny, that is, if one\r\nfails or falls, we have all failed.', '2018-12-04 13:36:23'),
(93, 76, 'We also saw the emotional connection of the leader when he ensured that the process of\r\nrebuilding began from each person\'s home or areas of dwelling. This experience could also\r\nmean that while we desire to build the work of revival, we must individually make sure that\r\nwe have taken care of our lives at home first before we try and help others. As we go far for\r\nthe Lord, we must make sure that our home has a solid wall of protection surrounding it. As\r\nwe go out ministering, we must be certain that our family altar and our children are walking\r\non the path of the message that we preach. Let us be like the Nehemiah\'s men and make sure\r\nthat our home life is taken care of first before any ministering or service to others.', '2018-12-04 13:36:23'),
(94, 76, 'You must have noticed how long this verse is. It shows us that God is a recorder of names and\r\nHe is very interested in the details. The Bible does not just say, “and lots of people made\r\nrepairs to the wall.” No, it specifically names each person that made repairs and that has\r\nbeen recorded for all of eternity! God keeps memorial of our labour. Our lives and actions are\r\nrecorded by the Lord for our rewards in the life to come. Nothing is done for the Lord in vain\r\non this earth, even if no one else sees it. Men may not recognise you, the alumni association\r\nmay not reach out to you, your local fellowship may forget your years of labour—remember\r\nthat God does not forget. So do not lose heart in your work for the Lord knowing that <i>“For\r\nGod is not unrighteous to forget your work and labour of love, which ye have shewed toward\r\nhis name...”</i> Heb 6 vs 10', '2018-12-04 13:36:23'),
(95, 77, 'The enemy is not giving up and we must be fortified and remain strong. It all starts from our\r\nmind. A mind to work: a mind to progress, a mind to move ahead, a mind never to give up, a\r\nmind to believe in oneself, a sound mind that thinks positively in the midst of threat and a\r\nWeek 42 ends here and week 43 starts below\r\nmind that continues to build in the midst of threat. Every defeat starts from the mind, hence\r\nwe must fortify our mind with the word of God and protect it from every fear and mockery of\r\nthe enemy. You must adopt the concept of building and battling! No stoppage, no excuse. In\r\nthe early days of TACEF when many were banned from meeting in the church for prayers,\r\nthey did not give up and stop praying. They found an alternative to pray from house to house\r\nwith all fervency, joy and no feeling of offense to those who abused or maligned them. They\r\ncontinued in prayers with no ill feeling until the breakthrough came and those who sent\r\nthem out of the church gladly opened the door for them.', '2018-12-04 13:47:05'),
(96, 77, 'A mind to work only comes from prayer. No revival work can go beyond the prayers that\r\npower the mind to work. Prayer is the fuel of the mind and the more we refresh it in prayers,\r\nthe more we attune it to work in the midst of worst affliction and threats.', '2018-12-04 13:47:05'),
(97, 77, 'The call for balance in the ministry of rebuilding is also very critical for us as God\'s people. If\r\nNehemiah\'s men were able to continue the work while they held the sword, we have no\r\nexcuse to be a failure or second-class citizen because of the assumed excuse that our being\r\nbusy in the work of God is the reason for academic, career or marital failure. No, the fact that\r\nyou serve God is the reason why you must be the best. This speaks to balance-priority per\r\ntime, time management, discipline and continuous self-development.', '2018-12-04 13:47:05'),
(98, 79, 'The road to revival usually will have speed bumps, sharp turns, and some potholes. It is\r\nnever a straight line. Oppositions will come and will get to the point of fake prophecy. TACEF\r\nhas its fair share of fake prophecies at the early stage of the vision. Many so-called men of\r\nGod even attempted to sow fears in the heart of the leader with statements like, “Revival\r\nwork cannot work in your church – run away for your life. The heaven over your church is\r\nclosed etc.” The enemy indeed used different tactics to try and stop the work. <b><i>The power of\r\ndiscernment and certainty of divine leading were the guarantees of the bearing of this\r\nmandate and will always be as the Lord lives.</i></b>', '2018-12-04 19:23:24'),
(99, 79, 'It has been said that there is no victory if there is no battle. Successful revivals of the past\r\nhave been hard-fought in the place of prayers, as men and women sacrificed their all to see a\r\nmove of God transform people and circumstances.\r\nBe careful of the enemy\'s invitation to “come down to the plain of Ono”. Be careful when you\r\nare invited to join a social club, a relaxation group, a virtual meet-up, a special caucus etc.\r\nThe “plain of Ono” is the path of compromise and destruction and like Nehemiah, you must\r\nbe bold to challenge every deception of the enemy and never give in.', '2018-12-04 19:23:24'),
(100, 81, 'The reason why the wall was built was not to add to city decoration. It was to provide\r\nprotection from invaders so that God\'s people could live securely in comfort to serve and\r\nworship God in spirit and in truth. When the wall of our career success is built and we grow\r\ntall in excellence to go into nations, the intention is not to become a “big man” but to use the\r\nplatform for the service of the kingdom. It is a pain today when a vibrant Christian gets a job in\r\na multinational and he uses excuses like“I am too busy” or “I can\'t travel for outreaches into\r\nthose local villages” or “I can\'t relate with certain people again”. We must be aware as\r\nTACEFites again and again that every lifting we receive from the Lord is to expand and\r\nWeek 48 ends here and week 49 starts below\r\nincrease the work of God in our hands. He lifts us up so that His work can be lifted. He will\r\nmake you go into nations so that His work can also go into nations.', '2018-12-04 19:36:59'),
(101, 81, 'In this study, we also see the importance of sustaining victory through the ministry of\r\nwatchmen. We must be watchmen who guard the ports of entry of our lives, our families,\r\nour businesses, and our ministries from being infiltrated by the enemy. We must not go to\r\nsleep after a major victory in life, but we must continue to keep watch since the devil will\r\nnever stop his attempts to steal, kill, and destroy (John 10:10) until the Lord returns and this\r\npresent age comes to an end.1 Peter 5:8 warns us, “Be of sober spirit, be on the alert. Your\r\nadversary the devil prowls around like a roaring lion, seeking someone to devour”. We need\r\nto watch out for the spiritual dangers that Satan strews across our paths, to avoid falling into\r\nsins that would destroy us. As married couples, be alert to the dangers that could destroy\r\nyour marriage. As parents, be alert to the dangers that could destroy your children. As\r\nfellowship leaders, be alert to the dangers that could damage God\'s flock. The enemy often\r\nhits right after a victory. Be especially careful, be vigilant and always watch and pray.', '2018-12-04 19:36:59'),
(102, 81, 'Many Christians have lost their businesses, their health, and other important aspects of\r\ntheir lives because they failed to keep watch and guard against the devices of the\r\nenemy.Jesus warns us frequently to be on the alert (Mark 13:34-37).', '2018-12-04 19:36:59'),
(103, 81, 'Also be driven by posterity and think about the future at all times. Look beyond today as you\r\ncarefully invest in quality leadership who will do better than you when you are not there.\r\nNehemiah knew that Jerusalem would need to be left in the hands and care of competent\r\npeople who could continue to successfully run affairs after he was gone. We cannot be\r\nmyopic in revival, but we must look into the future and make preparations today. We must\r\nstart raising quality leaders who will carry the burden of the vision in 20-50 years even while\r\nthey are still in the children\'s church. We must not give away our children church to a place of\r\nplay, play and play. It must be a place of envisioning and spiritual development as we see\r\nthem in the light of the great future. TACEF Seed of Purpose 7 pillars capture the heartbeat of\r\nGod to raise a generation under whose wings the vision will fly further and further and we\r\nowe God everything it takes to build them on these critical pillars of greatness using the age based\r\ndevelopmental series and right home-based interventions as advised in the series.', '2018-12-04 19:36:59'),
(104, 82, 'For spiritual renewal to happen and to be sustained, God\'s people must read His Word. There\r\nmust be a new passion for the word of God and a brighter light of revelation knowledge. The\r\nsame energy with which many will pray all night must also be applied to study the word of\r\nGod all night because how do you pray well if you do not know the mind of God.', '2018-12-04 19:46:17'),
(105, 82, 'We also see the place of understanding—that is a hearing with depth, application and\r\nimpact. Having ears that work does not guarantee that we really hear. Although God made us\r\nwith two ears that are permanently opened, which we cannot close, and one mouth that we\r\ncan open and close. This is a big message. Always let your two ears be permanently opened\r\nto hear me in double fold (2 ears) before you speak with one mouth (which can be open only\r\nwhen necessary). <b>We have two ears and one mouth so that we can listen twice as much as\r\nwe speak.</b>', '2018-12-04 19:46:17'),
(106, 82, 'Do you apply your mind sincerely to the word of God or are you thinking about a business\r\ntarget, GPA etc. with a distracted mind after you have spent only ten minutes reading the\r\nBible? That\'s why Jesus often said, “He who has ears to hear, let him hear” (Mark 4:9, 23). He\r\nsaid, “Take care how you listen…” (Luke 8:18). This is a call to listen to the word of God with\r\nattention and reverence and consciously avoid every form of mind travel or distraction.\r\nWe have also seen that the difference is usually clear when we hear the Holy Spirit preaching\r\nthrough a man versus a man preaching in his own knowledge. We can also appreciate the\r\nimpact and result produced when the word is preached as a download from heaven rather\r\nthan mere intellectual exercise. The Word of God must come forth in power to do its\r\nintended work as we learn in our last spiritual year in 2 Timothy 3:16, where we saw two\r\nthings the Word of God is profitable for: reproof and correction, which are often associated\r\nwith tears and deep inner pain which propels repentance and consecration. May the word of\r\nthe Lord be fresh in our heart again and again.', '2018-12-04 19:46:17'),
(107, 83, 'There will not be national revival until there is national repentance. There cannot be serious\r\nchanges in our society without revival agents standing up to intercede and activate an\r\natmosphere of repentance and change. In our study, this does not mean that every single Jew\r\nin Judea repented, but it does mean that the majority did, and there was a consensus to live\r\nrighteously in obedience to God. Prayer of intercession created a dense atmosphere of god consciousness,\r\nwhich provoked many unto repentance and sincere change. This only starts\r\nwith genuine heart-felt intercession for nations, where we genuinely confess our trespasses\r\nand the trespasses of our past leaders (spiritual and political). This is where we seek the face\r\nof the Lord to heal our land from the errors of those from the past, which has now led to our\r\ncurrent situation today, and to heal us from the damage wehave done with our own hands.', '2018-12-04 19:55:43'),
(108, 83, 'Nigeria is overdue for genuine national revival that is based on the concept of“Righteousness\r\nexalts a nation”. We have to care about exalting our nation, and the only way that will happen\r\nis by a change of heart from sin to righteousness. We need preachers to preach for this\r\nchange,and God\'s people who are in positions of influence to take action as true mediators of\r\nnational intercessors. In essence, we are birthing the kingdom of God in every sphere of life,\r\nas we begin to bring some level of His kingdom into the earth today. He said,“The kingdom of\r\nGod is within you” (Luke 17:21). He also said we should make the following petition to our\r\nheavenly Father when we pray: “Our Father which art in heaven, Hallowed be thy name, Thy\r\nkingdom come. Thy will be done, <b>as in heaven, so in earth</b>” (Luke 11:2). Let the experiences of\r\nthe kingdom take over our nations we pray.', '2018-12-04 19:55:43');
(109, 85,'Our foundation in the knowledge of God determines how far we can go with God. A singer sang, “ I want more of You, I want more of You Jesus, The more I know You, The more I want to know You, Jesus more of You”. This song is the heart cry of everyone who is seeking to build a sure foundation in a continuous non-stopping knowledge of God.','2019-10-31 12:28:19');
(110, 85,'There is no better time to fortify ourselves in the knowledge of God than now. We must seek to know God more than ever before. God created us to love Him. Our primary purpose is to love God and be loved by Him, to know God intimately and have a loving relationship with Him. If a man does not have that love, he does not meet his reason for being created.','2019-10-31 12:29:19');
(111, 85,'This foundation of the knowledge of God must be fortified with fear and love. Fearing and loving God means the recognition that He is holy and awesome, and that we cannot take the relationship we have with Him for granted through sin. In as much as He is a loving father, those who have the right foundation of the knowledge of God respectfully serve God in reverence and genuine fear. They serve God in holiness even when they know that He is ever forgiving and always loving.','2019-10-31 12:29:19');
(112, 86,'Many today have failed to see the difference between Religion and Relationship. Many only practice Christianity because it is what is in now in vogue that everyone is doing. Many do not have a genuine knowledge of the Lord and have assumed that being a beneficiary of a miracle or participating in an altar call where a deliverance session was held is the same as having a meaningful relationship. Have you wondered that after the so-called 100days prayer session and fasting, these individuals still find it so easy to lie, cheat, fornicate. Why? Because the most important entity of intimacy with God- the heart- has not been brought into a place of genuine repentance and reconnection to God.','2019-10-31 12:30:19');
(113, 86,'There is a huge difference between acknowledging Christ mentally (head knowledge only) and receiving Him into your heart (your innermost being). Outward religious practices without an internal transformation is like a beautiful house without foundations and pillars.','2019-10-31 12:31:19');
(114, 86,'With this understanding, it is important that we are sure we know God and God knows us in a personal genuine encounter in the place of salvation. It is not wrong to ask again – AM I REALLY SURE I AM BORN AGAIN? Can you recall the day and the experience that followed? If it was a meaningful encounter, it is likely you will remember with clarity the transformation that began from this period. If this is not the reality in your life, do not pretend going on a long journey with a deflated tyre. Like a smart driver, park aside, remove the leaking tyre and get a new one.','2019-10-31 12:32:19');
(115, 86,'In the same vein, we must willingly invest the time needed in getting to know God even more. We have to spend time and conscious efforts in His Word, in Prayer, in Meditation, in Fasting, in learning how to deny the flesh and walk in the Spirit. God reveals more and more of Himself when He sees that we thirst for a vibrant relationship with Him. No wonder, Apostle Paul after many years of serving God, cried out, “That I may know Him” Phil 3 vs 10.','2019-10-31 12:33:19');
(116, 87,'Our prayer and word life are the backbone of our relationship with God. Misunderstanding of these two cornerstones will cause our spiritual building to collapse. We have been given a privilege through prayer to be able to talk to the eternal Creator. What a privilege?  However, this does not permit us to abuse this gift. While God wants us to express ourselves to Him freely at all times, He does not expect us to become wayward in our prayer life. We cannot be asking for fancy fabulous material things, which is serving mammon or flashy things to gratify the flesh. God also does not  expect us to pray for destruction of other humans who are our enemies, but rather bless them and pray for their salvation. Prayer must come from a place of understanding God’s nature.','2019-10-31 12:33:19');
(117, 87,'In addition, the liveliness of our Word life depends first and foremost on whether we are genuinely born again, because it is the Spirit who reveals Biblical truths to the reader. It is He who teaches us proper exegesis of His Word so that we can avoid false teachers and false doctrines. Incorrect interpretation always leads to misapplication in real life.','2019-10-31 12:34:19');
(118, 88,'Unless we realise who we are in Christ, we will not reach our potential strength in God. The mandate of greatness upon the great house of TACEF is tied to each one knowing who we are and have become in Christ. We only become what we know, accept and practise','2019-10-31 12:35:19');
(119, 88,'As a child of God and true revival agent, be persuaded that your new ID card bears this list of descriptions with God:','2019-10-31 12:36:19');
(120, 88,'•	You are His own special possession. (1 Peter 2:9, Deuteronomy 14:2)','2019-10-31 12:36:19');
(121, 88,'•	You are chosen, handpicked by the God who created the universe. (1 Peter 2:9, Jeremiah 1:5, Ephesians 1:3-4)','2019-10-31 12:37:19');
(122, 88,'•	You are treasured. (Deuteronomy 7:6 14:2, 26:18)','2019-10-31 12:38:19');
(123, 88,'•	You are irreplaceable. (1 Thessalonians 1:4)','2019-10-31 12:39:19');
(124, 88,'•	You are loved beyond compare. (1 John 4:19, 4:10, 3:16, Romans 5:8, 8:35-39)','2019-10-31 12:40:19');
(125, 88,'•	You are worth dying for. (1 John 3:16, Romans 5:7-9)','2019-10-31 12:41:19');
(126, 88,'•	You are forgiven. (Ephesians 1:7, 1 John 1:9, Romans 8:1, 33-39)','2019-10-31 12:42:19');
(127, 88,'•	You are His child. (1 John 3:1, Galatians 3:26)','2019-10-31 12:43:19');
(128, 88,'•	You are secured for all eternity. (2 Corinthians 1:22, John 10:28-29)','2019-10-31 12:44:19');
(129, 88,'•	You are set free. (Romans 6:18, Galatians 5:1)','2019-10-31 12:45:19');
(130, 88,'•	You are precious to Him. (Isaiah 43:4)','2019-10-31 12:46:19');
(131, 88,'•	You are set apart. (John 15:16, 19, I Peter 2:9)','2019-10-31 12:47:19');
(131, 88,'It is also important we receive these truths with humility because we have received this not by our works but by the grace of God. This is complete act of unmerited favour that we do not ordinarily qualify for. ','2019-10-31 12:47:19');
(132, 90,'Salvation is God’s greatest gift to humanity and it must be treated as such. One can better appreciate why Paul admonished us all to work out our salvation with fear and trembling. “Therefore, my beloved, as you have always obeyed, so now, not only as in my presence but much more in my absence, work out your own salvation with fear and trembling, for it is God who works in you, both to will and to work for his good pleasure”. (Philippians 2:12-13)','2019-10-31 12:48:19');
(133, 90,'But why do we need to work out our salvation when works do not save us? We know that truly that we are saved by God’s unconditional grace through the gift of faith, the works we do prove that our faith is real. Works are evidence of genuine salvation but works never qualified us for salvation.','2019-10-31 12:49:19');
(134, 90,'For emphasis, the phrase, “Work out…” as applied in working something out is to prove it to be true. When we work out a mathematics problem, we are not fundamentally changing the answer. Two plus two always equals four. What we do daily is to balance this equation or work it out – that is - add up what is right, subtract what should be eliminated, multiply those things that must be evident so that we arrive at the desired answer. In other words, God has already done the work of salvation in us – He has saved us, forgiven us, rescued us, put his Holy Spirit in us, and united us to Jesus. That glorious work has already been done. But, that does not mean that we simply sit back and do nothing. Never. We are called to do good works as a way of showing that God does indeed live in us. These good works in NO way earn our salvation. They are simply proof of what God has already done in us. This is captured well in James 2:14, “What good is it, my brothers, if someone says he has faith but does not have works?”','2019-10-31 12:50:19');
(134, 90,'We must also note the verse, where we realise that the “working” out is also done by God in us.  Paul says, “…for it is God who works in you, both to will and to work for his good pleasure.” ','2019-10-31 12:51:19');
(135, 90,'This understanding that we are saved by His grace will cause us to be more faithful in our service to Him. This awareness will prevent us from falling into spiritual pride and will be the reason we will not go back to our vomit. It will be the compelling reason why our roots will go deep in God, helping us establish a firm foundation in Him which cannot be shaken by any challenges of life.','2019-10-31 12:52:19');
(136, 91,'Genuine repentance leads to a desire to redress wrongs. When someone becomes a Christian, he will have a desire born of deep conviction to do good, and that includes making  restitution whenever possible. The idea of “whenever possible” is crucially important to remember. There are some crimes and sins for which there is no adequate restitution. In such instances, a Christian should make some form of restitution that demonstrates repentance, but at the same time, does not need to feel guilty about the inability to make full restitution. Restitution is to be a result of our salvation—it is not a requirement for salvation. If you have received forgiveness of sins through faith in Jesus Christ, all of your sins are forgiven, whether or not you have been able to make restitution for them','2019-10-31 12:53:19');
(137, 91,'The summary of this teaching is that those who have turned from sin must also seek ways to correct wrongs and damages done to others in the past. This is one of the practical fruits of true repentance and godly sorrow. Money and material goods are usually the sort of items involved, but we may have slandered someone’s name or hurtfully deceived a person, and now we must correct those wrongs. If it is simply not possible to make amends for genuine reasons, we can talk to God and He will clear our conscience, because He sees that we want to restore but literally cannot. Restitution does not save us, no, but it is a sign that a person is indeed saved and is following the way of Christ. Zacchaeus made restitution without being told to do so, because genuine repentance and salvation had come into his heart through an encounter with Christ Jesus our Lord and Saviour.','2019-10-31 12:54:19');
(138, 91,'The cost of restitution is high and this is why you must be careful of the foundation that you are laying today. Avoid things that you will regret tomorrow. Can you imagine a Christian who is progressing in his career using a false date of birth is exposed when he gets to the peak of his career through another document he never knew existed. Are we going to say this is the work of the devil or the person’s failure to address issues when they should? Live a glorious Christian life in all purity, transparency and decency because when the demand of restitution comes, it comes at a cost. This is the time to settle your foundational errors before they rise to attack tomorrow. ','2019-10-31 12:55:19');
(139, 92,'A Christian that is living in sin, fear and torment is just existing without fulfilling the divine agenda for his/her life. One of the dangers of living without the authority of Christ as a believer is that such person may end up in hell because our authority in Christ is a complete package that involves power over sin, self and all the activities of the enemies. Such Christians may not be able to overcome sin and therefore end up in hell fire. The secret of success in life is embedded in the authority given to us in Christ Jesus.','2019-10-31 12:55:19');
(140, 92,'The keys of the kingdom of heaven are already in our hands and God expects us to bind and loose, He expects us to rule and dominate. The initial plan of God for Adam that was lost in the garden of Eden has been reactivated and restored. It is back and better and in a better package for us as New Testament believers and we have to fully maximize this golden opportunity. Any child of God that is not using his/her authority in Christ is a prodigal son and he/she is not even worthy to be called a servant of God, talk less of a child. It is time to arise and take our place in the kingdom.','2019-10-31 12:56:19');
(141, 93,'God wants us to know His will. He only requires that we become willing to do things His way as He reveals them to us. As we saw in the study, the first step is to come into obedience and agreement with His written Word. Jesus emphasised obedience to His Father’s will. If we are not willing to obey what is written in His Word, then He will not be willing to reveal His more specific plans for our individual lives.','2019-10-31 12:57:19');
(142, 93,'God has a will or plan for our lives. We are not a mistake; we are God's master plan. Predestined and called for specific purpose from the foundation of the earth. Also, God is interested in every aspects of our lives and He has a plan for each of them. So, we must know and be sure that it is the will of God to reveal His will and plan to us','2019-10-31 12:58:19');
(143, 93,'We must also be willing to surrender our will in order to do what God wants. Even Jesus said, “Not my will but thine be done”. We must surrender our own plans in order to follow His. Who you want to marry may not be right for you?  Or what you want to study in school, or what kind of business you want to open, etc. Allow God to lead your life and you will get the best results. It is not every open door that is yours; hence, the need to build a spiritual life that can relate and hear with God.','2019-10-31 12:59:19');
(144, 93,'God does not want us to live in confusion and uncertainty. Learn to trust God for His best and build an intimacy with Him whereby you can ask Him how He wants you to use the gifts and talents He has given you. Ask Him questions about each area of your life and He will give you direction.','2019-10-31 12:59:19');
(145, 95,'Many of us live busy lives. We hear all sorts of voices each day from people around us and from electronic media. Hearing God’s voice in the midst of all the clamour will require deliberate action on our part. He will not compete with other voices to get our attention, especially if we are already born-again after He has called us out of the old way of life. If we value His guidance, then we will seek it at all cost. We will go the extra mile. He has given us His written word as a primary guide. For more specific decision-making, we will need to hear from Him on that particular circumstance so we can know what to do.','2019-10-31 13:00:19');
(146, 95,'Do not be like those who fast and pray to hear God because there is a problem or because there is a decision to be made. Let it be a daily experience and not an emergency action. Don’t be like those who will go on seven days marathon or visit a prayer mountain, even when they have not maintained a daily quiet time for months and years. They are emergency solution seekers and not a sheep that the great shepherd is leading.  ','2019-10-31 13:01:19');
(147, 95,'A major thing we must practice is setting time apart when we can totally focus on God in prayers and study of His word. It is this type of discipline that helps us to learn how to tell the difference between our own voice, the voice of the enemy, and that special “still small voice” which comes from God alone.','2019-10-31 13:02:19');
(148, 95,'We must also be aware that God is willing to use other avenues to communicate with us, including dreams, prophets, and even inner witness. Jesus said the pure in heart will see God (Matt. 5:8), so our inward purity is a critical factor if we must hear God speak to us. Getting a word from God can be the difference between a high-quality decision or a disastrous decision in important areas of life. It will serve the Christian well to regularly tune into the Lord’s frequency as a regular way of life. Knowing how to recognise God’s voice will help us in building a strong foundation in our relationship with Him. We will not be deceived or misled if we invest the time needed to learn how to hear and know God when He speaks to us.','2019-10-31 13:02:19');
(149, 96,'In this study, we have discovered that the very first thing to do in becoming a disciple of our Lord Jesus is to be born again. As soon as a man is born again, he is expected to enrol in a discipleship relationship with Jesus. Also, we are to take the yoke upon our necks and be ready to follow Jesus. The only thing that makes yoke-bearing easy is a willing submission unto the leadership of the Lord in our lives. Bearing our cross connotes willingly sacrificing ourselves for the things of God. A sacrifice has to cost the offerer something or it would not be a sacrifice.','2019-10-31 13:03:19');
(150, 96,'Remember, when you enter into a discipleship relationship with Jesus, He will endure with you until you become what He wants you to be.','2019-10-31 13:03:19');
(151, 98,'One of the major ship that will convey true Christians to the shore of the kingdom of God is discipleship. It is a consistent, continual and continuous relationship with God and it has to be measurable, progressive, productive and fruitful. All the children of God must submit themselves and be enrolled in the school of discipleship where you can play a dual role as a student and a lecturer at the same time. They will be making disciples of others as they are being discipled It is a core course that one cannot afford to carry.','2019-10-31 13:04:19');
(152, 98,'As we follow Christ and also climb the shoulders of fathers and mothers that are following Christ, our lives will continue to produce like people and from generations to generations, Christ like people and not just religious people will be born and made into the kingdom. If you refuse to bear fruits and make disciples of others, then, you are a prodigal child of God and a waster of divine investments. God will be disappointed in you and he will pack such people aside to recruit men that will not be fruitless and barren.','2019-10-31 13:05:19');
(153, 99,'The whole essence of life is to live for God. To surrender all at the feet of the son of God who died for us. If He gave His life for us, nothing should be too big for us to let go for Him. He expects us to spend every time and moment of our lives pleasing Him and satisfying His intentions.','2019-10-31 13:06:19');
(154, 99,'If anything is too big for you to let go, you need to go back to Calvary and rededicate your life to God and drop everything on the altar. God can ask for anything from us as His children. Abraham our father has laid a good example for us when he laid his Isaac on the altar.','2019-10-31 13:08:19');
(155, 99,'A surrendered, consecrated, sanctified, holy, obedient lifestyle that exemplifies that attributes of Christ is the greatest worship that you can give to God!','2019-10-31 13:10:19');
(156, 100,'As many as are led by the Spirit, they are the sons of God (Rom. 8:14), and you can only be led when you take a walk with the Spirit of God. Our lives depend on this for without Him we are nothing. The foundation of our Christian faith starts and ends with the Spirit of God for through Him we were saved, and through Him we are currently sealed till the day of showing forth. He has a lot to reveal to us. Our Lord Jesus said, “He will guide us into all truth”. Not walking in Him is like someone doing scuba diving without an oxygen tank. Instant obedience to the promptings of the Spirit endears us to Him more and more, and also allows Him to reveal more truth to us. Let’s lay hold on this important part of our Christian foundation by deliberately walking in the Spirit every day of our lives.','2019-10-31 13:11:19');
